T1  - Ovulatory response rate with human menopausal gonadotropins of varying FSH/LH ratios
A1  - Jacobson A.
A1  - Marshall J.R.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - In a study of the importance of the FSH/LH ratio in human menopausal gonadotropins, HMG, used to induce ovulation, HMG was given as a single injecion to oligo ovulatory and anovulatory women on Day 1, and HCG, on Day 9, A FSH dose for each patient was selected which would give an ovulatory rate of 60-70% for an HMG preparation with an FSH/LH ratio of 0.14. Then, in each patient, 3 HMG preparations with FSH/LH ratios of 0.14, u* and 3.0, reapevtively, were compared at the selected FSH doses. The HMG preparation with least LH or highest FSH/LH was significantly less effective in including ovulation than were the other preparations. It was postulated that each individual has an ovulatory threshold dose for both FSH and LH.
