N2  - Clomiphene was administered to 31 married women, aged 25 35 yr, in the treatment of various disorders (secondary amenorrhoea, sterility, panhypo oligomenorrhoea with monophasic cycles). The biological response to the drug was studied as well as oestrogen, progesterone and 17 ketosteroid excretion and serum transaminase levels (assessment of possible liver damage). The conclusion is drawn that clomiphene must be regarded as the most suitable drug for the treatment of anovuiation in certain cases. With the experimental doses, side effects were slight and of short duration. Induced ovulation is often followed by spontaneous cycles.
