N2  - Studip.s with labelled steroids have suggested that in follicular tissue two interrelated pathways are involved in the production of C1., and C1. steroids, one involving hydroxysteroids us intermediaries and the other keto steroids. In addition, in some instances theA 3/J hydroxysteroids may be quantitatively more important. In micropolycystic ovaries the tissues are potentially very active except in the production of phenolic steroids, and more C1., steroids, especially androstenedtone accumulate in the incubation media. After ovulation and formation of a corpus luteum the 3beta dehydrogenase and Abeta activity appears to increase, with an associated decrease in lyase activity. These combined effects result in an accumulation of progesterone and other C., steroids with beta4 3 ketone group. There is only a small accumulation of C1- steroids due to their rapid aromatization to phenolic steraids and reduction to products with a Sa configuration. In addition, incubation studies with C1, substrates indicate a low reductase activity in this tissue. The low lyase and reductase activity may be explained by a high level of progesterone a both of these enzyme systems.
