T1  - Dermatoglyphic patterns in pure gonadal dysgencsis (PGD)
A1  - Loesch D.
A1  - Boczkowski K.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Dermatoglyphic data, obtained from 14 cases of pure gonadal dysgenesis are presented. The present investigation included the qualitative analysis of palm prints as well as some measurements, such as the atd angle, ridge width, total ridge count (TRC) and ulnar loop count (ULC)L The position of TRC and ULC means obtained in cases of pure gonadal dysgenesis with 46,XX karyotype is closer to the means for Turner's syndrome, than to normal females with 46,XX karyotype. The results suggest that in cases of pure gonadal dysgenesis with 46JCX karyotype the lack of the hormonal influence of active fetal ovaries diminishes the effect of X chromosome on pattern size; another possibility is that an invisible abnormality of one of the X chromosomes, is present in such cases.
