T1  - A study of induction of ovulation in Macaca Mulatta
A1  - Balin H.
A1  - Wan L.S.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Twenty-three amenorrheic/anovulatory sexually mature rhesus monkeys were treated with HMG/HCG for a total of 30 treatment cycles. Ovulation was induced in 74% of the animals in 60% of treatment cycles. By contrast, a control group of 20 animals studied for 34 cycles showed an ovulation rate of less than 5% for both animals and cycles. Multiple ovulation was observed in only 46% of the cycles studied. No changes in the zona pellucida of ova were seen in treated animals. It is inferred that the ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome following use of menotropic principles is due to the additive effect of the same on pretreatment levels of endogenous gonadotropins. Basal body temperature telemetry in the rhesus monkey is valuable as an index of ovulation.
