T1  - Anovular corpus luteum in a woman taking an oral contraceptive
A1  - Ludwig K.S.
A1  - Horowitz M.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - A regressing anovular corpus luteum with well preserved ovum and corona radiata cells in the ovary of a woman treated during three cycles with an estrogen progestogen combination is described. Compared with the alterations found during the second treatment cycle in a corpus luteum formed during the first treatment cycle, the conclusion is that it must be the regressing corpus luteum of the first treatment cycle, and it must be approximately 65 days old at time of examination. The good condition of ovum and corona radiata cells may be due to the effect of medicated steroids.
