T1  - Epidemic parotiditis and female sterility
T3  - Parotite epidemica e sterilita' femminlle
A1  - Debiasi D.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - The incidence of epidemic parotiditis among 200 sterile women and among 200 fertile ones was investigated. It was found that 127 out of the 200 sterile women and 98 out of the 200 fertile ones had had parotiditis. There is thus a significant difference between the two groups, which clearly shows that the incidence of this disease is higher among sterile women than among fertile ones. The parotiditis localization at the ovarian level would bring about some changes which might cause some disturbance of ovulation. The suggestion is put forward to try to induce ovulation by means of clomiphene or gonadotropins.
