T1  - Results of chromosomal analysis in Stein Leventhal's syndrome (with reference to the etiology of this syndrome)
T3  - Chromosomenanalytische befunde bei Stein Leventhal syndrom (beitrag zur atiologie des stein leventhal syndroms)
A1  - Knorr K.
A1  - Knorr Gartner H.
A1  - Uebele Kallhardt B.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Cytogenetic studies on the peripheral blood and polycystic ovaries were carried out on 16 female patients with a Stein Leventhal syndrone. In all cases a normal female karyotype (46, XX) was observed. There was no evidence for a kryptomosaicism of the gonads. The results are discussed in the context of previously published observations and lead to the conclusion that a chromosomal anomaly (especially an anomaly of the sex chromosomes), detectable by present cytogenetic methods, is not involved in the etiology of this disease. Furthermore, there is no evidence of a relationship between the Stein Leventhal syndrome and gonadal dysgenesis on the basis of chromosomal abnormalities. These conclusions do not exclude the possibility that gene defects may be involved in the Stein Leventhal syndrome.
