T1  - Experiences with a 2-phase preparation for contraception and the treatment of gynecologic affections
T3  - Erfahrungen mit einem 2-phasen-praparat zur antikonzeption und behandlung gynakologischer erkrankungen
A1  - Wittlinger H.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Personal experience and morphological studies on a biphasic anovulatory drug (CG 527, commercially available as Eunomin) in 48 women over 514 cycles is reported. In gynecological indications the preparation was especially satisfactory for the treatment of functional bleeding disorders and for anomalous cycles. For contraception the biphasic anovulatory substance was found to be reliable; after continuous treatment during the first and second cycles side effects were rarely observed. Histological studies in the second cycle phase showed a nonuniform picture. In addition to normally intensive proliferation with almost complete secretory transformation mucosae with slight proliferation or almost devoid of function were observed, especially after treatment for a longer period. The conclusion often expressed in the literature, according to which the administration of biphasic anovulatory substances leads to proliferation corresponding to the physiological state and secretory transformation of the endometrium could not be confirmed. Cytological examination and comparison with untreated women and especially with women treated with a monophasic anovulatory substance revealed that with the biphasic preparation the es trogen activity was distinctly increased.
