T1  - Congenital malformation and Stein-Leventhal syndrome
T3  - Malformacion congenita y sindrome de stein leventhal
A1  - Esteves F.A.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - A very unusual case of genital abnormality is reported: A patient with complete duplication from introitus to fundus, together with a Stein Leventhal syndrome. Excision of the vaginal septa and wedge ovarian resection, restored normal intercourse and menstrual functions, respectively. In this young woman the vaginal septa were removed too, to expose both cervices to a single vagina. A review of the literature concerning congenital anomalies of the female genital tract was made. It was found that of ail women exhibit any form of malformation of the genital tract. Between 25 and 40% of women with double uteri have no disturbances and do not need surgery. Hystcrosalpingography should be done preoperatively to establish the exact size of the uterine bodies and patency of at least one tube. Pneumopelvigraphy was helpful to the exact diagnosis in the case reported. The Strassmann metroplasty is a constructive procedure which provides a physiologic union, that nature forgot to complete.
