AN  - 289035118
T1  - Lipids in the tissue of the ovary in Stein Leventhal's syndrome
A1  - Bronshtein M.E.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - The results are presented of histochemical study of lipids (total, free and bound cholesterol, triglycerides and fatty acids) in the resected ovarian tissue of 54 patients with Stein Leventhal's syndrome and in 10 apparently healthy women of reproductive age. Cholesterol (free and bound forms) proved to be the main histochemically detectable lipid of ovarian tissue in both groups examined. A distinct topographic association of cholesterol and the main structures of the ovaries, responsible for biosynthesis of sex hormones existed. The cause of the detected reverse relationship between the level of secretory activity of the glandular cells of the ovaries and cholesterol content in them is discussed.
