T3  - Humant hypofysegonadotropin i behandlingen af anovulatoriske sterilitetspatienter
A1  - Pedersen P.H.
A1  - Larsen J.F.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Progress has been made in the treatment of certain anovuiar conditions by the production of preparations with follicle stimulating effects from human material. The treatment, however, is associated with a certain, though slight amount of risk. As one is concerned with women whose only complaint is absence of menstrual bleeding or sterility, treatment must be reserved for cases in which the excretion of hypophyseal gonadotropin in the urine is absent or slight as the risk is lowest in these patients. During treatment, the patients should be submitted to regular hormone analysis and vaginal examinations. Selection of cases for treatment and particularly for observation during treatment involves such great technical difficulties that these women should be referred to departments with a particular interest and with experience in the subject Treatment is still in an experimental stage and therefore all the patients should be registered and followed up.
