T1  - Treatment of amenorrheas and oligomenorrheas with a new retrosteroid substance ro 4 8347
T3  - LE TRAITEMENT des AMENORRHEES et des OUGOMENORRHEES PAR le RETROSTEROiDE RO 4 8347
A1  - Gerhard L.
A1  - Stamm O.-
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - A new stereo isomer of progesterone, RO 4-8347, was used to treat acute and chronic secondary amenorrhea of functional ovarian origin. A single course of treatment with 4-8 mg daily for 10 days restored menstrual flow in 40 out of 48 patients. Three became pregnant immediately. There were only 5 failures, attributable to organic abnormalities. RO 4-8347 was also given successfully for prolonged courses to regulate the cycle and thus permit conception. It also restored ovulation in 73 out of 128 cycles. Ovulation and pregnancies were also obtained in several cases of Stein Leventhal syndrome. This form of treatment, which is very well tolerated, appears to correct 3 essential points in functional amenorrhea: it restores menstruation and ovulation and stimulates progesterone secretion.
