AN  - 290040926
T1  - Induction of ovulation
A1  - Nelson T.E.
Y1  - 1969//
N2  - Recent advances in the knowledge and understanding of ovulation have made it possible for many oligo or anovulatory females to conceive and bear normal, healthy and viable infants. Clomiphene citrate effectively induces ovulation in many females who have an intact hypothalamic pituitary ovarian axis. Although reversible, there are dosage related side effects which should be watched closely. There is also a noteworthy incidence of multiple births (super ovulatory), and an increased incidence of pregnancy wastage. It is stressed that clomiphene citrate is not a panacea of the anovulatory state. Further researching of the literature shows the tremendous strides being undertaken in the usage of human pituitary gonadotropin (HPG), human menopausal gonadotropin (HMG)1 human chorionic gonadotropin (HCXS). These compounds are not marketable at this time and are primarily research tools, but they show further indications for pregnancy successes where there is no irreversible ovarian failure.
