AN  - 290074323
T1  - Endocervical inhibition of sperm capacitation by norgestrel contraception
A1  - Roland M.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Norgestrel, a totally synthesized gonane nor derivative of testosterone, was given to 60 patients for evaluation of its contraceptive efficacy. The compound was given continuously in daily microdoses without supplemental estrogen. Standard tests of cervical function and endometrial aspirations as part of the post coital test were carried out before, during, and after treatment. No conceptions occurred. All tests gave noraml or nearly normal results, with the exception of endometrial aspiration performed within two to three hr post coitum. No sperm were seen in the endometrial cavity in 239 determinations. In one instance a solitary, poorly motile spermatozoon was seen in the aspirate. It would appear that norgestrel in the dosage prevents access of sperm into the endometrial cavity. In turn, this suggests that norgestrel interferes pharmacologically with sperm capacitation. If this interpretation is correct, a previously mechanism of interference with fertility is involved. Microdose contraception with norgestrel may prove to be a more physiologic antifertility regiemn that older hormonal methods. Fourteen patients with naturally occurring infertility due to nonimmunologic interference with sperm capacitation in the cervix are currently under study.
