T1  - Functional classification of patients selected for gonadotropic therapy
A1  - Insler V.
A1  - Melmed H.
A1  - Mashiah S.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - A classification of patients selected for gonadotropic therapy is proposed, based on the level of urinary gonadotropins and the presence or lack of endogenous estrogen activity. A total of 264 treatment courses given to 133 patients so classified were analyzed. Group I comprised patients with low or !indetectable urinary gonadotropins and no evidence of endogenous estrogen activity. Group II consisted of patients with urinary gonadotropins in the normal range and evidence of endogenous estrogen activity. Patients with postpartum amenorrhea and galactorrhea formed a separate group (Ia). It was shown that Group I differed significantly from Group II in dose requirement and duration of therapy. On the other hand, no significant differences between various subgroups within the main Groups I and II could be found. A theoretical explanation underlying the proposed classification is suggested. The individual nature of the response in each patient is emphasised.
