T1  - Total gonadotropin and LH excretion in cases of menstrual cycle attentions and of Stein Leventhal syndrome under clomiphene treatment
A1  - Morresi G.
A1  - Ingrassia F.
A1  - Barciulli F.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Total gonadotropin and LH excretion following clomiphene treatment was studied by means of 84 assays in a group of 11 subjects presenting changes in the menstrual cycle and 97 assays in a group of 5 subjects with the Stein Leventhal syndrome. All the patients had anovulatory cycles during the control period, and ovulation was ascertained after their treatment. Both the control period and the period immediately following the beginning of treatment were divided into 4 fractions of 8 days each, and from the assays of each of these, the average total gonadotropin and LH excretion was evaluated and the standard deviation calculated. The results showed that clomiphene treatment induces a modification of the excretion pattern of LH in both groups of patients, while it is not very effective on total gonadotropin output. Nevertheless a wider range of excretion values of total gonadotropins was found in Stein Leventhal cases, after administration of the drug. As far as LH is concerned, while a marked increase was observed in cases of altered cycles the excretion pattern of this hormone became more regular, rather rising in the Stein Leventhal group. Clomiphene is probably able to stimulate FSH liberation, inducing rhythmic alternation between these 2 hormones.
