N2  - Hypophysectomy by implantation of yttrium 90 was carried out in 242 women with metastatic cancer of the breast. Three unusual prognostic factors were deduced in the successful cases: (a) A very large percentage was in blood group B or O. (b) A large number of patients excreted a small amount of urinary estrogen. (c) A number gave a low figure for fixation of iodine 131 in the thyroid.
