T1  - The use of estrogens in the pre- And post-menopause
T3  - Empleo dk estrogenos en la pre y fostmenopausia
A1  - Alvarez Bravo A.
A1  - Botella Llusia J.
A1  - Defares J.G.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Eistrogen therapy is justified in various circumstances: the present day elderly woman leads a sexual life; estrogens are used to prevent mucosal atrophy, topical estrogens in minute doses preserve tissues in a good state, thus helping to correct prolapse, urethritis etc. Hypoestronism is not an invariable accompaniment of the climacteric, however, since the mesenchymal structures of the ovary retain their function, and the adrenal acts as an estrogenopoietic organ. Estrogenopoietic organ. Estrogen therapy therefore needs to be given with discrimination. Premenopausal ovarian hypofunction or dysfunction is an indication for the use of anovulatory agents, combined if there is a tendency to menorrhagia or sequentially if there is oligo- or hypomenorrhea; also when there are signs of estrogenic insufficiency such as vasomotor disturbances, insomnia etc. There is no likelihood of this treatment producing endometrial hyperplasia, nor is there evidence that estrogen administration is carcinogenic. Liminal doses only are recommended, i.e. doses that just suffice to abolish the disturbance, with interruptions for, say, 7 days of each month. Estrogens judiciously administered increase mental wellbeing in the menopause by combating depression, enhancing the libido, and abolishing palpitations, insomnia etc. Estrogens are also useful as prophylactics against coronaropathy and arteriosclerosis. (Senor - Barcelona).
