N2  - The purpose of this study was to determine the functional activity of the stimulated tissues and the number of mitoses. The case described is that of a woman (40 yr) who was subjected to ovariectomy for polycystic ovaries (with inflammation). After operation she '.vas treated for 8 days with a daily injection of estradiol 3 mg., progesterone 20 mg. and testosterone 20 mg. Histologie examination of the uterine mucosa after curettage revealed a hyperplastic endometrium and an intensive reddish orange fluorescence of the cytoplasm of the glandular is concluded that the combination of the represser together with the estrogens had led to an inhibition of the repressive phenomena with an enhanced protein synthesis, and to secondary proliferation of the uterine tissue.
