T1  - Importance of morbid anatomical examination of the ovaries in the stein leventhal syndrome
T3  - IMPORTANCE de L-EXAMEN ANATOMO PATHOLOGIQUE des OVAIRES dans le SYNDROME de STEIN LEVENTHAL
A1  - Gerber E.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - On the basis of a critical review of the published findings and 15 cases which bring together all the clinical, biological and histological criteria considered as classical features of the syndrome, it is concluded that: The Stein Leventhal syndrome must be likened to a triptych composed of 3 clinical, biological and histological pictures, forming an indissoluble whole. In the current knowledge, examination of only one of its wings robs the entity of all its personality and brings it into the general category of ovarian dystrophies and ovarian or even extragonadal virilism. Histological examination of the ovaries in the Stein Leventhal syndrome is of prime diagnostic importance. The clinician who wants a precise answer from the pathologist must remember that he must submit to the latter, in addition to full clinical and biological information, wide fragments of bilateral wedge resection in preference to cortical biopsies. And if he takes cortical biopsies even so. he will still have to take his sample as widely as possible from a zone analytically helpful to the histologist.
