N2  - It was possible to show the ovarian origin of 17 ketosteroid urinary hyperexcretion in 6 of 15 women affected by hyperandrogenism. Dynamic scanning by the double gonadal adrenocortical suppression test with meprednisone + ethinylestradiol was employed. The results obtained show the usefulness of the test for the identification of hyperandrogenism of ovarian origin. It is emphasized that the trial should be used in the therapeutic field, because of normalization of 17 ketosteroids urinary excretion obtained after treatment of meprednisone + ethinylestradiol drugs.
