T1  - Treatment of anovulation with clomifene
T3  - LE TRAITEMENT de L1ANOVL1LATION PAR le CLOMIFENE
A1  - Bayot D.
A1  - Vokaer R.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The results of this trial confirm the reports by other authors: among 20 cases of anovulation without any other cause of sterility, there were 12 which developed the clinical signs of ovulation and in 9 of these cases, a pregnancy followed. No new data in regard to the mechanism of action of Clomiphene could be deduced from these observations. However, the fact that no result was obtained in the 3 cases of ovarian insufficiency confirms that treatment with this drug can only be successful in patients with functional ovaries. The success or failure of previous courses of treatment with gonadotropins or bis (acetoxyphenyl) cyclohexylidene methane (F 6066) appeared to have no influence on the changes of success of the treatment with Clomiphene. The drug is very easy to handle; it can be given orally and its undesirable side effects are few compared with the dose of the gonadotropins, so that on numerous indications it is to be preferred. On the other hand, it appears that the gonadotropins may be effective in some cases in which Clomiphene is not. This aspect determines the respective places of these different forms of treatment in our therapeutical arsenal.
