A1  - Talas M.
A1  - Stehlikova J.
A1  - Jezdinsky J.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Using the method of Simkin and Goodart comparison was made of the crop weight response. following local application of extracts of prolactin from the blood of 10 patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome, in 10 women in the secretory phase of the menstrual cycle and in 10 women with galactorrhoea. The crop weight response following application of the extracts from the blood of women with Stein-Leventhal syndrome was found significantly higher than that caused by extracts from blood from women in the second half of the menstrual cycle and significantly lower than the crop weight increase following application of extracts from the blood of women with galactorrhoea. Additionally a comparison was made between histological changes encountered following the application of standard Luteotropin and those following the application of blood extracts. In the present study a possible contribution of inflammatory changes to crop weight response following the application of blood extracts is discussed.
