N2  - In studying the etiological role of ovarian defects in female sterility and therefore in sterile marriages, a review has been carried out of 719 patients who sought advice because of sterility. Of these, 87 showed changes which made it possible to include them in the group of sterility from ovarian causes. The criteria are presented which enabled this diagnosis to be reached. A review is made of treatment of the ovarian factor by means of MRL-41 or clomiphene, and the regime of therapy which was employed and the results obtained are presented.
