Y1  - 1968//
N2  - In a comparative cytological study of menstruating girls, conducted simultaneously in the Netherlands and in South Africa, it was found that among Dutch girls of 15 yr old (n = 22) there was a higher percentage (50% of ovulatory menstrual cycles than among a group of Bantu girls (n=17) of the same age group (17.60X). This may indicate that the event of first ovulation (ovularche) as well as the menarche occurs earlier in Europeans than in Bantus. Cytological studies of 15 complete menstrual cycles have been made in conjunction with pregnandiol determinations in 6 girls aged 13 to 17. Besides characteristic ovulatory and anovulatory curves there exists a socalled second half plateau curve. This type of curve is probably a reflection of cyclical changes in the ovaries with the growth of hormonally active follicles but without ovulation.
