N2  - On the basis of 43 cases studied endocrino-logically and operated on, the authors conclude that the most characteristic changes in this disorder are functional bleeding of any type, infertility (primary or secondary), bilateral enlargement of the ovaries, and prolonged absence of ovulation. Hirsutism can be evaluated only as a secondary atypical sign. The disorder first appears in about 50% of the cases during the menopause, whereas in another large group of cases it develops some years after the normal sexual period.
