N2  - Changes in blood-coagulation and fibrinolysis have been studied in 15 patients (10 on continuous treatment with 1 lynoestrenol + mestranol tablet daily, 5 on cyclic treatment: 1 tablet of the same estroprogestational association - 1 tablet from the 5th to 24th day from the start of the last period, for 5 mth). Periodic controls were performed during the whole treatment period. The thrombo-elastographic parameters have revealed a statistically significant (Fisher's F) increase in coagulability, especially in patients on continuous therapy, together with a fall in the recalcification-time and fibrinolytic activity. Nevertheless, on the results obtained, the authors cannot establish an increased tendency to thromboembolic complications. In fact, the relationship between hypercoagulability and thromboembolic syndromes is still an open question.
