N2  - Exclusive treatment with Ro-4-8347 stopped uterine bleeding within 6 days in 40 out of 43 cases with dysfunctional uterine bleeding. A normal withdrawal bleeding is observed 11-15 days after the onset of treatment. This therapy is well tolerated and there are no undue side effects. Colpocytologic examinations show that Ro-4-8347 has an indirect estrogenic effect which probably enhances endometrial regeneration with concomitant secretory changes in the endometrium. The important advantage of treatment with Ro-4-8347 compared to combined eetrogen-norsteroid therapy is that it is well tolerated and initiates ovulation which in turn corrects the anovulation which causes the bleeding.
