N2  - The myometrial activity has been studied during cyclic and continuous treatment with contraceptive pills (norethisterone and ethinyl estradiol, Anovlar). On cyclic treatment the contractility pattern changes in the same way but more rapidly than in ovulatory cycles. On continuous treatment accentuation of the 'prelabor-like' pattern is observed. Cessation of treatment is followed by 'laborlike' activity. The relation between the two hormonal substances and the different activity patterns are discussed.
