T1  - To the diagnosis of Stein-Leventhal syndrome. II. The biochemical part
T3  - K diagnoze Steinova-Leventhalova syndromu. II. Cast biochemicka
A1  - Matys Z.
A1  - Gregorova I.
A1  - Vrbova H.
A1  - Reisenauer R.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - No statistically significant difference in the elimination of 17-hydroxy-ketosteroids in basal conditions (8.5 +/- 3.9 mg/24 hr) or after the administration of ACTH (25.7 +/- 10.6 mg/24 hr) was found in 25 patients with the diagnosis of Stein-Leventhal syndrome confirmed radiographically or by operation supplemented by histology, in comparison with the group of 20 healthy women (7.4 +/- 2.6 mg/24 hr after ACTH: 24.9 +/- 7.3 mg/24 hr). The elimination of 17-KS both in basal conditions (16.7 +/- 6.0 mg/24 hr) and after ACTH (24.1 +/- 8.9 mg/24 hr) proved to be significantly higher in the patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome than in the control group (9.8 +/- 3.8 mg/24 hr; after ACTH 19.4 +/- 6.1 mg/24 hr). Graphic representation and statistical evaluation of different fractions of 17-KS for 42 patients suffering from Stein-Leventhal syndrome were presented. The absolute values of elimination of most fractions of 17-KS in the patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome proved to be significantly higher than in the control group. The index calculated from the relation of the total sum of 11-hydroxy and 11-keto-17-KS and dihydroepiandrosterone to the sum of androsterone and etiocholantrene lower than 0.5 was found only in patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome based on the blockade of androgens aromatization, where the elimination of dehydroepiandrosterone was proved to be lower than 1.50 mg/24 hr. The suprarenal virilization syndromes and cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome with blockage of steroid 3 ol-dehydrogenase proved to have an index above 0.5. The elimination of pregnandiol in five patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome proved to be significantly higher (1.59 +/- 0.46 mg/24 hr) than in the ten control persons (1.04 +/- 0.28 mg/24 hr). Eighty per cent of the patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome proved not to eliminate pregnandiol in the period related to one menstrual cycle. Dexamethasone administration proved to suppress significantly the elimination of 17-KS in patients with congenital hyperplasia of the suprarenals and with adrenogenital syndrome combined with Stein-Leventhal syndrome. The findings indicate that in most patients suffering from Stein-Leventhal syndrome no disorder of the pituitary - suprarenal relations develops. The higher elimination of 17-KS indicates a higher production of androgens. The relation of the different fractions of 17-KS eliminated in Stein-Leventhal syndrome appears to be of importance more than their individual values. The complete inhibition of pregnandiol elimination indicates anovulatory cycle in most of the patients. The results of a suppression by dexamethasone may differentiate between the Stein-Leventhal syndrome and the suprarenal virilization syndromes.
