N2  - Daily immunoassay of luteinizing hormone excretion was performed in the menstrual cycle with anovulation and during treatment with clomiphene. Clomiphene probably has a primary action at the hypothalamus on the FSH-estrogen inter-relationship. The release of LH is secondary to the primary action of the drug. The peak of LH excretion was observed only after Clomiphene treatment had been terminated and occurred 0-3 days prior to ovulation and basal temperature shift.
