N2  - The volume of the ovaries was estimated in 112 patients with hirsutism by means of gas pelvigraphy. Common hirsutism is essentially the combination of hirsutism and menstrual disturbances. No correlation was found between ovarian size and the degree of menstrual disturbance. It is felt that the concept of the large ovary in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome should be revised. The features of importance are macroscopical aspects euch as the thickness of the tunica albuginea in association with certain microscopical details characterizing the ovary in this condition.
