T1  - Hysterosalpingography induced pregnancies
T3  - Sulle gravidanze da isterosalpingografia
A1  - Cagnazzo G.
A1  - Storace A.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - In view of the therapeutic value of hysterosalpingography in some cases of sterility, the authors have investigated 275 sterile women who had undergone this examination. In 10.54% of cases the women, who had not in the meantime been treated for sterility in any way, became pregnant within 3 mth after the examination. In 17 cases, the cycles had been shown (by endometrial biopsy and pregnanediol urinary excretion) to be ovulatory, which makes the authors think that in this group the therapeutic effect of the hysterosalpingography may be due to the mechanical action of the introduction of the contrast medium under pressure on tubal patency, probably associated with the antiphlogistic action of its iodine component. In the remaining 12 patients, who were shown to have anovulatory cycles, it must be supposed that hysterosalpingography, by promoting the utero prehypophyseal reflex, produced a reflex ovulation and therefore a recovery of the diencephalo prehypophyseal ovarian correlations, thus reestablishing normal ovulation, soon followed by pregnancy.
