N2  - The authors report on a series of cases of Stein Leventhal syndrome submitted to wedge resection of the ovary. The urinary excretion of testosterone and epitestosterone was repeatedly estimated both before and after the operation. On this basis and on the urinary levels of estrogens, pregnanediol and 17 ketosteroids, the authors estimated the ovarian function in each case. The patients clinical pictures were very similar but they varied widely in their urinary steroid levels, a finding that was difficult to interpret.
