N2  - In addition to the symptomatic and approximate etiological classifications, pathogenetic classification is suggested of hypothalamohypophyseal disorders of the menstrual cycle based on the present conception about the hypothalamic regulation of the gonadotropic function of the adenohypophysis. Besides the scheme suggested, there are the syndrome of polycystic ovaries, isolated disturbances of the adenohypophysis (adenoma and ischemic postpartum necrosis) and psychosomatic (corticovisceral) disorders. The clinical pathogenetic classification is a necessary condition for rational treatment of hypothalamohypophyseal disorders which are the cause of menstrual disturbances in 2/3 to 3/4 of the cases.
