T1  - Dietetic treatment of menstrual changes in obese women
T3  - Terapia dietetica delle alterazioni mestruali nella donna obesa
A1  - Debiasi E.
A1  - Cagnazzo G.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Forty two women of reproductive age suffering from simple obesity, in whom investigations hud excluded a primary endocrinopathy as the cause of their metabolic abnormality, were subjected to a dietetic slimming treatment. The menstrual disorders (hypomenorrhea, oligomenorrhea and amenorrhea), which had been constantly present from an early stage in these patients, responded favorably to a reduction in weight, not only with normalization of the rhythm and other characteristics of the menstrual flow, but also with a return of normal ovulatory cycles, controlled by endometrial biopsy and hormone tests. Six patients with anovulatory sterility who wanted a baby became pregnant and gave birth at term. On the results of the semeiological exploration of these cases, certain hypotheses are advanced to explain the mechanism of action of simple obesity in causing early abnormalities in the genital functions.
