N2  - The authors have found alterations in estrogen excretion during treatment with this compound. Estriol excretion was practically unchanged. The estrone output was clearly increased and the estradiol excretion diminished. The drug may hinder the metabolism of estrone into estriol, which would have endocrine consequences. The compound's metabolites interfere with the traditional methods of assaying estrogens, color reactions and fluorometric determinations are affected. A thin layer chromatographic technique is described which makes it possible to separate estrogens from these metabolites.
