N2  - The morphologic findings in the ovaries of 22 patients with mild adrenal hyperplasia are presented. A decrease of the primordial follicles and an increase in follicular cysts were encountered as well as a variable degree of thickness of the tunica albuginea, stromal and thecal hyperplasia and luteinization. These histologic features are comparable with those found in a Stein Leventhal ovary. An abnormal release of gonadotrophin is considered as the most likely causative factor.
