T1  - Considerations on birth control from the point of view of the christian doctor
T3  - Consideraciones sobre el control de la natalidad desde el punto de vista del medico cristiano
A1  - Liria R.H.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Blind and, as it were, instinctive reproduction as a consequence of coitus is by no means acceptable. Procreation should be planned with human and Christian responsibility. The choice of the number of children in a family depends on the responsibility of the parents. The method of periodic or selective abstinence based on the procedure of Knaus and Ogino, combined with adherence to the results of basal body temperature measurements and carried out correctly, offers adequate safety in spacing the pregnancies in the setting of normal married life. The physician may give the couple this information and its technical aspects in order to facilitate its flawless realization. This is the task of the doctor and not of the priest. To give instructions, however, does not mean to make propaganda since this practice is permissible only in the presence of genuine and serious motives. The anovulatory drugs provide a high degree of safe contraception; their use by the physician is allowed as a therapeutic method for gynecologic: affections but not for contraceptive purposes, even when more or less momentous health problems are involved. In this sense the traditional doctrine of the Church remains valid.
