T1  - Stein Leventhal syndrome. A report of seventeen cases
A1  - Sherman G.H.
A1  - Clark J.F.J.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Sixteen cases of Stein Leventhal syndrome were treated by bilateral ovarian wedge resection and one by total abdominal hysterectomy and bilateral salpingo oophorectomy. All 16 treated by wedge resection reverted to normal menstruation and 10 showed definite evidence of ovulation. Three patients delivered normal infants, while a fourth has had 2 abortions; 3 others are pregnant. Ovarian physiology in the Stein Leventhal syndrome as well as different types of hormonal therapy were briefly discussed.
