T1  - Ovulation-inducing drugs
T3  - Les agents inducteurs de lovulation
A1  - Cession G.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The treatment is discussed of ovarian hypofunction (anovulation) with gonadotrophic substances of different origin: Human (HPG) and animal (APG) hypophyses, pregnant mare serum (PMS), urine of pregnant women (HCG), of castrated and postmenopausal women (HMG). The presence of ovarian tissue capable of responding to hormonal stimulation is a prerequisite for therapeutic success. The treatment schedules of Staemler, Diczfalusy and Gemzell are listed. Dosage should be individualized on the basis of clinical and biologic studies (vaginal smears, cervical mucus, diminution of estrogenic substances and pregnanediol). Furthermore, synthetic substances with a gonadotrophic action are mentioned (F6066 and clomiphene citrate or MRL 41). Clomiphene in particular has proved efficient. Its action takes place either by way of the hypothalamic pituitary system or via steroidogenesis in the ovary. Complications and side effects of these forms of treatment are pointed out.
