N2  - The present situation of the treatment of female sterility with human gonadotrophins HMG HCG is reported. The indications and the different therapeutic schemes proposed are described in detail. Strict control is required of the ovarian response during treatment to avoid possible complications. Case histories are presented of 3 patients treated for hypothalamic hypophyseal anovulation as the sole cause of their sterility. In the 8 cycles performed, 4 ovulations were obtained and 1 patient became pregnant. No complications were observed.
