T1  - Further clinical experience with clomiphene citrate
A1  - Macgregor A.H.
A1  - Johnson J.E.
A1  - Bunde C.A.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Data on 6,714 patients treated with clomiphene citrate has been assembled. There were 2,196 pregnancies comprising 1,744 delivered and 452 whose reports are not available. There were 407 who fell in the category of abortion, hydatidiform mole, premature stillbirth and ectopic pregnancy. There were 1,201 single live births with 1,179 survivals. Multiple pregnancy was increased 10 fold. The overall ovulatory response was consistent at about 70%. The clinical conditions responding best to clomiphene were polycystic ovary, postcontraceptive amenorrhea, and oligomenorrhea (menses 2 to 6 mth). Poor response was noted in cases of demonstrable pituitary or ovarian failure as shown by low FSH or low estrogen production. Best treatment schedule was 50 mg daily on days 5 to 9. The side effects were moderate ovarian enlargement 13%, vasomotor hot flushes 10.8%, pelvic discomfort 7.4%, nausea and vomiting 2.1%, breast discomfort 2.1% and poorly defined symptoms in a very small group. In the great majority no side effects were recorded.
