T1  - Use of clomiphene citrate in treatment of wedge resection failures and as a preoperative test for wedge resection success
A1  - Wider J.A.
A1  - Neuwirth R.S.
A1  - Vande Wiele R.L.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Twenty referred cases of failed wedge resection were treated with clomiphene citrate. Fourteen patients ovulated and 8 became pregnant during clomiphene treatment or during the first posttreatment cycle. Twenty-four patients were treated with clomiphene citrate prior to wedge resection. Eighteen patients demonstrated a positive response and had a successful reaction. Four patients became pregnant. The response to clomiphene is compared to other criteria for operability in these patients. Sixty-eight per cent of women who failed to respond to wedge resection ovulated after clomiphene therapy and half of these became pregnant. The high percentage of success suggests that a trial of clomiphene is worthwhile as a first step in the patient who has failed to respond to wedge resection.
