T1  - A case of Chiari-Frommel syndrome associated with polycystic ovaries
A1  - Zarate A.
A1  - Villalobos M.
A1  - Valenzuela S.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Most investigators define the Chiari Frommel syndrome as persistent postpartum lactation associated with amenorrhea. Although there are several reports concerning the clinical and laboratory findings in the Chiari Frommel syndrome, there are only a few papers dealing with the histologie appearance of the ovaries. In certain patients with galactorrhea amenorrhea the ovaries are very similar to those found in patients with the constant estrus syndrome or patients responding to wedge resection; however, there are 2 distinguishing features: the onset of anovulatton in the galactorrhea amenorrhea group usually does not date back to puberty or shortly thereafter but is sudden in later life; also these patients do not respond to wedge resection. The purpose of this paper is to present a case of Chiari Frommel syndrome associated with polycystic ovaries resembling those reported in the Stein Leventhal syndrome.
