N2  - In a group of 20 women with symptoms of androgenism and with anovulatory cycles sequential therapy with Mestranol and Lyndiol 2.5 was applied during 4 cycles. A decrease of urinary androgen excretion was observed, together with a regression of seborrhea, hirsutism and acne. The menstrual cycle became more regular. Vaginal smears demonstrated the estrogenic and progesterone effect parallelly to the administered therapy. The basal body temperature diagrams demonstrated the thermic effect after the administration of gestagen. The sequential therapy may be regarded as an efficient mode of achieving 'ovariectomy'.
