T1  - The surgical provocation of rapture of the follicle. The clinical aspects of the polycystic ovary syndrome
T3  - Die chirurgische provokation des follikelsprunges. Ein klinischer beitrag zum polyzystischen ovar-syndrom
A1  - Dapunt O.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The polycystic ovary syndrome is an etiologically unexplained failure of endocrine regulation (brain stem-hypophysis-ovary-adrenal cortex) that is more often acquired than congenital in nature. A clinical entity such as that put forward by Stein and Leventhal (bilateral polycystic ovaries, amenorrhea, hirsutism and adiposity) is dubious because of the inconstancy of the symptoms. The polycystic change is the only obligatous symptom, while primary or secondary anovulation in association with it is the most important proviso for the diagnosis. In view of the uncharacteristic findings of hormone excretion (17-ketosteroids being slightly raised in only 23% of the cases) pre- and postoperative ACTH stimulation is considered to be of greater differential diagnostic value than increase of the andrenal androgens and the recognition of mixed ovarian and adrenal forms. This report covers 7 cases that were confirmed by biopsy, which over a period of 20 mth came to the Hormone Consultation Clinic of the University Gynecological Clinic in Innsbruck (4.6% of all women patients registered as being sterile). Out of 6 married women who expressed the wish to have a child, 5 became pregnant after bilateral wedge resection of the ovaries; one of the women became pregnant twice. The exception to the achievement of pregnancy was a patient with an ovarian-adrenal mixed form. In the 7th and unmarried patient prolonged biphasic cycle with late ovulation followed on the primary amenorrhea after the operation. Three of the 6 pregnancies were complicated by bleedings in the first three months. Hormonal protection of the pregnancy seems to be necessary because of the enhanced tendency to abortion. An attempt at conservative therapy should be made before having recourse to wedge resection in order to try out the efficacy of the hormonal therapy at present available (gonadotropin, clomiphene, dexamethasone, gestagen) and also in order to determine the indications for operation.
