T1  - Correction of ovulatory disorders induced by clomiphene
T3  - Correcao de disturbios ovulatorios induzida pelo clomifene
A1  - Amaral Ferreira C.
A1  - Zalmon I.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The authors analyze the effects of clomiphene citrate and similar drugs, drawing attention to the antagonistic effects of clomiphene in women: induction of ovulation and facilitation of the gestation period. The final results of its action is the liberation of hypophyseal gonadotrophins, though it sometimes acts directly on the ovaries and other organs of conception. The drug induces ovulation, and in men it improves spermatogenesis, with the advantage of not affecting liver and renal functions. The authors have studied 11 cases, of which 8 started ovulation and 2 became pregnant (25%). Later they analyze 36 more cases, separated in 2 groups: I - Anovulation; II - Luteinic insufficiency, with the administration of 50 mg daily from the 5th to the 9th day of the cycle. Of 22 patients, 15 ovulated and 7 became pregnant with uneventful pregnancies and they conclude with the total of 9 positive pregnancies, showing the success of the method.
