N2  - Twenty-four women with oligomenorrhea failed to respond to estrogens given intramuscularly and by vein. In 13 of 66 cases of monophasic cycle, ovulation was obtained 18 times, with 1 pregnancy. Of the 13 women, 10 had been under observation 3-8 mth before treatment. In 52 patients observed for 12 mth and more, no cases responded with ovulation. No difference in the success rate was demonstrable between those given intravenous and those given intramuscular intermittent high-dose treatment.
