N2  - An electroencephalographic, biological and clinical investigation was carried out in 23 patients with Stein Leventhal syndrome or ovarian dystrophy. In 52% of these cases pathologic cerebral bioelectric potentials were recorded. A comparison of the biological and clinical data with the electroencephalographic tracings seems to rule out a constant relationship between the type and extension of the dystrophy and the electroencephalographic record. Based upon these findings, it is concluded that the alterations of the cerebral bioelectric potential might be caused by a idiopathic condition of the encephalic structures of these patients, probably due to and increased by an endocrine derangement.
