T1  - Treatment of acute intermittent porphyria with anovulatory drugs. Studies on delta aminolevulinic acid, porphobilinogen and total excreted porphyrin
T3  - Zur frage der behandlung der akuten intermittierenden porphyrie mit ovulationshemmern (untersuchungen von delta aminolavulinsaure, porphobilinogen und der gesamtporphyrinausscheidung)
A1  - Hocevar V.
A1  - Rausch Struomann J.G.
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The treatment of acute intermittent porphyria (AIP) with oral contraceptive drugs is discussed and partly rejected, because these drugs by themselves may cause attacks. Four patients with AIP and 1 control were treated with a combination of gestagens and estrogens for 3 mth up to 2 yr. During this time, delta aminolevulinic acid, porphobilinogen and total porphyrins were determined frequently. During the treatment, no attack was observed. The control had slightly elevated porphyrins, also the patients with AIP at intervals. During attacks, however, values 20 to 30 times higher were observed. The amount of hormones given and of those produced by the organism are thought to be responsible for the attacks; treatment with oral contraceptive drugs is proposed.
