N2  - Chromosome analysis has been carried out on the lymphocytes of 41 patients suffering from the Stein Leventhal syndrome and on 21 normal pregnant controls. The cells of all but 1 patient in the experimental group and of all controls exhibited normal karyotypes. The patient with the abnormal karyotype demonstrated an apparent abnormality in a G group chromosome in 2ffi of her cells. She represented one of the more clinically severe examples of the syndrome and responded in no way to any therapy attempted. The possible significance of this finding is discussed.
