T1  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome. Research on its definition
T3  - Le syndrome de Stein-Leventhal; a la recherche de sa definition
A1  - Barnard I.
A1  - Audit J.F.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - In the light of an extensive bibliography, the authors have been impressed by the clinical, histopathologic, biochemical, genetic and therapeutic divergencies that lead them to conclude that the Stein-Leventhal syndrome is as yet in search of definition and that its autonomy is more than questionable. They ask if it would not be better to juxtapose this syndrome to sclerocystic ovaritis and to unite both under a common term: ovarian polycystia. Summarizing then the ideas brought by Stein in answer to the excesses that have been bound up with his syndrome, they conclude: if the syndrome exists, a definition has to be given that may be accepted unanimously; if it is only representative of a symptomatology as questionable as inconstant, their individuality has to be left to these signs, while their association brings confusion and not light.
