T1  - Twinning in relation to the marital status of the mother
A1  - Erikeeon A.W.
A1  - Fellman J.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Official statistics and church records (parish registers) from different periods relating to Scandinavian populations reveal a significantly higher twinning rate in illegitimate maternities than in legitimate ones, especially among mothers aged 2539 yr. The possibility is discussed that mothers with illegitimate maternities comprise an elite from the standpoint of fertility and reproduction, and that they may become pregnant more easily owing to an increased tendency to polyovulation and a low frequency of anovulatory cycles, including the possibility of super-fecundation and superfetation. Furthermore, it is suggested that they may have better physical qualifications, on the average, for completing a multiple pregnancy. The hypothesis of a higher ovulation rate among unmarried mothers is supported by the fact that the difference in twinning rate between married and unmarried mothers seems to involve only dizygotic twin maternities. The risk of immunization against the father ought to be less among unmarried mothers than among married ones. This might also be a contributory cause of their higher dizygotic twinning rate. (10, 1, 7, 21).
