N2  - The authors report their observations on a new series of 20 sterile women treated successively by H. M. G. -H. C. G. Eleven pregnancies occurred in the course of 27 cycles of treatment. Two of them gave birth to twins. The frequency of latent or definite hyperstimulation found by all the authors who have used these gonadotropins indicates that the greatest caution must be exercised, thus the administration should be adapted according to ovarian and cervical responses to the drug. The complete H. M. G. -H. C. G. treatment was administered to 8 patients suffering from amenorrhea in order to test the gonadal response. A new stimulation test using H. M. G. alone is proposed and discussed.
