A1  - Ferriman D.
A1  - Purdie A.W.
A1  - Corns M.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The ovulatory response to clomifene is significantly better in patients with menstrual cycles of less than 6 mth duration compared with those whose cycles exceed this figure, and in patients with polycystic ovaries compared with those whose ovaries are of normal size. It is better in patients with basal estrogen excretions exceeding 21 mug/ 24 hr than in those whose excretion levels fall below this figure (obtained by a method having a nonspecific background fluorescence of 10 mug/24 hr), though the difference does not quite reach formal significance. Patients with normal-sized ovaries conceive more readily than those with polycystic ovaries. The difference does not quite reach formal significance.
