T1  - Clomiphene citrate for improvement of ovarian function
A1  - Jones G.S.
A1  - De Moraes-Ruehsen M.D.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - This study concerns the influence of clomifene on the ovarian function. This drug was used in a group of patients with various forms of ovarian dysfunction: 6 so-called 'normal infertile females', 9 women with luteal phase defects, 56 with oligomenorrhea and anovulation, 4 with lactation amenorrhea, 10 with primary amenorrhea, and 7 with 'unresponsive ovaries'. Ovarian function was estimated by basal body temperature, endometrial biopsy, and urinary excretion of estrogens and pregnanediol. Pregnancies were followed with primary pregnanediol and serum HCG titers. Previously normal ovarian function became abnormal after 450 mg of clomifene citrate. Anovulation not associated with severe pituitary insufficiency was corrected in all patient, by 250-500 mg of clomifene citrate, and smaller dosages seemed more effective than larger. Luteal phase defects following induced ovulation were significantly higher than in a series of patients with spontaneous ovulatory function.
