A1  - Zelenetskaya V.S.
A1  - Bronshtein M.E.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - An attempt was made to compare the results obtained by studying steroid excretion with peculiarities of ovarian structure in cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome. An initial level of 17-oxycorticosteroids, 17-ketosteroids (total and fractions), estrogens and the nature of the changes in these indices caused by ovarian stimulation by gonadotrophin without depressing the adrenal cortex and after such depression with dexamethasone, were used as indices. In order to compare certain ovarian anomalies observed in Stein-Leventhal syndrome with the biological data, the authors chose an internal theca structure of cystic follicles. Three groups of patients could be distinguished in this way. A discussion is given as to the possible nature of the disturbances specific in each group.
