T3  - Utilisation des gonadotrophines humaines pour le traitement de la sterilite anovulatoire et le diagnostic etiologique de certaines amenorrhees. A propos de vingt-huit nouveaux cas
A1  - Salomon-Bernard Y.
A1  - Millet D.
A1  - Netter A.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A report is presented of a new series of 20 sterile women who were treated with HMG-HCG, with good results. In the course of 27 cycles of treatment, 11 pregnancies occurred, of which 2 were twin pregnancies. The high incidence of latent or frank hyperstimulation observed by all authors who use these gonadotropins render it necessary to be as cautious as possible, with gradual, empirical adjustment of the dosage in each individual case. The complete treatment was administered to 8 women with amenorrhea in order to test the gonadal response. A new stimulation test, for which only HMG is used, is proposed and discussed.
