T1  - The distribution of lipolytic enzymes in the ovaries in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome
A1  - Bronshtein M.E.
A1  - Leites F.L.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The activity and distribution of lipolytic enzymes (aliesterase, lipase and lipoprotein lipase) were studied histochemically in the ovaries in Stein-Leventhal syndrome (10 observations) and under normal conditions (2 observations). As revealed, in Stein-Leventhal syndrome the lipolytic enzyme activity was associated with the following structures: internal theca of follicular cysts, persisting theca of fibrous atresic follicles, paralutein cells, as well as foci of the comatosis which not infrequently occur in this material. There was noted a reverse relationship between the lipid content and the activity of lipolytic enzymes in the corresponding cells. It is supposed that lipolytic enzymes played a certain role at the early stage of hormone formation, splitting lipids, gaining access to the blood, and thus participating in the formation of 'raw material' for steroid hormone synthesis.
