T1  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome
T3  - Le syndrome de Stein-Leventhal
A1  - Benaim Pinto V.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Those who study sterile women exhibiting amenorrhea and hirsutism note that few subjects exhibit a number of the clinical, biochemical. histopathologic and therapeutic criteria that theoretically are characteristic of this syndrome. The author makes a severe critical study of such criteria that, as a rule, are not sufficiently motivated, a fact that explains the elasticity of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. It is in the same sense that he makes a review of the various exploratory investigations and especially of the laboratory, chemical, biologic and anatomic tests that are here related with full details. The pathogenesis may be summarized as a congenital enzymatic disorder located in the ovaries and consisting in a partial or may be total blockade of estrogen biosynthesis. This ovarian dyssteroidogenesis constitutes a pathogenic mechanism very similar to the one met in congenital adrenal hyperplasia. For treatment, taking into account the transitory action of the newly advanced therapies, the author gives preference to wedge resection of both ovaries, the results of which were as excellent in a number of patients.
