N2  - In-vitro studies in 3 cases of polycystic ovaries are presented. Although 1 of these patients was not a typical case of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, the results obtained from the incubations were similar. They strongly differ from the results of biosynthesis in normal ovaries, mainly in the corpora lutea. The following substrates were used: progesterone-4-C<ovid:sup>14</ovid:sup>, androstenedione-4-C<ovid:sup>14</ovid:sup>, testosterone-4-C<ovid:sup>14</ovid:sup>. The method used is that previously described (Forleo and Collins, 1964; Forleo et al., 1967) and the conditions of incubation were maintained strictly constant in order to have comparable results. The strong production of androstenedione and the lack of aromatization are discussed. The work is part of a systematic study of in-vitro steroid biosynthesis in the human ovary.
