T1  - Technique for estimation of the rate of testosterone production
T3  - Mesure du taux de production de la testosterone. Etudes physio-pathologiques
A1  - Lanthier A.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A new technique to measure the blood production rate of testosterone is described. This technique measures the testosterone secreted plus the testosterone originating from the peripheral metabolism of other secreted steroid precursor of testosterone. In 2 normal men. the testosterone production rates found were resp. 4.5 and 4.6 mg/ day. In 2 subjects without testes, low values of 1 mg/day were noted, while in a 3rd subject a value of 2.9 mg/day was observed, probably due to residual circulating testosterone from the last injection of depot testosterone. In a patient with 1 cryptorchid testis recently surgically descended into the scrotum and in another patient with atrophic testes due to longterm estrogen administration, it was shown that the testes of both subject could respond to gonadotropin stimulation. In 4 cases of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, elevated values for testosterone production were noted; suppression with dexamethasone could not delineate the ovarian or adrenocortical contribution.
