T1  - The action of clomiphene on hormonal secretions. The endometrial response
A1  - Ancla M.
A1  - De Brux J.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The authors have studied, by light and electron microscope, the endometria of 2 groups of clomifene-treated patients. Examination of the 4 patients in the 1st group, of whom 3 presented with mucosal atrophy and anovulatory amenorrhea, confirmed the experience that this treatment favors the normal, biphasic development of the endometrium. Its optimum effect, however, can be judged only if one takes into account a latent period necessary for the mobilization and realization of the various metabolic reactions thus provoked. The 2nd group, which was composed of 8 patients with subnormal but not absent function, showed: a delay in the appearance of the luteal phase possibly due to a lateness in ovulation caused by the initially antiestrogenic action of the clomifene; a decrease in the endometrial storage of glycogen which seems related to a frequent hormone imbalance and hyperestrogenism observed after this treatment.
