N2  - Study of a group of 12 women with perfectly normal cycles showed that oral cytology is entirely unsuited to replace vaginal cytology for the study of alterations of the cycle. It was only in a small proportion of the cases that the 2 extreme phases of the cycle (and only these 2) could be demonstrated: the desquamation or menstrual phase and the cornification or ovulatory phase. It seems clear that factors of a non-hormonal nature play a part in the determination of the cytological picture of the oral mucosa.
