T3  - Pathogenie des ovaires polykystiques. Comparaison avec les activites endocriniennes des testicules
A1  - Jayle M.-F.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The author makes a good case for his thesis that the androgenizing aspects of Stein-Leventhal syndrome result from disordered adrenal steroid metabolism. Dexamethasone, in a dose of 3 mg. daily, suppresses pituitary and adrenal activity to the point where 17-ketosteroids in the urine, represented by androsterone and etiocholanolon, are much reduced. The intrinsic metabolic defect is the inability of the adrenals to complete the synthesis of cortisone. The ACTH rises and excessive stimulation leads to a greater production of the androgens. In normal man about 2-6 mg. of these androgens are produced daily; in normal women the amount is less than 0.5 mg. daily; while in Stein-Leventhal syndrome the daily production may reach 4.0 mg.
