Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The chromosomal examination of a patient affected with a Stein-Leventhal syndrome, a focus of temporal epilepsy and behaviour disturbances of psychological origin did not reveal an anomaly of the heterochromosomes, but an asymmetry of the 16th pair. A technique of precise chromosomal measurements and a method for the statistical analysis of such data are described in detail. They made it possible to determine a 35% increase in the long arms of one of the chromosomes in the pair 16. The meaning of this translocation is discussed in relation to the other anomalies of the pair 16 previously published and with regard to Stein-Leventhal syndrome. The statistical method applied was specially established for the study of the chromosomal anomaly described here; in our opinion, it is, generally speaking, perfectly suitable for the study of translocations of minor quantitative importance.
