N2  - Very recently several therapeutic agents for induction of ovulation in women with ovulatory failure have been made available. These agents have been extensively studied by several investigators and their clinical usefulness has been established. This report is concerned with the results obtained in this department with the use of clomiphene (Clomid), HMG (Pergonal), and HP-FSH. These substances were used in sterile women with ovulatory failure and in fertile women with normal ovulatory cycles in which the ovarian function was inhibited by cyclic administration of an oral contraceptive (Metrulen-M). The response was assessed by direct inspection and biopsies of the ovaries at laparotomy.
