N2  - The authors report 18 cases where the effects of the gonadotropins HMG-S and HCG administered consecutively have been studied by repeated dosages. Although they have been able to realize only 1 or 2 cycles per patient, they describe 13 cases with a luteal response and 5 with pregnancy (among which 4 full term with normal living child). They think that it would be necessary to be able to repeat the treatments for 4 or 5 consecutive months adjusting the doses according to the effects observed during the previous cycles.
