T1  - Stimulation of the gonads by gonadotropins of hypophyseal origin
T3  - Stimulation des gonades par les gonadotropines d'origine hypophysaire
A1  - Jayle M.-F.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The treatment of anovulatory female sterility by a sequential stimulation (in which a gonadotropin with FSH action, generally extracted from the urine of a menopausal woman (HMG), precedes the chorionic gonadotropin (HCG) with LH action) incurs considerable risks such as: a number of fetuses due to the polyovulation, thrombo-embolic accidents, and, in particular, the formation of multiple ovarian cysts which may lead to some peritoneal drama. The dosage most often adopted is 150 units of IRP<ovid:inf>2</ovid:inf> of HMG for 10 days in succession followed by 3 daily injections of 5,000 units of HCG. But to avoid accidents, the dosage should be adapted to the needs of each particular case. In point of fact, there exists a certain relationship between the degree of the polycystic change in the ovaries and the quantities of estrogens, and the amount of pregnanetriol and of 11-desoxy 17-ketosteroids excreted at the end of the sequential treatment. The dynamic HCG-dexamethazone test suggested by Jayle makes it possible to appreciate how great will be the risk incurred because of the sequential treatment. This risk is much reduced when the dynamic test shows low levels of all the steroids evaluated, and in particular that of the estrogens. of the pregnanetriol and of the androsterone + etiocholanolone fraction. On the other hand, if the dynamic test reveals an excess either of the estrogens or of the androgens or of both, accidents must be feared, and the dosage of the HMG reduced to 75 units/day in the course of a first therapeutic trial. Another method for the control consists in doing, every 3 to 5 days after the commencement of treatment by HMG, an assay of the estrogens by a rapid fluorometric method in the night urine, thus making it possible to have the results during the course of the day. When under HMG, the level of the estrogens (between 5 and 20 mg initially) reaches values of between 60 and 100 mg, the follicles have sufficiently developed to be receptive to the action of HCG, a single injection of which brings about ovulation and the formation of corpora lutea. Thus the HCG-dexamethazone test and the control of the HMG by assay of estrogen makes it possible to carry out sequential stimulation of the ovary with relatively little risk and with greater efficacy, by indicating the dosage in cases of feeble response.
