A1  - Lima Filho O.A.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - There has been made a comparative therapeutic study of the compound synthetic progestogens (ethynodioldiacetate, chlormadinone and lynestrenol) and mestranol, covering 94 women who were given 1 tablet daily for 20 consecutive days. The patients have been divided into 3 groups: (1) 22 women with anovulatory cycles but without amenorrhea; (2) 20 women with anovulatory cycles and amenorrhea; and (3) 52 eumenorrheic and normally ovulating women. A total of 810 cycles have been studied (66 from group I, 120 from group II and 624 from group III). The ethynodiol acetate produced anovulatory cycles in 60% of patients from group I and 100% of those from group II. Such cycles were obtained in all the women of group I and in 88.8% of group II with chlormadinone. The main side-effects produced by the combinations were the following: Ethynodiol/mestranol: mastodynia (45.4%). Chlormadinone/mestranol: headache (30%), break-through bleeding (25%), emotional instability (20%), and clinical signs of phlebitis (20%). Lynestrenol/mestranol: emotional instability (19.3%) and hirsutism (11.5%).
