N2  - The authors did a biopsy of endometrium, in the 2nd stage of the cycle, in 21 women with a story of habitual abortion. They found a good luteinic activity in 52.35%; organic anomalies in 19%; absence of ovulation in 47.65% of all cases. The comparison between the biopsy of the endometrium and colpocytology showed a disagreement in 14.2% of the cases. Concluding, they found that there are clear causes of habitual abortion in 90.43% of the cases; in the other, 9.57%, they did not find any cause by the usual methods of inquiry.
