N2  - In a group of 24 women with various gynecologic disorders primarily seen for infertility, clomifene citrate was administered to induce ovulation. Five pregnancies were obtained, 1 of them ectopic. Two patients had massive enlargement of the right ovary following the 1st course of treatment; in both cases the ovarian enlargement regressed spontaneously within 2 wk. No other side effects were recorded. Clomifene citrate was also administered to 8 oligospermic males. One patient's wife became pregnant. There is no certainty, however, that this pregnancy resulted from the husband's treatment.
