T1  - Differential diagnosis of hypertrichosis
T3  - Zur differentialdiagnose des hirsutismus
A1  - Kucera F.
A1  - Sarembe B.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - On the assumption that endocrine diseases which do not manifest characteristic symptoms require more comprehensive diagnostics, 5 cases of hirsutism and oligo-amenorrhea were tested by applying hormonal functional tests. The authors diagnosed a Cushing syndrome, a congenital adrenogenital syndrome, as well as 3 cases of polycystic ovaries. The diagnosis established by the hormonal functional tests was confirmed by laparotomy. The therapy initiated was successful in all cases. Menstruation now proceeds according to the cycle being of normal duration and intensity. The hirsutic process was arrested and the women's general state of health markedly improved. For examining the functional reserve of the adrenal cortex the authors applied the ACTH test, while the hypophyseal inhibitory test was applied for excluding an adrenal cortical tumor. The FSH test and the progesterone test both gave an insight into ovarian function. Both the theoretical conception and the practical application of these tests are explained in detail. These tests are valuable in the differential diagnostics of endocrine borderline cases of female hirsutism.
