T1  - Prolonged treatment with ovulation inhibitors. The endometrium, cervix uteri and vaginal epithelium after cyclic prolonged treatment with a progestogen-estrogen mixture for the inhibition of ovulation (histological, cytological and colposcopic findings)
T3  - Langzeitbehandlung mit ovulationshemmern. Endometrium, cervix uteri und vaginalepithel nach zyklischer langzeitbehandlung mit einem progestagen-ostrogen-gemisch zur ovulationshemmung (histologische, zytologische und kolposkopische befunde)
A1  - Breinl H.
A1  - Warnecke W.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - In 67 women after longterm treatment with a mixture of hormones inhibiting ovulation, composed of 4 mg of norethisterone acetate and 0.05 mg ethinyl estradiol, careful colposcopic, cytologic and histologic investigations were carried out. The histomorphologic state of the endometrium may be described as that of a gestagen-like effect as an insufficiently proliferated 'transitional endometrium'. There was no atrophy but a sort of 'resting cycle' of the endometrium, that was started off in 92% of the patients as early as the 1st drug-free cycle by typical changing phases of the mucosa of the corpus, together with a biphasic BT curve. The cytohormonal diagnosis from the vaginal smear showed that fine endocrinologic changes were going on. The cytogram faithfully reflected the estrogen-progestogen mixed effect during the treatment and in the sequence of pre- and postovulatory function patterns allowed a distinction to be drawn between hypofolliculin-anovulatory cycles and cycles with only a prolonged follicle maturation phase. A rise in the quota of abnormal and atypical colposcopic findings is to be explained by the exogenous hormonal influence of the surface relief during longterm treatment with the progestogen-estrogen mixture. By means of the cytologic and histologic controls it was possible in only 1 (1.5%) of 67 women, to observe truly atypical epithelium (carcinoma in situ of the pavement epithelium). In comparison with large average groups, this does not signify any rise in the atypia quota. On account of the high indicative value with regard to the degree of the proliferative and metaplastic processes, cytology must be considered of greater importance than colposcopy in checking the epithelium of the cervix during treatment with ovulation inhibitors.
