T1  - Influence of oral gestagens on increased elimination of neutral 17-Ketosteroids and 17-Hydroxycorticosteroids in anovulatory, sexually mature females
T3  - Uber den einfluss oraler gestagene auf die erhohte ausscheidung der neutralen 17-Ketosteroide und 17-Hydroxycortico-steroide anovulatorischer geschlechtsreifer frauen
A1  - Gitsch E.
A1  - Friedrich F.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Forty female patients with pathologic amenorrhea, monophasic cycles and oligomenorrhea were divided into 3 groups of 20, 11 and 9 females each. The action of Delpregnin (5 mg megestrol acetate and 0.1 mg mestranol), Niagestin (5 mg megestrol acetate) and Anovlar (4 mg norethiaterone acetate and 0.05 mg ethinyl estradiol) on the increase in elimination of neutral 17-KS and total 17-OHCS commonly present in these cases was tested and concomitantly the effect on the endocrine disturbances studied. All 3 groups showed a significant decrease in 17-KS elimination and the Delpregnin and Niagestin groups also of 17-OHCS. In 7 out of 8 patients with increased or normal gonadotropin elimination this decreased; which was demonstrable immediately after completion of the treatment. Eight temporary successes and 2 pregnancies among the 31 patients of the first 2 groups and the withdrawal bleeding precipitable in all cases suggest the causative action of the therapy applied. In the group treated with Anovlar 8 out of 9 patients responded with a withdrawal bleeding.
