T3  - Pneumopelvigraphia Stein-Leventhal syndromaban
A1  - Berta I.
A1  - Kelemen J.
A1  - Nagy T.
A1  - Gorgey M.
A1  - Jona G.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome (virilization, hirsutism, male-type distribution of genital hair, negative anomalies of the genital cycle, sterility, monophasic cycles, eventually a moderate preponderance of the estrogens and enlarged ovaries) may be confused with androgen imbalance; therefore the greatest importance should be attributed to the verification of ovarian enlargement. Because of the uncertainty of clinical examination in nulliparae and in virgins, pelvipneumography alone or in combination with hysterosalpingography is the method of choice in these cases. Of 27 patients with the clinical Stein-Leventhal syndrome examined with pelvipneumography, 13 were confirmed by operation. Six cases are reported in this paper.
