A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Sebaoun M.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A report is presented of 16 cases of very early menopause. In these 16 cases, there were unilateral or bilateral anatomical signs of ovarian dysgenesia. In 14 cases, the karyotype was normal and in 2 cases the chromosomic pattern was of the mosaic type XX-Xx. The nosology of these early menopauses is discussed and the conclusion is drawn that all transitions between gonadal agenesia and some nonhereditary and nonneurogenic early menopauses do exist.
