T1  - Pelvipneumography in gynecologic lesions. II. Differential diagnosis, indications and side effects
T3  - Die pneumopelvigraphie in der gynakologischen diagnostik. ii. differentialdiagnostische bedeutung. Indikationen und nebenwirkungen
A1  - Richter K.
A1  - Mach S.
A1  - Lisewski G.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The differential diagnosis of findings on pneumopelvigraphy in diseases of the internal female genitalia is discussed on the basis of 200 examinations, and the method is illustrated. Particular attention is paid to the problem whether the method represents genuine improvement in gynecologic diagnosis. The method is superior to all other available examinations in the clarification of uncertain physical findings, in the demonstration and localization of recurrent malignancy, in the demonstration of ovarian size in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome and in examining the internal genitalia in congenital abnormalities and gonadal dysgenesis and agenesis. The indications and contraindications are described and figures for the radiation dose to the gonads are given.
