T3  - L'incidenza dell'ipoluteinismo e del ciclo anovulatorio in un gruppo di donne soggette ad aborto abituale. Indagine colpocitologica
A1  - Dalla Pria S.
A1  - Minucci D.
A1  - Pelusi G.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Vaginal smears, taken in the 2nd phase of the cycle from 45 women with habitual abortion, were examined. Good luteinic activity was present in 31.1%, luteinic deficiency together with hyperestrogenic activity in 11.1% and with hypoestrogenic activity in 44.4% of the women. In 13.3% absence of ovulation was observed, in half the cases associated with hyperestrogenic activity and in the other half with hypoestrogenic activity.
