T1  - Pregnancy after combined HMG-HCG treatment in amenorrheic patients
A1  - Pasetto N.
A1  - Montanino G.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The results reported in the literature show that treatment with human gonadotropins (HMG-HCG) is especially effective in cases of primary and secondary amenorrhea and anovulatory menstrual cycles. It is now stated that changes in the vaginal smear and in the volume and other characteristics of the cervical mucus are good indices of ovarian function during treatment with gonadotropins. It is also possible to avoid the overstimulation syndrome or multiple pregnancy by measuring the dose of gonadotropin according to the response of the 'target organs'. In 25 cases of amenorrhea (3 primary and 22 secondary), 17 pregnancies were obtained; 16 of them continued to term and the patients gave birth to living, viable infants. All were single pregnancies; only 1 miscarriage occurred and this was in a woman with bilateral ovarian cysts.
