N2  - HCG in a dose of 25,000 U was employed for inducing ovulations in 8 cases of anovulation that developed during artificial insemination. Two pregnancies and 16 presumably ovulatory cycles followed. The authors stress emotional conflicts as a cause for delayed ovulation. Lack of correlation between BBT thermal shift and culdoscopic examination in 2 patients following the treatment is reported.
