N2  - Five of 7 patients with bilateral polycystic ovaries had a history of CNS injury. In some of these patients the evidence of CNS injury was not elicited until special efforts were made to find it. The association of brain damage, hirsutism, and polycystic ovary in this group of patients conforms with the concept of a central mechanism for the development of polycystic ovaries.
