T1  - The inhibition of ovulation by the sequential method
T3  - Inhibicion de la ovulacion con el metodo secuencial
A1  - Dexeus Trias De Bes J.M.
A1  - Carrera Macia J.M.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A study was made of the anovulatory activity of sequential treatment, constituted by the combination of mestranol and chlormadinone. A genital physiologic control was carried out as well as the side effects studied by means of clinical observation, hormonal and morphologic cytology, estimating the basal temperature and the hormones, examining the cervical mucus, and by means of colposcopy and biopsy of the endometrium. From a study of the charts of 82 puerperal women, with a total of 492 carefully supervised cycles, the conclusion is drawn that sequential treatment, and especially the combination of drugs in the present study, has proved itself to be a highly efficient anovulatory therapy, especially with regard to genital physiology. It is almost completely free of any appreciable side effects.
