T3  - Attualita terapeutiche nel ciclo anovulare
A1  - Danesino V.
A1  - Monteforte C.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The progress which has been made, particularly during the last decade, in the treatment of the anovulatory cycle, and the various therapeutic possibilities are discussed. After pointing out that most successful therapies are based on the use of gonadotropins and clomifene, the desirability of the selection of a certain therapy in connection with the endocrine syndromes of each patient is stressed. It is emphasized that a correct interpretation of the hormonal deficiency responsible for the anovulatory cycle is fundamental for a rational selection of patients in connection with present-day therapeutic possibilities.
