T1  - Radiologic exploration of tumors of the uterus and adnexa uteri
T3  - Explorations radiologiques des tumeurs uterines et annexielles
A1  - Walter J.P.
A1  - Destree J.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Gynecography, or pneumopelvigraphy, is a method seldom used nowadays for exploring the uterus; yet is is a simple, painless means of visualizing and defining tumors of the womb and adnexa. It is the method indicated mainly for these tumors in conjunction with Stein-Leventhal's syndrome, As lymphography provides evidence as to the integrity or otherwise of the lymphatic glands, this mode of examination enables the physician to form an opinion as to the extent of the growth, the prognosis and the therapeutic prospects of surgery. Very exact information about the gynecologic tumors in question can be obtained by applying the 2 above methods one after the other with a day's interval and reproducing the results in 1 photograph.
