T1  - Treatment of idiopathic anovulatory cycles by X-ray stimulation
A1  - Ainslie W.H.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Small series of patients with idiopathic anovulatory cycles has been presented and treatment by X-ray stimulation outlined. The pregnancy rate in this series was 69% of those so treated. Live babies were delivered to 49% of the mothers in this group. All but 3 patients ovulated within 3 mth. The establishment of ovulation by X-ray stimulation is transient in most cases, usually lasting less than 1 yr. Nine of this series reverted to anovulatory cycles. Pregnancy in this series usually took place in the first 3 mth after treatment. This method for treatment is simple and can be carried out by a competent radiologist with minimum of equipment and expense.
