T1  - Bilateral polycystic ovaries. A histologic study of surgical biopsies on unselected cases
T3  - Ovaires polykystiques bilateraux. Une etude histologique de biopsies chirurgicales faites sans selection des cas
A1  - Procopio-Valle Y.
A1  - Chagas W.A.
A1  - De Paola D.
A1  - De Souza Matsui A.
A1  - Goulart De Andrade C.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - This interesting histologic study reports a comparison between, on the one hand, bilateral polycystic ovaries discovered in unselected women submitted to laparotomy because of various diseases and on the other fragments of wedge resection obtained from women exhibiting the socalled Stein-Leventhal syndrome. A rigorous study, both histologic and clinical, of both groups allows the conclusion to be reached that, apart from some signs such as obesity and hirsutism, and a greater frequency, purely quantitative, in the histologic changes, there are few differences between these 2 groups of patients except that the majority of women with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome were young persons.
