A1  - Grattarola R.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The analysis of variance of the values for total urinary 11-deoxy-17-ketosteroids shows highly significant differences between the 4 experimental groups (P<0.001). The mean value (3.77 mg/24 hr) of the total 11-deoxy-17-ketosteroids in the control subjects with an ovula tory cycles was significantly higher (P<0.01) than the mean (2.24 mg/24 hr) of the total 11-deoxy-17-ketosteroids of the controls with ovulatory cycles. The mean value (4.76 mg/24 hr) of the total urinary 11-deoxy-17-ketosteroids in patients with breast cancer and anovulatory cycles was higher (3.04 mg/24 hr) than that in patients with breast cancer and ovulatory cycles; the difference was highly significant (P<0.001).
