AN  - 288087560
T1  - Clinical observations on cases of sterility in the Women's Clinic of Kyoto University: A consideration on the cause of sterility
A1  - Nishimura T.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The causes of sterility in a series of 798 infertile couples were studied. The average duration of infertility was 4.5 yr. The younger the age at marriage, the longer was the duration of infertility. The most frequent feature in the case history was appendicitis (140 cases) while tb was found in 75 cases. Operations for treatment of sterility were carried out in 70 cases. The causes of sterility were established in 634 cases. At gynecologic examination, uterine hypoplasia was observed in 188 cases. Displacement of uterus, and uterine or tuboovarian tumors were found in 96 and 45 cases. resp. Azoospermia or oligospermia was found in 217 cases of primary sterility and in 45 cases of secondary sterility. Complete occlusion of the tubes was found in 36 cases and insufficient patency of the tubes in 118 cases by means of kymoinsufflation and hysterosalpingography. The Huhner or Miller-Kurzrock test was negative in 68 of 294 cases. In 101 of 296 endometrial biopsies there was luteal dysplasia. The menstrual cycle was irregular in 40 out of 58 anovulatory cases.
