N2  - Chromosomal analysis of a patient affected. with St ein- Leve nth ai syndrome, temporal focal epilepsy, behavior disturbances of psychological origin and a family history of psychological disturbances, revealed asymmetry of the 16th pair. A technique of precise chromosomal measurements and a method for the statistical analysis of such data are described. It was possible to determine a 35% increase in the long arms of one of the chromosomes no. 16. The meaning of this translocation is discussed in relation to the other anomalies of no. 16 chromosomes previously published and with regard to Stein- Leventhal syndrome.
