A1  - Pinto R.M.
A1  - Leon C.
A1  - Mazzocco N.
A1  - Scasserra V.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A double blind study was conducted on 100 pregnant patients at term to determine the effect of estradiol-17beta on the onset of labor. Those patients who did not enter spontaneous labor within 7 days were subjected to induction on the 8th day. A maximum dose of 5 U of oxytocin was administered. Patients treated with estradiol started labor before nontreated patients, and the difference between both groups was statistically significant. Significantly lower doses of oxytocin had to be used for induction of those patients treated with estradiol.
