T1  - The stedm-leventhal syndrome
T3  - Le syndrome de Stein-Leventhal
A1  - Botella Llusia J.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Because of the present major confusion concerning this syndrome, the author retains only the one that has as characteristic feature large polyfollicular ovaries with hyperthecosis and virilization. As regards etiology, this syndrome is considered by him as an enzymatic disease perhaps linked with a chromosomal defect. Endocrinologic ally, relations exist between ovarian and adrenal metabolisms and therefore between the Stein-Leventhal and the adrenogenital syndrome. Histologie ally, the syndrome appears to constitute a true ovarian collagenosis. After some clinical and diagnostic observations (certainty is only brought by laparotomy). the author insists on the efficiency of wedge resection complemented by a demedullation of the ovary. He thinks nevertheless that the results thus obtained are less good than those reported hereafter. In short, the Stein-Leventhal syndrome has its own limits and it would be more advisable to exchange its present denomination for the term 'juvenile hyperthecosis' which appears as more logical. (10, 3, 5, 6).
