N2  - The authors studied the activity of steroid 30-ol dehydrogenase and glucose 6-phosphate in normal and pathologic human ovaries using 7 kinds of steroids as the substrate. In theca and granulosa lutein cells of the corpus luteum, no correlation was found between the distributions of glucose 6-phosphate and steroid 3/3-ol dehydrogenases. The activity of both enzymes showed similar distribution and intensity in normal follicle and cystic follicle of the polycystic ovary. An intense steroid dehydrogenase activity for androstane-30-ol, 17one and 5-androstene-3s-ol, 17-one in a luteinizing cyst associated with a chorionic tumor was suggestive of an abnormal steroid metabolism in the ovary. (10,3,5*).
