A1  - Cohen J.
A1  - Merger R.
A1  - Krulik O.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - A report is presented on the effect of F. 6066 on anovulation and luteal insufficiency. This preparation may induce ovulation, stimulate the corpus luteum of anovulatory or luteally insufficient females, without secondary effects. Of 11 cases of amenorrhea F. 6066 has induced menstruation in 9 patients, 3 of them at least following an ovulation. In 10 cases of secondary infertility due to luteal insufficiency, 3 pregnancies occurred. In 1 case of anovulatory infertility ovulation has occurred regularly.
