T1  - Duration of fertility after wedge resection of ovary in the course of the stein-leventhal syndrome
T3  - La duree de la fertilite apres resection cuneiforme de l'ovaire au cours du syndrome de Stein Leventhai
A1  - Stein I.F.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Author recalls first the 3 constant signs of the syndrome named after him; secondary anovulation, sterility and bilateral development of polycystic ovaries. The diagnosis is made chiefly with the aid of gynecography and it necessitates, in a fair number of cases, to eliminate virilism. No cure can be obtained in the absence of treatment. Apart from the new drugs that have not shown their whole mettle, hormones appear to have a noxious effect when administered prior to the bilateral wedge resection of ovaries, which remains the only valid treatment. In the course of 34 yr, the author has submitted to surgery 108 patients. Regular periods have appeared in 95% of the instances; 71 women became pregnant. 85fo of which more than 1 time - i.e. 183 pregnancies with 145 live children (5 cases with twins). 40 abortions or stUlborns. 1 ectopic pregnancy. Duration of fertility: in 5 women from 4 to 10 yr; in 17 from 11 to 19 yr; in 8 from 20 to 30 yr. Surgery has to be undertaken as soon as the diagnosis is made without waiting for an eventual marriage. Author has never noted an endometrial carcinoma associated with his syndrome. (10, 3*).
