A1  - Kaminetzky H.A.
A1  - Swerdlow M.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Twenty two patients with polycystic ovary syndrome were treated during 6 yr. Nineteen had wedge resection of the ovary of whom only 10 developed regular ovulatory menses. Three of the 22 patients were treated by prednisone without operation and resumed regular menses. Two patients of the 10 treated successfully by operation had subsequent recurrence of symptoms. The patients were similar in age at treatment, age at menarche. duration of symptoms. 17-ketosteroid excretion, and ovarian histology. No explanation for differences in response to treatment is apparent.
