T3  - Resultats histologiques, biochimiques et therapeutiques obtenus chez les femmes dont les ovaires avaient ete diagnostiques Stein-Leventhal a la coelioscopie
A1  - Palmer H.
A1  - De Brux J.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The finding of 2 large smooth ovaries of porcellaneous appearance is indicative of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, but does not form absolute proof. After the age of 22 their presence malies the Stein-Leventhal syndrome very likely (17 of 18 cases). In subjects younger than 22 the finding of smooth porcellaneous ovaries is not very suggestive of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome (6 of 15 cases only, but possibly some of these patients may eventually be diagnosed as beginning the Stein-Leventhal syndrome). A further report will be given in 4 or 5 years' time. The therapeutic effect of ovarian biopsy is undisputable, as in 18 of 30 cases diphasic cycles were re-established and 6 pregnancies with normal delivery (20%) occurred.
