AN  - 287134976
T1  - Daily tmmunoassay op luteinizing hormone excretion in patients receiving clomiphene citrate
A1  - Mishell Jr. D.R.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - The results obtained in t his study of daily assay of urinary LH excretion in patients receiving clomiphene indicate that the release of LH is secondary to the primary action of the drug. In all 4 patients with oligomenorrhea with either anovulation or oligo-ovulation, who had low baseline levels of LH. a significant rise of LH excretion was observed only after clomiphene treatment had been terminated. In all these patients, the peak of LH excretion consistently occurred at the approximate time of ovulation, whether it was definitely known because pregnancy followed, or presumptive because of the rise in basal body temperature and subsequent menses. The results of this study indicate that clomiphene probably has a primary action on the FSH-estrogen inter-relationship, possibly disrupting an imbalance. Further investigation is needed to determine whether clomiphene acts directly on the pituitary, the ovary, or possibly both organs. Whatever its initial mechanism, the resulting increased estroejen secretion, with possibly some progesterone secretion terminally, apparently stimulates LH release with subsequent ovulation. These latter events are probably similar to those occurring in normal ovulat ing women.
