AN  - 287128769
T1  - Vaginal cytology during puberty
A1  - Sonek M.
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - In order to assess the cytologic patterns of physiological and pathologic conditions during puberty, 212 girls with a physiologic pattern of prepuberty and puberty and 667 girls with disturbances of the menstrual cycle, all ranging in age from 9 to 15 were studied by serial cytologic examinations. In 127 girls with physiologic prepuberty, mixed types of cytologic patterns are very often found, such as irregular proliferation of cells, anisocytosis, giant forms of cells, etc. Cyclic changes were found in 42.5% of the girls examined. The cycles during puberty are characterized by an anovulatory character, by variability, and by lability. In 85 girls with physiologic patterns of puberty it was possible to diagnose anovulatory cycles in 90.6%. Examination of individual cycle disturbances during puberty revealed a predominance of normo- and hyperestrogenic patterns. The typical pattern of the cytological hyperestrogenic syndrome of iuvenile females are also described.
