T1  - Histopathology and ultrastructure of an ovarian hilar cell tumor
A1  - Green J.A.
A1  - Maqueo M.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Description of a tumor which histologically was composed of uniform epithelioid cells containing a brownish cytoplasmic pigment. Fine structure studies revealed an abundance of agranular endoplasmic reticulum and large mitochondria. Pigment granules similar to those seen in testicular Leydig cells were observed in the neoplastic cells. Study of the nonneoplastic ovarian tissue revealed that both ovaries possessed a histologic appearance identical to that of ovaries of the socalled Stein-Leventhal syndrome. This remarkable coexistence of sclerocystic ovaries with hilar cell tumor has not been reported previously.
