T1  - Biosynthetic studies of human ovarian arrhenoblastomatous tissue in vitro. II. Formation of androgens from dehydroisoandrosterone sulfate
A1  - Sandberg E.G.
A1  - Jenkins R.C.
A1  - Trifon H.M.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Virilizing ovarian arrhenoblastomatous tissue was simultaneously incubated with H<ovid:sup>3</ovid:sup>-dehydroisoandrosterone sulfate and C<ovid:sup>14</ovid:sup>-progesterone with and without the addition of human menopausal urinary gonadotropin, HCG and ACTH. A small and indeterminant yield of testosterone was obtained from dehydroisoandrosterone sulfate while androstenedione was obtained from both substrates in a yield of 0.1 to 0.7%. An ancillary incubation using polycystic ovarian tissue was also performed. Similar results were obtained with the exception that no testosterone was recovered. The influence of gonadotropins and ACTH on the conversions of these substrates to androstenedione was inconclusive. No sulfurylated products were noted.
