N2  - The authors studied 155 cases of primary (Stein-Leventhal syndrome) and secondary (hypothalamic syndromes) ovarian insufficiency. A statistically significant increase of I<ovid:sup>131</ovid:sup> uptake was found in both groups showing differences with the clinical findings and results of laboratory investigations. These observations may explain the appearance of increased values of I<ovid:sup>131</ovid:sup> uptake in women despite absence of clinical manifestations of thyroid hyperfunction.
