T1  - Androgen metabolism in man - Some current concepts
A1  - Prunty F.T.G.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - The complexity of gonadal adrenal interaction still presents a challenge to the understanding of androgen metabolism, especially in the polycystic-ovary syndrome. Space has not permitted consideration of the more difficult problem of 'simple hirsutism', in which some of the abnormalities in the polycystic-ovary syndrome are also found. Virilization and precosity in congenital adrenal hyperplasia have also been neglected, but recent reviews on this topic are available. The new ability to study testosterone metabolism in detail (labeled androgens) is leading to big advances in the understanding and diagnosis of abnormalities of the adrenals and gonads; at least it is now possible to distinguish clearly between the sexes, and to recognize eunuchoid individuals by direct biochemical means.
