A1  - Goldzieher J.G.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A description of the different hormonal activities on the hypophysis, cervical mucosa, endometrium and possibly on the ovaries, is followed by a discussion on rapid restoration of fertility immediately after therapeutic interruption. Besides anovulatory efficiency, other advantages are indicated, such as regulation and control of dysmenorrhea. As regards side effects, the author analyzes the hypothesis of fetal masculinization due to progestational compounds and affirms that no proofs exist that in normal dosage human beings may be affected in this aspect. It is concluded that the combination norethindrone-mestranol is useful and acts in several biologic plans to give an effective result which is 40-200 times more efficient than any other method.
