T3  - O tratamento sequencial para propiciar ciclos anovulatorios
A1  - Oclander G.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - After generalizations on the use of combined anovulatory drugs, progestational and estrogenic, with emphasis on the inconvenience of this method, reference is made to the so-called sequential method, attention being drawn to the growing use of 'Sequens', which utilizes mestranol for 18 days followed by 5 days of mestranol associated with chlormadinone. Proofs are presented that the histologic aspect of the endometrium during 1 cycle of treatment differs very little from that of normal cycles. With abundant statistical material the author studies the duration of the cycles (emphasizing the maximum frequency of 27-28 days), the interval of hormonal suppression before the bleeding, the duration and volume of the hemorrhage by deprivation of the hormone, the incidence of dysmenorrhea before and after prolonged treatment, and the incidence of intermenstrual spotting and transhormonal bleeding.
