N2  - 19-Hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone is aromatized to eetrone and estradiol by placental and ovarian preparation in vitro in higher yields than androstenedione or testosterone, the yields being approximately equal to those of aromatization of 19-hydroxyandrostenedione and 19-hydroxvtestosterone. In a microsomal + cytoplasmatic fraction of polycystic ovaries 19-hydroxydehydroepiandroaterone could be demonstrated among the metabolic products of dehydroepiandrosterone incubation. ( 3, 2b*).
