N2  - Twenty-four patients with primary or secondary amenorrhea were treated with human menopaueal gonadotrophin (HMG) for 3 days. A gradual rise in estrogen excretion continuing for 2-4 days after HMG treatment indicated ovarian responsiveness. Inadequate responses were found in 6 patients, and satisfactory responses in 11, 10 of whom subsequently ovulated on gonadotrophin or clomiphene citrate treatment. Overresponses (7 patients) indicated cystic or polycystic ovaries; 6 patients in this group, when treated further, ovulated. This ovarian function test may be useful as a preliminary to clomiphene citrate treatment.
