N2  - Urinary pregnanetriol in apparently normal Indian women varied from 0.08 to 2.78 mg. per 24 hours with a mean of 0.82 +/-0.20. Excretion of thie steroid did not differ quantitatively from that in adrenocortical syndromes or in hirsutiem associated with the polycystic ovaries. On the other hand, none of the normal subjects excreted pregnanetriolone before or after the administration of a standard test dose of ACTH. The excretory pattern of pregnanetriolone varied in adrenocortical dis eases as well as in hirsutiam associated with polycystic ovaries. This knowledge was of help in delineating the etiological pathology in such cases.
