T1  - The determination by gas chromatography of the testosterone in the plasma or polycystic disease of the ovaries
T3  - Deterininazione gas-chromatografica del testosterone plasmatico nella policistosi ovarica
A1  - Surace M.
A1  - Polvani F.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A detailed description of the original method used for the determination of plaema testosterone is given. This utilizes preparatory horizontal thin layer chroma tography followed by subsequent identification and quantitative evaluation by means of gaseous phase chromatography. The method's reproducibility, precision and sensitivity have been checked, also by the use of testosterone 4-C14. The results obtained for healthy male and female subjects are similar to those reported by other authors. An increased plaema testosterone level was found in hirsute women, and was found to be particular Iy significant in women suffering from polycystic ovar ies. Dynamic tests of ffonadotropin stimulation and adrenal inhibition, and cuneiform resection of the ovaries led to changes in the plaema testosterone values indicating a definite ovarian genesis of the high testosterone level in the hirsutism patterns studied.
