T1  - Reversible sterility induced by medroxyprogesterone injections
A1  - Coutinho E.M.
A1  - De Souza J.C.
A1  - Csapo A.I.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - The present study reports 100% efficiency in the dose range 50-400 mg. with an injection interval of 1-3 mth. Although all side effects disappeared at the end of treatment, and the normal cycles returned, this regimen must be improved in order to reduce significantly the side effects and thus make the treatment more acceptable. According to the literature the contraceptive effect of endocrine regimens, such as the present one. are due to reduction of gonadotrophin secretion produced by action of the progestogens on the hypophysis. This conclusion is based largely on the finding of atrophie endometrium during and after treatment. This observation well explains the persistent amenorrhea in the majority of patients. The inhibition of gonadotrophin secretion is thought to result in anovulatory cycles and upset the cyclic activity of the ovaries. Since a suppression of anterior-lobe function suppresses the secretory activity of the thyroid and the adrenals, this type of contraceptive regimen should not be employed when the function of these glands is already reduced.
