T1  - ESTROGEN SYNTHESIS by OVARIAN CORTEX and MEDULLA from STEIN-LEVENTHAL PATIENTS
A1  - Noall M.W.
A1  - Kaufman R.H.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Ovarian tissue from Stein-Leventhal patients was grossly dissected into cortical and medullary zones. Slices from the 2 zones were each incubated in vitro with 17ahydroxypregnenolone-7a-H3 and testosterone -4 -C14. and steroid conversion products were determined. The ratio of H3/C14 in the isolated estradiol and estrone was similar to that in the tracer substrate mixture before incubation, thus indicating an approximately equal conversion of the 2 substrates to estradiol-estrone. In contrast, the total yield of activity in estradiol-estrone was 2.1-15 times greater per g. of cortical tissue slices as compared to medullary tissue. The results confirm the ability of ovarian tissues from Stein-Leventhal patients to synthesize estrogen from neutral steroid precursors. The concept of a specific metabolic block in the aromatizing enzymes is not supported.
