N2  - In 88% of 54 patients treated with progestational drugs for menstrual disorders and acne vulgaris, a favorable effect was seen on the skin disorder. In 24% results were very good, in 20% good and in 56% subjectively satisfactory, the skin felt softer and less greasy. The possible mechanism of the drug ('anovlar'), dragees containing 4 mg of ethinylnortest oster one acetate and 0.05 mg of ethinyl-estradiol) is discussed. Further studies in a greater number of patients are necessary. (XIII, 2c*).
