T1  - Clinical trial of an anovulatory drug composed of lynestrenol and mestranol
T3  - Ensayo clinico de un preparado antiovulatorio compuesto de Lynestrenoly Mestranol
A1  - Cremades Marco J.
A1  - Botella Llusia J.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A study was made of the evolution of a group of 7 women treated with a combination of Lynestrenol and Mestranol (Anacyclin, Ciba) according to the normal procedure of 3 straight months. In these women no pregnancy started during the treatment period. The tolerance was good, although nausea was observed, mainly during the first month, as well as breast tension and nervousness. The basic temperature showed a typical pattern of constant hyperthermia, the curves being not absolutely horizontal, but wavy. The vaginal cytology was in all cases cyclic, with karyopycnosis and acidophilic in the 2nd week and with folded cells in the 3rd and 4th. The endometrium showed the most important changes. In all but one case, the endometrium did not react with secretory atrophy, associated with a preceding hyperplasia. Finally, the blood coagulation is not affected and the biphasic function of the endometrium, temperature and vagina was recovered in all cases during the 1st month after discontinuation of the treatment.
