N2  - Description of a bilar cell tumor, Histologically the tumor was composed of uniform epithelioid cells containing a brownish cytoplasmic pigment. Fine structure studies revealed an abundance of agranular endoplasmic reticulum and large mitoeiiondria. Pigment granules similar to those seen in testicular Leydig cells were observed in the neoplastic cells. Study of the nonneoplastic ovarian tissue revealed that both ovaries possessed a histologie appearance identical to that of ovaries of the so-called Stein-Leventhal syndrome. This remarkable coexistence of sclerocystic ovaries with hilar cell tumor has not been reported nrpviouRlv (10/3,5.16).
