N2  - A patient with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome who was found to have a benign cystic teratoma of one ovary is described. The tumor was discovered on culdoscopic examination. Among 241 examples of Stein-Leventhal syndrome on file at the AFIP. 11 patients also had ovarian tumors, an incidence of 4.6%. It is recommended that culdoscopic examination and uterine curettage be routinely performed before institution of nonsurgical therapy.
