T1  - Serum enzyme studies on liver damage from oral anovulatory drugs
T3  - Serumenzym-Untersuchungen zur Frage der Leber - Schadigung durch orale Ovulationshemmer
A1  - Daci Z.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A report is given on the results of determinations of GOT, GPT. LDH and serum cholinesterase in the serum of 80 women who had taken anovulatory drugs for 1-24 cycles. Except for one case, where the GPT activity was increased by 23.6 IU (this finding could not be checked and therefore it was not evaluated) the enzyme-activities were normal. With reference to the role of the liver in estrogen metabolism the possibility of liver damage from anovulatory drugs (cholestatic or toxic-allergic drug jaundice) is discussed. From a study of the literature and from personal findings the decision is reached that there is no hepatotoxic effect. However, for reasons of safety, treatment with oral anovulatory drugs is not recommended for patients with damaged liver.
