T1  - Parallelism between clinical and morphologic manifestations in patients with dysplastic mucosa of corpus uteri (pussian)
A1  - Vishnevskaya L.G.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Morphologic features of the dysplastic mucosa of the corpus uteri were correlated with the clinical features of the disease in 110 patients. A majority of tiie patients had hypofunction of the ovaries. In addition. 48 patients had functional changes in adrenal cortices, thyroid glands and metabolic processes. Marked changes were present in the uterine mucosa: the epithelium was unevenly flattened and microcellular containing dark and pyknotic nuclei. Fibrous structures were frequently present; accumulations of collagen fibers were localized mainly in the deeper strata of the functional layer. A dense network of irregularly interwined argyrophilic fibers was present. It could be concluded that dysplastic uterine mucosa occurs predominantly in young patients with a long history of anovulatory menstrual disorders of various origins which have been treated with hormones for long periods of time<< and accordingly that institution of hormone treatment without a preliminary histologie examination of the endometrium is unjustifiable. Rafalkes - Moscow.
