T1  - The clinical diagnosis of an abnormality of the steroid production in the ovaries, similar to that which in-vitro characterizes the stein-leventhal syndrome
T3  - Ensayo para el reconocimiento clinic o de una alteracion de la esteroidogenesis ovarica. similar a la que caracteriza, 'in vitro', el sindrome de Stein-Leventhal
A1  - Patrono V.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - The author's studies have shown that in a considerable number of women with hirsutism even when associated to menstrual disorders, urinary 17-ketosteroids increase 48 hr following the administration of 25 mg of progesterone. This increase never occurs in normal women. According to the author this phenomenon is constant and occurs also after inhibition of the adrenal cortex with dexamethasone. It would be indicative of a faster and greater intraovarian formation of precursors of the urinary 17-ketosteroids from progesterone. In other words, it would be the consequence of a disorder of ovarian steroidogenesis, similar to the alteration which characterizes in vitro the ovaries of women with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. In this paper a modification of the original progesterone test is proposed which is to be done during the administration of dexamethasone. In this way the results would be free of possible extraovarian interferences.
