T3  - Il clomifene nella patologia ovulatoria
A1  - Giaquinto M.
A1  - Conte D.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - On the basis of the doctrinal presumptions in recent experimental and clinical studies on the action of clomifene citrate, the authors of the present work have treated the therapeutic problems of the various pathologic aspects of ovulation induced by clomifene therapy. Forty-three patients 6 of which presented polycystic ovaries (SteinLeventhal syndrome) were treated; 16 had uterine disfunctional bleeding, and 22 anovulatory cycles with secondary amenorrhea and severe oligomenorrhea. This group of 43 patients underwent functional investigations such as vaginal cytology. Fern test, hormonal dosages (gonadotropins. pregnanediol. 17-ketosteroids. 17-hydroxycorticoids). basal temperature besides the ordinary routine examinations. From an analysis of the results obtained, the metabolic tests<< and the possible mechanisms of action of clomifene, the authors assume that this drug has remarkable possibilities although the nosology and clinical indications of its use are not. as yet. clearly defined. (10.2C*).
