T1  - Present-day notions on the steinleventhal syndrome
T3  - Ideas actuates sobre el sindrome de Stein-Leventhal
A1  - Botella Llusia J.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A report is given of 2types of cases with polymicrocyetic ovaries, one without any thecal hypoplasia and the other with hyperthecosis and associated with raised urinary 17-ketosteroids and other manifestations of virilization. The etiology of the syndrome is thought to be due to a block in the transformation of progesterone to estrogen so that excessive amounts of androstenedione are produced. It is assumed that changes in both the pituitary and in the suprarenal cortex are secondary to those in the ovary. Treatment with corticosteroids has little value in the true Stein -Leventhal syndrome and wedge resection gives much better results, although the mechanism of its action remains obscure. It is suggested that the name St ein-Leventhal syndrome should be abandoned and the more comprehensive term juvenile hyperthecosis substituted.
