Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A cooperative placebo-double blind study has been conducted by 5 investigators experienced in the use of clomiphene. They selected patients with prolonged anovulation to receive clomiphene and placebo, resp., in 2 courses of treatment. Ovulatory response to clomiphene occurred in 29 patients, to placebo in 1, to both in 6, and to neither in 29 patients. Incidence of ovulatory response to clomiphene was highly significant as compared with placebo. No evidence of 'carry-over' effect of clomiphene on the succeeding cycle was noted.
