N2  - In 1961 Lunenfeld et al. presented their initial report on the use of Pergonal, an extract of human postmenopausal urine, sequentially administered with HCG for the induction of ovulation in anovulatory patients. Subsequent reports have confirmed the effectiveness of this preparation in both the induction of ovulation and subsequent pregnancy. The present report describes the experience with this material in 20 patients with infertility associated with amenorrhea or anovulation.
