T3  - Niektore k Uni eke aspekty benfgneho hirzutizmu. i
A1  - Hrnciar J.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Hirsutism is from the pathologic aspect a complicated and heterogeneous symptom. There is no difference between ovarian and adrenal hirsutism as regards intensity and distribution of hair. Hirsutism, obesity and endocraniosis are coinciding symptoms without a causal mutual relationship. Every 4th case of hirsutism corresponds to the clinical picture of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. The frequent finding of raised ctf and *y-globulin levels in hirsutic women is due to the overproduction of cortisol and biologically potent androgens.
