T1  - Induction of ovulation by clomiphene citrate
A1  - Gupta A.N.
A1  - Carey H.M.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - A series of 32 cases with ovulation failure were treated with 100 mg/day of clomiphene for 5 days; 18 (56.25%) ovulated and 9 (28.2%) became pregnant. There was a highly significant difference in response of 26 cases of primary infertility as compared to the results observed in 6 cases of secondary infertility. In the former 34.6% became pregnant and 65.4% ovulated, as compared to no pregnancy and 16.6% ovulation in the secondary infertility group. There was no correlation of response with the initial cornification index in the vaginal smear. Cases of polycystic disease of the ovary showed the highest (87.5%) incidence of ovulation. In the dose schedule described the side effects were minimal, the most significant being temporary ovarian enlargement in 9.3%. The majority of patients who ovulated (77.7%) showed a constant response. This paper is an interim report, as 18 of the 32 cases have had less than 3 courses.
