T1  - Stein-leventhal syndrome: resection versus clomiphene therapy
A1  - Cohen M.R.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - In a group of 24 patiens with the St ein-Le vent h al syndrome treated with clomiphene citrate during 60 cycles, 40 cycles showed typical diphasic temperature curves. Only 4 cases were completely refractory to therapy. There were 8 pregnancies in 7 patients treated with clomiphene; 5 were term single births, 2 patients are currently pregnant, and 1 patient delivered triplets at term. Six patients were considered clomiphene failures and have had ovarian resections; 5 of them have conceived. Side effects to clomiphene were minimal except in 1 patient who developed large bilateral cysts. Her case report is included. The pathology of the SteinLeventhal syndrome is reviewed. Zn th<< Steiii-Leventhal syndrome an adequate trial is urged of therapy with clomiphene citrate before resorting to bilateral ovarian resection.
