N2  - The gross pathology, histopathology, and ultrastructure were described for a hilar cell tumor that had been the subject of extensive clinical and biochemical investigation. Histologie ally the tumor was composed of uniform epithelioid cells containing a brownish cytoplasmic pigment. Fine structure studies revealed an abundance of agranular endoplasmic reticulum and large mitochondria. Pigment granules similar to those seen in testicular Leydig cells were observed in the neoplastic cells. Study of the nonneoplaetic ovarian tissue revealed that both ovaries possessed a histologie appearance identical to thai of ovaries of the socallcd Stein Lcvcnthal syndrome. This remarkable coexistence of sclerocystic ovaries with hilar cell tumor has not been reported previously. (10,3,5.16*).
