T1  - Study of the action of two antiovulatory gestagens on the histologic structure of the endometrium
T3  - Ensayo de dos gestagenos antiovulatorios sobre la estructura histologica del endometrio
A1  - Merlo J.G.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - Two groups of 5 women were treated: one group with a typical antiovulatory drug and the other group with a new drug, Metruien-M. containing 1 mg of ethinodiol acetate, a. very potent gestagen. and 0.1 mg of ethinyl estradiol. In both groups endometrial atrophy was observed principally of the glandular part, more marked in the group treated with Metrulen. The reaction of the endometrium was therefore atypical and 'nonprogestional'. This finding suggests that sterilization may not be exclusively anovulatory hut may be also due to inhibition of the implantation of the ovum in the uterine mucosa, i.e. to 'very precocious abortion*. The authors, therefore, feel that it would be both illicit and immoral for this procedure to be generally adopted. Beato - Burgos (10, 2c, 3. 5, 21*).
