T1  - Features of steroid genesis in patients with steinleventhal syndrome (Russian)
A1  - Zelenetskaya V.S.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - In 38 patients suffering from the Stein- Leventhal syndrome, the urine over a 24-hr period contained various steroids reflecting individual stages of steroid genesis, after stimulation of the ovaries with chorionic gonadotropin. It was found that the most characteristic index of this disease is the Level of excretion of androstanolone. In cases where the initial level of androstanolone in the urine was low. after the administration of chor ionic gonadotropin an increased excretion of pregnanetriol. 17 -ketosteroiusand androstanolone was observed; the output of estradiol remained unchanged. In cases of increased level of androstanolone in the urine, after the administration of chor ionic gonadotropin there was a reduced excretion of androstanolone with a simultaneous increase in the content of estradiol. The findings indicate that a high level of androstanolone in the urine is associated with a deficiency of the enzyme 3s-ol-dehydrogenase, and a low level with deficiency of the enzyme 19-hydroxylase.
