T1  - Spontaneous mixed androgenic vaginal smears in young women
T3  - Frottis vaginaux androgeniques mixtes spontanes chez la femme jeune
A1  - Herve R.
A1  - Philippe D.
A1  - Chevalley J.
A1  - Sergent P.
Y1  - 1966//
N2  - The description is given of 14 casee in which spontaneous mixed androgenic smears were found in young women suffering from luteal insufficiency with and without a rise of 17-ketosteroids. The cytologie findings revealed that the number of hyperplastic inter mediary cells (only androgenic cells were taken into consideration) allows the recognition, in graphs, of a 'mirror image' between the curve of the intermediary cells and that of the acidophilic and pyknotic cells, which suggests a cyclical variation of the androgenic activity of the ovary and that cytolysis was quasi constant in the smears. This is followed by a discussion of the hype randrogenic value pf this sign. The significance of these androgenic smears is discussed from the endocrinologie point of view and the question is raised whether they can be considered as very sensitive criteria of vaginal changes which are produced by ovarian and suprarenal hyperandrogeny. A therapeutic trial with dexamethasone has shown a parallelism between cytologie and clinical improvement.
