A1  - Green J.A.
A1  - Goldzieher J.W.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - The authors investigated 47 polycystic ovaries and found in all cases a thickening of the tunica albuginea. This thickening is the consequence of a fibroblastic process possibly due to a high local concentration of androgens. The increase in the number of atretic follicles is attributed to an altered biosynthesis of steroids. Hyperthecosis was not encountered.
