A1  - Giglio F.A.
A1  - Stewart J.P.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Five anovulatory patients were studied in regard to plasma elevation and urinary excretion of 17-OHCS and urinary excretion of 17-KS and FSH. The urinary 17-OHCS and 17-KS were not detectably changed by oxytocin stimulation. In 3 patients the plasma values for 17-OHCS were slightly higher than expected, although in normal range. No conclusions can be drawn from these data. The 24-hr urinary excretion of Na. K. and Cl were also recorded. There appears to be no appreciable change. There is an antidiuretic response to oxytocin, in 4-hr urinary output, but the 24-hr urine volumes did not vary significantly from the pretreatment values.
