T3  - Beitrag zum Wirkungsmechanismus der oralen Ovulationshemmer beim Menschen
A1  - Mau-HaefeIi M.
A1  - Ludwig K.S.
A1  - Keller M.
A1  - Cioeren S.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Six patiente who received ovulation inhibitors (2-12 cycles) were examined morphologically, endocrine Logically and histologically. At laparatomy, corpora lutea in different stages of development were found. The question was discussed whether they were persistent corpora lutea or if they developed under the treatment of ovulation inhibitors. Macroscopic description is presented of the changes in the ovaries according to the duration of the treatment. It was noted that the uterus became softer and larger. The histologie examination proved the theca interna to become hypoplastic, probably due to inadequate gonadotropic stimulation, leading to functionally defective corpora lutea. The ovum is probably not ripe for fertilization at that stage. Prolonged treatment with ovulation inhibitors leads to a diminution of the large follicles. The ovaries acquire a white juvenile appearance. After cessation of treatment a delayed ripening of the ovum and prolonged cycles are to be expected which might become ovulatory or anovulatory.
