N2  - Report oa and analysis of SA ovarian tumor made up of various structures; e.g., in addition to nonspecific associations of epithelium, the ovarian neoplasm was seen to contain nonkeratinizing and keratinizing islands of columnar epithelium, mucinous and serous glandular structures and. not in the least, formations resembling the mucous membrane of the fallopian tubes. The inference drawn is that, in the ultimate, the various structures of the tumor must simply be various trends of differentiation deriving from a common tumor germ which was generated from embryonal or postnatal derivatives of the paramesonephriccoelomic epithelium. This case suggests that the benign and malignant forms of Brenner tumors, as, indeed, also benign and malignant mucinous, serous and seromucinous ovarian neoplasms of a solid or cystic nature must represent a common species of tumor which could be denoted as tumors with the potentialities of the paramesonephric coelomi cervical mucus), a study was made of 24 patient, (8 of them presenting hormonal alteration, and sterility with estrogenic insufficiency; 5 with anovularity with slight estrogenic insufficiency and with luteinic insufficiency and 12 with sterility or mild gynecologic disorders with normal estroluteinic activity) who were observed in the Clinic of Obstetrics and Gynecology of the University of Rome. In precise accordance with aie theoretical data, these investigations constantly revealed the presence of 0-giucuronidaee activity in the cervical mucus, as well as a correlation between the 0-glucuronidase activity and the estrogen contents of the urine.
