N2  - A case of Stein-Leventhal syndrome in a child aged 13 is presented. The 1st symptoms appeared at the age of 11. Regular menstrual cycles followed wedge resection of the ovary. Histological alterations of the ovaries were characteristic. Before and immediately after surgery there was a significant increase of a-fractions indicating increased dehydroepiandrosterone secretion, besides normal ketosteroid. Following appearance of the menstrual cycles the ratio of 17-ketosteroid fractions became normal.
