T1  - Excretion of steroids and gonadotropins in the human anovulatory cycle
T3  - Die Ausscheidung von Steroiden und Gonadotropinen im anovulatorischen Cyclus der Frau
A1  - Hammerstein J.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - In 7 patients 8 anovulatory cycles were examined in various phases of sexual maturity. The following methods were used: urinary estrogen excretion, pregnandiol, 17-ketosteroids, 17-hydroxysteroids, in most cases also gonadotropins, basal temperature, curettage. fern test, viscosity, and colpocytologic smears. A description is given of 3 types of anovulatory cycles. Type A: increase of the estrogen excretion 7-10 days before menstruation, with a rapid decrease 1-2 days before menstruation. Type B: maximum estrogen excretion approximately halfway the cycle, with absence of the luteal phase. Bleeding begins some days after the estrogen excretion is reduced. Type C: low estrogen excretion during the entire cycle. The cornification curves approximately correspond to types A. B and C. The pregnandiol in the 24-hour urine was below the quantitative threshold of sensitivity of the method. High values were only found in a premenopausal patient.
