N2  - A description of 2 patients; 1 had received Anovlar for 13 cycles, the other for 27. During the last anovulatory cycle and the next cycle (when no treatment was given) the following studies were made: measurement of the basal temperature, determination of the pregnandiol in the 24-hour urine, determination of total excreted estrogens, gonadotropins and hydroxycorticoids and 17-ketosteroids in the 24-hour urine. The 1st cycle after protracted anovulatory treatment is usually longer, ovulation can cccur in the 1st cycle after discontinuance of treatment, but it is usually delayed. This 1st cycle may also be monophasic. The hydrocorticoids and 17-ketosteroids may be reduced to the lower normal limit. After 9 or at most 12 m th., treatment should be suspended until a biphasic cycle can be shown.
