T1  - Environmental menstrual disorders
A1  - Matsumoto S.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Among telephone operators, instances of a normal menstrual cycle decreased while cases of oligomenorrhea increased. The latter, however, recovered after 10-13 mth.,In many student nurses menstrual change occurred immediately after admission into the school, and during 7 mth. thereafter the basal body temperature indicated luteal insufficiency or anovulatory cycles in the majority of them, and normal ovulatory cycles in a small number. In about 40% of delinquent girls, menstrual change was elicited after confinement in a reformatory. Rorschach's test revealed that those having changes showed near-normal personality. Out of patients operated at the follicular phase, about 2/3 noted a change in the menstrual cycle and 90% developed an anovulatory cycle, whereas after operation at the luteal phase scarcely any showed a change. Menstrual disorders resulting from various environmental changes should be regarded as a physiologic response of the living body to environmental changes.
