N2  - Reference is made to personal experience with the new drug in the field of amenorrhea. Nine cases were treated for a total of 14 cycles. One pregnancy, 1 ovulatory menstruation and 2 anovulatory menstruations were brought on. On the basis of these results and the various evaluation factors (metabolic, cytologie and clinical), it is concluded that Clomiphene should only be given to patients with normal gonadotropinuria if positive results are to be obtained. The hypothesis is then advanced that the action should be ascribed to a primary influence on the metabolism of ovarian and suprarenal estrogens.
