N2  - Following a rapid clinical and par aclinic al study of the characteristics of anovulatory cycles and a review of the poor results of former treatment the authors discuss a new method of therapy which appears to be much more promising. HMG is injected in a dosage of 20 mg daily over 10 days, associated with 1,000 IU of chorionic gonadotrophin during the last 5 days. Clomiphene is administered in daily doses of 150-200 mg during the 1st half of the cycle. There are slight side effects like hot flushes, transient visual disturbances, cutaneous rashes, and functional ovarian cysts; most of them disappear spontaneously after about 10 days. This therapy has been followed by pregnancies.
