A1  - Guhr O.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - A report on 79 personal observations of women who used anovulatory drugs and who were examined by colpoecopic, cytologie and histologie techniques to determine whether epithelial changes had occurred in the cervix during treatment. Colposcopy showed that after use for at least 4 mth atypical regions developed. These resembled leukoplakia and were mostly localized in the squamocolumnar junction. These are called 'suspect areas in statu nascendi'. Histologie and cytologie studies showed that the suspect areas had a slightly irregular epithelium or changes strongly suspect for carcinoma in situ. Among 67 women examined 2 cases of carcinoma in situ were detected. In 5 patients the diagnosis was dubious and decision between marked atypia or carcinoma in situ could not be made with certainty. The duration of contraceptive treatment, follow-up and frequency of examination are not stated. Stehouwer - The Hague (X. 5).
