N2  - Celioscopy, both transabdominal and transvaginal, is a very valuable means for the diagnosis of female endocrine alterations in general and of ovarian alterations in particular. It has little value for the diagnosis of ovulation. Conversely, celioscopy is of great importance in the diagnosis of primary amenorrheas, Turner' a syndrome, and most secondary amenorrheas. In virilism it allows the differential diagnosis between the Stein-Leventhal syndrome and other forms of ovarian and extraovarian virilism.
