T3  - Unsere Erfahrungen mit der Ovulationsauslosung durch Clomiphene
A1  - During G.K.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Clomiphene citrate was used during 3-16 cycles for treatment of 20 women with mainly anovulatory cycles. The daily dose was 50 mg until temperature increased which mostly occurred on the 17th day. Other patients received 150 mg daily for 5 days. In 15 cases a hyperthermic phase developed as a result of treatment after 8-16 days. In consequence of this variability conception was rare; only 1 woman became pregnant. Enlargement of the ovaries was never seen; in 1 case waves of hotness were noted. It is thought that the drug substitutes the natural estrogens in the diencephalon, so that the anterior pituitary is activated resulting in an increased release of gonadotropins.
