N2  - The ovulatory activity was investigated in 75 women operated on the second half of the menstrual cycle and in whom there was a certain diagnosis of ovarian endometriosis based on laparotomy findings and histologie control. Of the 75 women, 69 were married and 12 of these suffered from involuntary primary sterility. Gonadal investigation showed that of the 75 cases of ovarian endometriosiS1 the menstrual cycle was anovulatory in 42 cases, while the presence of a recent cycle was accertained in 33 cases. The relationships between ovary endometriosis, anovulatory menstrual cycle, and sterility are discussed briefly. (X, 5*).
