T3  - Biopsie ovarienne per-coelioscopique et anovulation
A1  - Thoyer-Rozat J.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Twenty-eight times, biopsy was carried out in this way, without ever giving rise to any hemorrhagic or other incidents. All the patients could leave the hospital 2-3 days after the operation. It is concluded that ovarian biopsy by the percelioscopic technique for a longer or shorter duration restores normal cycles in women with surgically curable anovulation. It is also a highly valuable therapeutic test. It gives excellent results in cases of the authentic Stein-Leventhal syndrome, indifferent results in cases in which the volume of the ovaries is normal or larger than normal, and no results in cases of ovarian insufficiency.
