T1  - NORETHYNODREL with MESTRANOL in INFERTILITY
A1  - Arrata W.S.M.
A1  - Arronet G.H.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Norethynodrel with mestranol (Enovid) was effective in regulating ovulation and consequently improving the pregnancy rate for patients in whom ovulation, although present, was irregular. Enovid was found successful in treating luteai-phase inadequacy. The pregnancy outcome was 55%, although 45.4% of these pregnancies terminated in abortions. Little success was achieved in treating anovulatory patients, most of whom had primary infertility; some beneficial effect was achieved in cases of secondary infertility. Statistical evaluation of results in the normal ovulatory group was not possible because of the size of the sample.
