T1  - ANOVULATORY EFFECT of LYNESTRENOL in COMBINATION with MESTRANOL
A1  - Knutsson F.
A1  - Rybo G.
A1  - Anberg A.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - The inhibitory effect on ovulation of 2.5 mg. lynestrenol combined with 75 y mestranol was studied in women. The following features were studied in one control cycle and one treatment cycle: basal temperature, excretion of pregnanediol in urine, arborization of the cervical secretion, careful inspection of the ovaries at laparotomy, and histologie examination of ovarian tissue and endometrium. The preparation has a thermogenic effect. The excretion of pregnanediol does not rise during the latter phase of the treatment cycle, indicating inhibition of ovulation. At laparotomy and on histologie examination of ovarian tissue no fresh corpora lutea could be found. This proves that ovulation is effectively inhibited by the preparation. Side effects were low, but in 5 of the patients a small rise of the serum transaminases GOT and/or GPT during treatment was found. (X, 3, t*).
