T1  - TREATMENT of AMENORRHEA and of ANOVULATION with HUMAN MENOPAUSAL and CHORIONIC GONADOTROPINS
A1  - Vande Wiele R.L.
A1  - Turksoy R.N.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - The authors report the experiences of treatment of amenorrhea and of anovulation with Pergonal (FSH extracted from menopausal urine) and with HCG. The treatment was started with Pergonal (4.75-18 mg. equivalents of FSH-NIH-SI daily). Follicular maturation was reached and ovulation was induced with HCG (4.000-5,000 I. U. daily). The treatment of primary amenorrhea (5 patients) was without effect. In the other patients ovulation appeared at least once and often several times. The best results were obtained in the 20 patients with primary or secondary sterility, 14 of whom conceived. The treatment was unsuccessful in cases of overstimulation of ovaries or in cases of sterility due to the husband. Vesety - Prague (X, 3).
