N2  - Resected tissues of 74 ovaries from 37 patients with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome were examined (the method is described). It was found that the theca interna, as judged from the type of fluorescence, may or may not contain lipids (hormonally active steroids). When the microscopic sections were treated with acetone or alcohol, only the fine green granules in the cytoplasm of the cells in the theca interna disappeared; the diffuse green color of the cytoplasm did not change. Fine fluorescent golden-yellow droplets were constantly observed in the periphery of the cells of the primordial follicles; these did not disappear after treatment with acetone or alcohol.
