N2  - FSH and LH activities of total urinary gonadotropin extract obtained by Johnsen ' s method have been determined from urines tested daily during 10 menstrual cycles of 5 women with normal menstruation. If we exclude the 2 cases of anovulatory cycles, in the 3 cycles of regular ovulation the excretion rate of FSH was higher during menstruation and in the days immediately following the flow with a maximum of 80-120 IRP-HMG Units, and a minimum during the middle of the cycle (11th-13th day). Two other small peaks, with a maximum of 50 IRP Units were observed on the 14th-15th day and on the 20th-21st day. The maximum increase of LH activity is 24-48 hr after the thermal shift in the vaginal basal temperature indicating ovulation. (X, 2a, 3*).
