N2  - When compared with normal adult ovaries, the ovaries from 25 women suffering from the Stein-Leventhal syndrome disclosed a quantitative difference with regard to the reaction with ferric chloride and Schiffs reagent. The histochemical differences were most evident in some areas of the theca interna and in areas undergoing hypertrophy and hyperplasia. The differences are thought to be caused by the presence of some substances related in chemical structure to the corticosteroids, their precursors, or their metabolites. Fuchs - New York, N.Y. (X, 3.5).
