A1  - Vorontsova G.M.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Seventy six women,of whom 42 had sterility in combination with some type or other of menstrual disorder, were examined clinically, with the aid of functional diagnostic tests, and by cervicoisthmohysterography. It was found that in cases with a normal ovulatory cycle the isthmic part of the uterus is dilated during the follicular stage, markedly constricted during the progestational stage, and again dilated 2 days before the onset of menstrual bleeding. Inoligomenorrhea with a normal menstrual cycle the isthmus does not dilate, while in anovulatory disorders it remains dilated throughout the cycle.
