T3  - Stimulering van de ovaria met menselijke gonadotrofinen
A1  - Aartsen E.J.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - By means of injections of human gonadotrophins, in accordance with a scheme given by Staemmler, it was tried to provoke ovulations in 27 patients suffering from amenorrhea and anovulatory oligomenorrhea. Twenty-one women with amenorrhea and 6 women with anovulatory oligomenorrhea were treated in this way. The treatment resulted 25 times in a uterine bleeding. Microscopic examination of the endoraetrium during the bleeding showed the following results: menstruating endometrium in 10 patients, irregular ripening in 7, and a proliferative endometrium in 5 patients. In 3 patients it was impossible to examine the endometrium during the bleeding. One patient became pregnant following treatment with gonadotrophins. The value of the Staemmler treatment and its indications are discussed. (X. 3).
