T1  - INITIAL CLINICALEXPERIENCESWITH 16-METHYLENE-6-DEH YDROITa- ACETOXYPROGESTERONE (MDAP)
T3  - Die ersten klinischen Erfahrungen mit 16-Methylen-6-dehydro-17a- azetoxyprogesteron (MDAP)
A1  - Sterba R.
A1  - Aa K.
A1  - Ulrych J.
A1  - Vaiova B.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - In 60 patients the authors studied the progestational, antiestrogenic, and blocking action of MDAP and its combination with ethinyl estradiol in various doses. The drug showed high progestational activity, and low antiestrogenic and antiovulation activity, so that for contraceptive purposes it only supplements the antiovulation activity of the estrogens and helps the substitution cycle in the endometrium. The high progestational activity of the drug makes possible the use, for blocking pituitary gonadotrophins, of a combination of fairly high doses of estrogens and a relatively low dose of MDAP. The new oral progestogen has no androgenic effects and may therefore be used in cases of imminent and habitual abortion at the time of development of the placenta, for temporary substitution of endogenous progesterone lack, and in all types of defective corpus luteum function, namely in asecretory cycles with hyperestrogenic amenorrhea and subsequent anovulatory bleeding. For the actual treatment of functional bleeding and for antiovulation purposes estrogens must be added to the preparation. The most effective ratio found was about 0.075 mg. ethinyl estradiol and 5 mg. MDAP; experience shows that the doses of ethinyl estradiol may be raised to 0.1 mg. per 5 mg. MDAP. This mixture is also useful for therapy of functional sterility by the rebound effect, for therapy of endometriosis, dysmenorrhea, acne, and premenstrual tension, i.e. functional disorders caused by poor hormonal balance, and also for therapy of mammary hypoplasia owing to the trophic effect of both hormones on the tubo-alveolar structure of the breast.
