T3  - Les aspecte endocriniens de la metropathie preme nopaueique
A1  - Ingiulla W.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - In 50 cases of premenopausal disturbance the level of ovarian, adrenal and pituitary hormones was followed in correlation with colpocytology, crystallization test, basal body temperature and biopsy. In fact, 4 different situations occur: (1) Biphasic cycle with normal estrogen and low progesterone level; (2) low progesterone level and hype rest rogenism occurring with an image of irregular ripening; (3) true anovulatory cycles with low pregnanediol and high estrogen levels; (4) anovulatory cycles with low estrogen and progesterone levels. It may be concluded that preclimacteric metropathy is bound with a pathologic corpus lute urn with various biologic expressions.
