T3  - Biosynthese van steroiden en het Stein-Leventhalsyndroom
A1  - Van Der Molen H.J.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - A review is given of the facts known about the biosynthesis of steroids in relation to the syndrome of Stein-Leventhal. Special attention is paid to the merits of the techniques used for the development of our understanding of the problems involved. Defects in enzyme systems, that are suggested to exist in patients with this syndrome are discussed. Various possibilities for the site of location of these defects (a. o. adrenal and ovary) and the possibilities to differentiate between these sites are reviewed.
