N2  - FSH, LH, and estrogen fractions for est r one, estradiol, and estriol values were determined in urine during normal menstrual cycles and in 4 anovulatory patients during clomiphene therapy. FSH levels rose in all cases during or immediately following this therapy. LH did not rise prior to a rise in estrogens. Estrogen fractions were determined using thin-layer adsorption chromatography as a final purification step before Kobe r ' s color development. The estradiol fraction contained at least 3 estrogen components. During clomiphene therapy the estradiol fraction fell. It was postulated that this fall occurred in the estrogen components other than estradiol. The identity of these estrogen components is unknown, but 2 possibilities are suggested. The role of the reported fall in estrogen in the mechanism of action of clomlphene is discussed.
