N2  - A 27-year-old nulligravida with 4 yr amenorrhea following emotional disturbance had 1 anovulatory period after 2 yr amenorrhea, and then several episodes of drug induced withdrawal bleeding. PBI 4.8 /ig%, skull X-ray normal, endometrial biopsy: proliferatlve endometrium. History negative. Wt 85 pounds, height 58 inchess Pelvis normal. 17-KS 11.5. 17-KGS 12, FSH positive 'at 10, but negative at 50 units'. CIomiphene on 3 occasions produced Diphasic temperature followed by abnormal menses, and succeeded by recurrent amenorrhea. In January, 1963 Personal (25-E38-B, Inst. Farm. Serono) was ineffective. One month later, human chorionlc gonadotropln was also ineffective. She was then given a 2-week course of pergonal with chorionic gonadotropin the last 5 days. Ovulation (BBT) occurred On the 2nd or 3rd day of this treatment', and pregnancy was confirmed 4 weeks later. Because of bleeding and rapid growth, mole was considered, but ruled out by sequential gonadotropin determinations. Quadruplets were diagnosed by X-ray 19 wk following ovulation. Determinations of urinary estriol, estradiol, estrone, pregnanediol and pregnanetriol were in the normal range for a single pregnancy. Labor at 34 wk was ineffective although stimulated and delivery was by cesarean section. The placenta weighed 970 g and was quadramniotic and quadrichorionic. Infante and their blood types: The mother and infants survived, and are in normal health. The authors briefly review concepts involved in the use of these new and powerful therapeutic agents.
