N2  - By means of injections of human gonadotropins, in accordance with a scheme given by Staemmler, the author tried to provoke ovulations in 21 women with amenorrhea and 6 women with anovulatory oligomenorrhea. The treatment resulted 25 times in a uterine bleeding. Microscopic examination of the end omet r him during the bleeding showed the following results: menstruating endometrium in 10 patients, irregular ripening in 7, and a proliferative endometrium in 5 patients. In 3 patients it was impossible to examine the endometrium during the bleeding. One patient became pregnant following treatment with gonadotropins. The value of Staemmler's treatment and its indications are discussed.
