N2  - The authors examined repeated biopsy specimens from the ovaries of 7 women suffering from Stein-Leventhal syndrome, who had had bilateral ovarian resection. In the majority of cases they found at the site of operation, where the thickened fibrous capsule had been interrupted, primordial follicles, non-atretic follicles and remnants of corpora lutea. Thus the mechanical etiology of the syndrome appears to be proven. In some cases the ovaries had again undergone cystic degeneration and showed no sign of cyclic function.
