T1  - Causes of error in the diagnosis of the anovulatory cycle based on biopsy of the endometrium
T3  - Causas de error en el diagnostico del ciclo anovulador por la biopsia de endometrio
A1  - Marquez Ramirez M.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - A study was made of the endometrium of 500 sterile women, of whom other important anamnestic and laboratory data, including the basal temperature, had also been carefully collected. The biopsy of the endometrium was carried out in the premenstrual phase; in some of the cases the author also performed Gomori staining (alkaline phosphatase) and the PAS test (mucopolysaccharides). In all. 8.6% anovulatory cycles were found, which figure is in agreement with the findings of other authors. The causes of error, which are frequently found in the assessments of authors who report higher proportions (11 to 13%). may be: (1) connected with the moment of the taking of the biopsy sample, hence the necessity of performing this examination at a suitable moment, and if necessary taking more samples than one; (2) connected with the interpretation of the histological image, hence the suggestion of using suitable staining methods for the determination of glycogen.
