T1  - First results in the treatment of anovular sterility with clomiphene citrate
T3  - Risultati preliminari sul trattamento della sterilita anovulare col citrato di clomifene
A1  - Migliavacca A.
A1  - Chiara A.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Four cases of sterility, proved to be due to missed ovulation, were treated with clomiphene citrate in a dose of 50 mg per day for periods of 5 to 11 days per cycle. In 3 cases it could be ascertained that the patients took the drug as prescribed, but in the case of the 4th patient there was some doubt about this. In one patient, who had been sterile for 8 yr, a pregnancy was diagnosed after 2 courses of the treatment (50 mg per day for 5 days). Gynecological exploration revealed the presence of 2 cystic ovaries; the cystic degeneration had occurred in the course of the treatment, but was only of moderate degree. In a second case the clomiphene was administered during 5 cycles, in a dose of 50 mg per day for 9 days, viz. from the 5th to the 14th day of the cycle. During the 5th course of the treatment the patient became pregnant. During the first 2 mth of the treatment, the administration of the drug caused flushes, but this effect regressed spontaneously. In the 3rd case, the clomiphene was administered during 4 cycles to a woman who was sterile and amenorrheic. The dose amounted to 50 mg per day, from the 9th to the 13th day of the cycle. The treatment had then to be interrupted because the drug could no longer be procured. In the course of the treatment, the menstrual cycle had returned to normal, but no pregnancy had occurred; after the end of the treatment the patient's menstrual cycle once more presented the same characteristics as prior to the treatment with clomiphene; at the time of writing, the patient was amenorrheic and not pregnant. The drug was also administered to a patient who suffered from post-partum amenorrhea, and who had previously been treated, without success, with hormonal preparations and with parasympathico-mimetic drugs. Menstruation appeared again after a single course of the treatment (50 mg per day for 11 days).
