T1  - Excretion of estrogenic hormones in some forms of dysfunctional uterine hemorrhage
A1  - Dobrotina A.F.
A1  - Zagryadskaya L.P.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Total excretion of estrogens in patients with juvenile hemorrhage was fairly constant, without ovulatory and luteinic peaks. The total output of estrogens averaged 12.4 mug. This type of excretion of estrogen pointed to an anovulatory type of hemorrhage in young females. Patients of childbearing or menopausal age could he divided into 2 groups according to the amount of estrogen excreted in the urine: (1) those with constant excretion of estrogens not exceeding 30 mug.; and (2) those excreting estrogens in varying amounts or in excess of 30 mug. The latter 2 types of estrogen excretion predisposed to glandulocystic hyperplasia of the endometrium. There was no essential difference in the ratio of the active and inactive fractions of estrogens in juvenile patients or in patients of childbearing age with dysfunctional uterine hemorrhage; this ratio was 1:1 in juvenile and 1:2 in childhearing years. Excretion of the active fraction of estrogens in patients with hemorrhage decreased in the climacteric age while the excretion of estriol increased, in contradistinction to the 2 preceding age groups. Excretion of pregnanediol in the urine was constant and its quantity did not exceed 1 mug., with an average of 469 mug., which confirmed the anovulatory character of the hemorrhage in the investigated patients.
