T1  - Effect of prednisone on female infertility
A1  - Perloff W.H.
A1  - Smith K.D.
A1  - Steinberger E.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Prednisone was used to treat 153 infertile patients, 46 with Stein-Leventhal ovaries and 107 with follicular cysts of the ovaries. Approximately 40% of the former conceived after an average period of 11 mth., and approximately 50% of the latter became pregnant after an average duration of approximately 5 mth. Approximately 85% of patients showed improvement in menstrual function. The total average dose of prednisone required to improve menstruation and ovulation and to induce conception was higher in patients with Stein-Leventhal ovaries than in patients with follicular cysts of the ovaries, and the average time required was longer. The percentage of patients who conceived with prednisone compared favorably with results reported by others after wedge resection of the ovaries. It is suggested that patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome be treated with prednisone for a minimum of a year, and that subjects with follicular cysts of the ovaries be treated for a minimum of 6 mth., before wedge resection of the ovaries is recommended.
