T1  - Elimination of urinary steroids and gonadotropins after treatment with clomiphene
T3  - L'eliminazione delle gonadotropine e degli steroidi urinari dopo somministrazione di clomifene
A1  - Valente D.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Hormonal determinations, including total gonadotropins, estrogens, pregnandiol, 17-ketosteroids and 17-ketogenic steroids, have been performed on the urines of 13 women suffering from amenorrhea or anovulatory menstrual cycles, before and after treatment with clomiphene. In all, 22 menstrual cycles have been controlled weekly, with a total of 774 hormonal estimations. An increase of urinary gonadotropins was recorded in 91% of the clomiphe ne-treated cases; ovulation ensued in 73% of the cases, as shown by the increase of estrogens and pregnandiol. In a few cases the urinary excretion of 17-ketosteroids and 17-ketogenic steroids was influenced by the clomiphene treatment. (10,2a, 2c*).
