T1  - Use of clomiphene to induce ovulation in womam
T3  - Il clomiphene nelT induzione dell' ovulazione ne Ua donna -
A1  - Andreoli C.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - The ovulatory action of Clomid (Clomiphene Citrate) was investigated in a group of 55 women which comprised 5 cases of menarchal metrorrhagia. 30 cases of functional uterine bleeding associated with an anovulatory cycle, 2 cases of primary amenorrhea, 8 cases of secondary amenorrhea, 2 cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome and 8 experimental cases. A positive result was obtained in 27 cases, with 5 pregnancies. Positive results were obtained most often in cases of menstrual anomalies associated with a hyperhormonal gonadal picture, whereas the response in hypohormonal cases was practically nil. A positive response was obtained most often in patients who suffered from hot flushes and gonadal pain during Clomid administration. Clomid had no effect on the ovary during the menopause and was clinically ineffective in cases of ovarian hypoplasia and in women with ovaroprival symptoms. (10.3,21*).
