A1  - Chalmers J.A.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Of 11 cases of Stein-Levcnthal syndrome treated at Worcester since 1959, culdoscopy had aided in the diagnosis of 5 and gynecography in that of 1. Two were recognized at cesarean section. Wedge resection of the ovaries was carried out in all but 1 patients, who has so far refused operation. Associated der moid cysts were found in 2 cases. Regular menstruation was established in 8 out of 10 cases although 1 relapsed after 9 months. Successful pregnancy occurred in 5 cases. Induzione ormonale delia ovulazione - Debiasi E., and Cagnazzo G. Clin. Ostct. e Ginecol. , Univ. di Genova - MONIT. OSTET. - GINEC. ENDOCRINOL-. METABOL,. 1966, 37/2 (135-191) After an outline of the importance, from a social and human point of view, of sterility, of which anovulation seems to be 1 of the most frequent causes, an examination was made of the nature and the effective value of the hormonal tools capable of provoking ovulation and therefore of correcting sterility due to ano vulation. The literature often gives conflicting data. Results from personal experience are shown in relation to the ovulatory action of estrogens, progesterone, synthetic progestational steroids, estroprogestinic compounds, cortisone, thyroid hormone, gonaHotropins (PMS, APG. HP-FSH, HCG, HMG). (10.3,21*).
