T1  - The cervical factor in relation to the ovarian cycle
T3  - El factor cervical en relacion con el ciclo ovarico
A1  - Hierro Alberich P.
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - From 750 protocols of the outpatient department of infertility, the author has selected 55 case records with completely normal sperm. The women, according to their ovarian function, were classified into ovulatory and permanently or alternately anovulatory cases. On applying the Huehner-Sims test in both groups it was seen that ovulatory cases gave a favorable result in 19.56% of cases, and anovulatory cases in 42.85% of cases. In the group of patients with a biphasic cycle, pregnancy occurred in 14.58% and in the other group in 28.57%. Sustained estrogen activity during the entire cycle is perhaps a condition that favors the spermatic ascension test.
