N2  - Two sisters with Stein-Leventhal syndrome are described; the diagnosis was established both clinically and surgically. A 3rd sister presented with possibly the same syndrome but she was not explored surgically. The patients had marked body hair, menstrual disorders, sterility and masculinised ovaries ; the sex chromatin was positive. The cases reported may be added to the extremely few instances of familial Stein-Leventhal syndrome, which suggest that inherited factors might be one of the aetiological agents.
