T1  - USE of BENZODIAZEPINE DERIVATIVES in GYNAECOLOGY - Empleo de los derivados de la benzodiazepina en ginecologia
A1  - Orenego F.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - A study was made of the benzodiazepine derivatives librium and valium in gynaecological practice, and also of Lib rax, which is a combination of librium with clidinium bromide. In total>> 155 cases were studied. In the first place the effect on ovulation was investigated. In 93.3% of the cases an ovulatory cycle was demonstrated which coincided with the treatment, whereas in 6.6% an anovulatory cycle occurred. The relaxing effect on the musculature (and also the psychotropic effect) of these drugs was especially manifest in the treatment of vaginismus, with 93.3% of good results, and in a less degree in dysmenorrhoea (75% of successes; 3.3% of improvements and 21.6% of failures). It also appeared to be useful in the preparation for tubal insufflation and hysterosalpingography. Finally, good results were obtained in the treatment of some symptoms that were genital in appearance (non-existent foetid leucorrhoea, feeling of guilt in cases of sterility), but which, actually, were of psychiatric origin. The tolerance was excellent in all the cases. It is to be hoped that these drugs may find a frequent use in gynaecology.
