N2  - Among I,?b2 women treated for sterility, 177 cases of anovulatory cycle were found. The diagnosis was established by endometriai biopsy obtained in the preor intramenstrual phase, by study of the crystallization of the cervical mucus and basal temperature. Correction of the anovulatory cycle, rendering it biphasic, was obtained with the following drugs: in 34 cases with thyroid gland (61%), in 40 with estrogens (72.2%); in 20 with gestagens (80%); in 20, with estrogens and gestagens (80%); in 14, with corticoids (35%); in 15 with hydrazides, streptomycin and estrogens (80%); in 8. with irradiation using Kaplan's technique (62%); in 5, with wedgeshaped ovarian resection (80%); in 3, with unilateral adnexectomy (100% of corrections). Twenty-one cases of pregnancy with viable fetuses and 1 abortion were obtained, i.e. pregnancies in 12.4% of the monophasic cycles treated.
