T1  - Induction of ovulation by 'clomiphene. experiments in man
T3  - Declenchement de l'ovulation par le clomiphene (MRL-41). Essai chez l'homme
A1  - Bret A.-J.
A1  - Coiffard P.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - The drug was given to 14 women and 2 men, in all cases for sterility. Three women had amenorrhea, 10 had anomalies in the menstrual pattern responsible for sterility. In one patient no cause was found. Both men had oligospermia. The women were divided into a group of 9 patients in which treatment did not lead to pregnancy, and 5 in which it was successful. Clinical data, are given on all patients. Except for one case the drug caused distinct changes in the basal temperature curve. It was found that the temperature remains constant for some time after discontinuance of treatment and this leads to the conclusion that the thermogenic effect is a progestational one. In general a distinct progesterone effect was seen in the endometrium, even including decidual reactions. The excretion of pregnandiol and estrogens mostly increased markedly. In some cases ps eu do -pregnancy was seen, ovarian cysts were sometimes found. It is pointed out that pregnancy is the only absolute proof of a previous ovulation, but nevertheless the analysis led the authors to the conclusion that ovulation also occurred in the patients thai did not become pregnant. It is not certain whether the drug acts via the hypophysis or the ovary. In ovarian atrophy or at high FSH levels (menopause) results ma_y not be expected. In one of the 2 patients with oligospermia improvement in spermatogenesis was seen.
