N2  - A case is described in which a woman with a previous history of a pituitary chromophobe adenoma subsequently developed persistent lactation and dysmenorrhoea. Abnormally high levels of oestrogen excretion were found to be associated with cystic ovaries and uterine fib r omis. Steroid concentrations in the ovarian cyst fluid are presented, together with hormone excretion data for periods previous and subsequent to hysterectomy and bilateral salpingo- oophorectomy.
