N2  - The authors have added 2 cases of torsion of normal adnexa to the literature. In addition, they have discussed the aetiologic factors involved and the clinical picture presented by this accident. In evaluating the so-called 'normal* adnexa, the authors must, because of the very nature of the tissues concerned, become involved in controversial anatomical considerations. Undoubtedly, many torsions of so-called diseased adnexa are, in fact, due to twisting of physiologic cystic ovaries. As others have noted, it is often impossible to be precise regarding the histological nature of the cystic process after infarction and degeneration have taken D!ace.
