A1  - Mohr U.
A1  - Kaiser R.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - A primipara with late toxaemia and severe liver and kidney lesion died in collapse on the second day after the delivery of a macerated child. The post-mortem examination revealed bilateral, baby-head-sized cystic ovaries with rupture of a larger cyst and haemorrhage into the free peritoneal cavity. Furthermore, a severe liver dystrophy and a glomerulo-tubular nephrosis were found. The development of the large cystic ovaries can be explained with an iver stimulation by chorionic gonadotrophin consequent to the toxaemia.
