T1  - ANTHROPOMETRIC INVESTIGATIONS on THE INTERRELATION between STRUCTURE of the BODY and THE FUNCTION of the OVARIES
T3  - Anthropometrische Untersuchungen uber die Beziehungen zwischen Korperbau und Ovarialfunktion
A1  - Staemmler H.-J.
A1  - Sachs L.
A1  - Brehm H.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Somatometric studies on 89 patients with ovarian insufficiency of different origin were made, The reSults are compared with those from a group of 140 healthy women. The patients were divided into 3 groups according to the stature. The statistical analysis of the value shows the following tendencies: 64 women with hypothalamic insufficiency had an abnormally broad trunk. The percentage of the breadth of pelvis to that of shoulder (acromio- cristal index) is doubtlessly smaller (p < 0.025) in the 3 groups. Some remarkable differences in the absolute and relative breadth of shoulder and pelvis could be found, but not with all 3 groups. In contrast to the normal women 11 patients with postpartum ovarian insufficiency, having had a normal cycle before pregnancy, showed no deviations. 10 women with polycystic ovaries had a longer trunk (p < 0.05), a less relative length of the leg (p < 0.05) and a significantly smaller acromio- cristal index (p < 0.0025) as its outstanding features in contrast to the normal group. 4 patients with gonadal dysgenesis were much smaller (x<< 14 7.40 cm, p< 0.0025) than 23 normal women of group I. Comparing the length of the leg of the 4 women with those of the nunnal group there is a significant difference (p< 0.001). From this investigation it is concluded that already during the time of the puberal growth period the centralnervous derangements of regulations and/or aberrant production of steroid hormones are existent and exercise their influence.
