T3  - Correccion del ciclo anovulador
A1  - Xandri Oliveras R.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Among 1,782 women treated for sterility, 177 cases of anovulatory cycle were found. The diagnosis was established by endometrial biopsy obtained in the pre- or intra-menstrual phase, by study of the crystallization of the cervical mucus and basal temperature. Correction of the anovulatory cycle by rendering it biphasic, was obtained with the following drugs: in 34 cases with thyroid gland (61% of corrections), in 40 with estrogens (72.2% of corrections); in 20 with gestagens (80% of corrections); in 20, with estrogens and gestagens (80% of corrections); in 14 with corticoide (35% of corrections); in 15 with hydrazides, streptomycin and estrogens (80% of corrections); in 8 with irradiation using Kaplan's technique (62% of corrections); in 5 with wedge-shaped ovarian resection (80% of corrections); in 3 with unilateral adnexectomy (100% of corrections). Twenty-one cases of pregnancy with viable fetuses and 1 abortion were obtained, i.e. pregnancies in 12.4% of the monophasic cycles treated.
