T1  - The Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster syndrome
T3  - Het syndroom van Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster
A1  - Weeke A.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Description of a 21-year-old woman with normal female development, suffering from a primary amenorrhea. The vagina was absent and rectal examination revealed in the broad ligaments a separate mass (diameter about 1.5-2cm.) at the right and the left of the pelvis. No uterus was palpable. The same applied to the ovaries. Chromosomal abnormalities were not present. At laparotomy the cystic ovaries were situated very high, near the under pole of the kidneys. The 2 masses in the broad ligaments consisted microscopically of normal uterine smooth muscle. The vagina was represented as a fibrous band. So she had a uterus bipartitus rudimentarius solidus cum vagina solida or the syndrome of Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster.
