N2  - The author extols the diagnostic virtues of pneumopelvigraphy, he reports his experience with 110 patients. The procedure has clarified the diagnosis in fibromyoma, uterine displacements, uterine anomalies, ovarian cysts, Stein-Leventhal syndrome, gonadal agenesis. Under Fluothane anesthesia a needle is passed to the peritoneal cavity and CO<ovid:inf>2</ovid:inf> is run slowly until the pressure is 100 mm. H<ovid:inf>2</ovid:inf>O. The patient is placed prone after instilling the gas and on a 450degree angle, head down. The exposure is made in this position. Contraindications are few: pelvic inflammatory disease, severe cardiac or pulmonary disease. The dangers are minimal: bowel injury, peritonitis; but these are exceedingly rare.
