N2  - Twenty-one patients presenting the Stein-Leventhal syndrome were treated with injection of Neolutin (17-hydroxy progesterone capronate) and with tablets of 16-methylene-6-dehydro-17alpha-acetoxy progesterone (M. D. A. P.). Recovery ensued in 52% of these cases. Two patients became pregnant. The authors advise that the treatment be started with drugs; M. D. A. P. in smaller doses has proved to be efficacious. In resistant cases, wedge excision of the ovaries is indicated, followed by hormone treatment. The efficacy of the preparations can be proved by laboratory tests (17-ketosteroids, 17-ketogenic steroids, pregnanediol).
