T1  - Gonadocortical dysgenesia (conclusion)
T3  - Disgenesias gonadocorticais (conclusao)
A1  - Vespasiano Ramos A.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - After a brief review of the embryogenesis of the ovary and the sexual determination and differentiation the author describes a syndrome that has been seen by him. He presents its etiology, diagnosis and treatment. In the second part of the work, he concludes that the term 'gonadocortical dysgenesia' defines the malformation of the ovary and embraces logically all ovarian conditions - congenital and primitive - whose origins are to be found at the time of differentiation of the primitive gonad by chromosomic error or by the noxious effect of known and unknown agents whether maternal or fetal. The syndrome gathers the cases of ovarian agenesis, hypoplasia and hyperplasia (including several tumors), polycystic ovaries and Turner's syndrome and includes a variegated symptomatology.
