T1  - Chromosome aberrations and anomalies of sexual development
T3  - Aberrations chromosomiques et anomalies du developpement sexuel
A1  - De Grouchy J.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - This is a compilation of many personal case histories previously published. Different modes and results of meiotic and mitotic accidents are discussed, with the resultant clinical syndromes. These include: (1) Turner's syndrome sensustricto (XO); (2) Turner with XX supposed to have arisen by a recessive inheritance, and Turner with XY; (3) Turner with mosaicism; (4) Triplo X; (5) XXXX; (6) Stein-Leventhal in three cases, one with a deletion of the long arm of an X-chromosome, one with the same deletion in a mosaic with normal X-chromosomes, and one with a mosaic XX/XXX; (7) Klinefelter's syndrome (XXY) with its variants; (8) True hermaphroditism with XX, with mosaicism, or with an XY which, according to the haptoglobins, had supposedly arisen by double fertilization; (9) Pseudohermaphroditism, including males with XY, XO/XY, and other mosaics, and females with XX. The characteristics of the Barr-bodies are further discussed.
