T1  - Problems in female sterility and its treatment
T3  - Probleme der sterilitat der frau und ihre behandlung
A1  - Lork E.C.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - This article, briefly deals with current questions of sterility and gives a summary review of the principal diagnostic and therapeutic measures. Production by the woman of antibodies against the sperm is a new unsolved problem. Psychogenic factors are gaining importance. Treatment is mostly on an empirical basis. Formerly a 2-year-limit was considered necessary for diagnosis, but this is not justified and it constitutes a loss of time, since the fertility of a woman rapidly decreases with age and with the duration of marriage. Examination of the husband is briefly mentioned. As regards female fertility the importance and value of the basal temperature curve is mentioned. In special cases, for instance suspected anovulatory cycles (which are rare), vaginal smears, endometrial biopsies and examination of the cervical mucus are also required. Diagnosis of a tendency to maldevelopment of the ovum is difficult; application of large doses of vitamin E for several months is often favourable in this respect. Plastic surgery for tubal changes has little chance of success (salpingolysis is somewhat better than implantation) and therefore conservative measures are recommended (pertubation, hormonal therapy, short-waves and mud baths). After tb of the genital tract, pregnancy is not impossible, but it should not be permitted earlier than 2 yr. after recovery. Artificial insemination is not thought valuable.
