N2  - Amenorrhea can be divided into primary amenorrhea, secondary amenorrhea and uterine amenorrhea by gestagen (progesterone) and estrogen tests. Secondary amenorrhea can be further subdivided into 8 types by various endocrinological tests. A scheme for analytical differential diagnosis and treatment of each type are given. Other menstrual disorders can be divided further by basal temperature charts and other tests into habitual anovulatory cycle.
