N2  - The author presents 5 cases who had an operation with subsequent pregnancy in 3. Correct diagnosis is essential for good response to treatment. In Cushing's syndrome there is always elevation of 17-ketosteroids either spontaneous or induced by ACTH. In the diffuse luteinization syndrome of Geist and Gaines there is both elevation of 17-ketosteroids and progesterone. In the syndrome of androgenic amenorrhea of Bret and Bardiaux there is a definite increase in the 17-ketosteroids. In the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, beside manifest enlargement of the ovaries it is characteristic that no variation occurs in 17-ketosteroid excretion after cortisone or ACTH administration but a definite increase occurs after chorionic gonadotropin.
