T1  - Menstrual dysfunctions in obese women. Aetiopathogenetic and therapeutic features
T3  - Sul deficit mestruale nelle donne obese. Considerazioni etiopatogenetiche e terapeutiche
A1  - Andreoli C.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Menstrual dysfunctions, especially anovulatory cycles, are present in a high proportion of obese women. The best results in the treatment of this condition are obtainable by reducing the body weight by a period of fasting (total fasting for 10 to 15 days, followed by one day of fasting every week), rather than by hormone treatment. With this dietary treatment, the menstrual function can be restored in a high proportion of cases, with the appearance of ovulatory cycles. The hypothesis is suggested that the menstrual dysfunctions in obese women may be due to an alteration of the metabolism of the ovarian steroid hormones.
