T1  - Human hypophyseal gonadotropin (HHG) and its clinical effects
A1  - Bettendorf G.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - The extraction of human pituitaries by a simple procedure resulted in a high active gonadotropin preparation. Treatment of patients with hypogonadotropic amenorrhea by HHG led to a marked increase of gonadal function. On the basis of the following changes - vaginal smear, endometrium, basal body temperature, estrogen, and pregnanediol excretion - it can be assumed, that ovulation was induced by the administration of HHG alone. No side reactions were observed and no poly cystic enlargement of the ovaries occurred. The possibility that the different ratio of FSH to LH is responsible for these effects is discussed. No effects were observed with HMG preparations given in the same dosage as HHG.
