N2  - The idiogram of patients with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome is identical with the normal female chromosomal formula 46/XX. No deviations even in autosomes were found in the women investigated by the authors. According to their experience, any hematological laboratory with standard equipment is suited for the determination of idiograms by studies of short-term culture of bone marrow. However this type of work is very time consuming. Determination of sex-chromatin and idiogram are recommended in women with obscure menstrual disorders, particularly in women with primary and secondary amenorrhea of undetermined etiology. Determination of the idiogram assists in establishing an accurate diagnosis.
