N2  - The authors investigated a series of 300 females suffering from disorders of the menstrual cycle by means of the intradermal test with toxoplasmin. Disturbances of regulation on the level of the diencephalon-pituitary were present in 188 women, primary ovarian impairment in 29, the Stein-Leventhal syndrome in 23 and other disorders in 60 women. It was established that the incidence of these disorders is not more frequent in women with a positive test and that the incidence of positive tests in the disorders studied does not differ significantly. Not even the overall incidence of positive tests in the series (37 +/- 2.7%) did not apparently differ from the incidence in a series of normal women.
