Y1  - 1964//
N2  - The results of investigations in a aeries of 525 married couples are analyzed. By reference to the main clinical features and to the results of endocrinological investigations the following main groups were singled out: (1) primary ovarian lesions; (2) endocrine disturbances of pituitary origin; (3) endocrine disorders of adrenal origin; (4) ovarian disorders secondary to thyroid disease; (5) anovulatory cycles or relative functional insufficiency of the corpus luteum (secondary ovarian die-function due to vitamin C deficiency, inflammatory or congestive pelvic disorders etc.i.
