T1  - Diagnostic ovarian stimulation with heterologous gonadotrophin
A1  - Shearman R.P.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Using heterologous serum gonadotropin, a diagnostic ovarian stimulation test has been developed which has proved of assistance in the differential diagnosis of 'no cause' secondary amenorrhea. Thirteen patients with hypothalamic/hypogonadotropic amenorrhea showed a modest increase in the urinary excretion of estrone levels rising from less than 4 mug. to 8-14 mug./24 hr. In 4 subjects with polycystic ovaries the excretion of estrone rose to at least 50 **g. /24 hr. Four of the former group were treated with human follicle-stimulating hormone and human chorionic gonadotropin. Three showed hormonal evidence of ovulation and 2 conceived in the first cycle of treatment. Three of the 4 subjects with polycystic ovaries were subjected to bilateral ovarian wedge resection and each now has regular ovulatory menstruation.
