A1  - Grant A.
A1  - Meares S.D.
A1  - Ferguson K.A.
A1  - Wallace A.L.C.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Persisent anovulation is a problem encountered in 5% of patients complaining of infertility. Temporary anovulation and defects in the function of the corpus lutcum are additional ovarian causes of infertility. In the present preliminary clinical trial an attempt has been made to assess the effectiveness of H. P. F. S. H. and H. C. G. in producing ovulation without using the excretion of pregnanediol and oestriol as guides to dosage. Two of three patients appeared to have ovulated, suggesting that activity in the human of the H. P. F. S. H. preparation, made by a procedure different from those used by other investigators, was accurately forecast by the Steelman Pohley assay.
