T1  - The condition of the genital system in women suffering from mastopathy
A1  - Manuilova I.A.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - The functional and anatomical features of the genital system were studied in 68 patients affected with mastopathy. In 52 of them disturbed menstrual functions had been recorded in recent years. Anatomical changes in the genital system were found in 59 women. Clinical observations, histological data derived from analysis of endometrial scrapings, the cytological picture of the vaginal smear and basal temperature records pointed to a relative frequency of anovulatory cycles in mastopathic patients. It is inferred that in some cases the anovulatory cycle leads to hyperoestrus and to the development not only of functional but also of anatomic changes in the genital system of women afflicted with mastopathy.
