AN  - 281242367
T1  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome (masculinity) and its types
A1  - Kvater E.J.
A1  - Krymskaya M.L.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - A detailed examination was made of 20 patients operated upon by wedge resection of the ovaries for Stein-Leventhal syndrome. The diagnosis was confirmed histologically. The authors employed a series of clinical, hormonal (determination of steroid hormones, ACTH and cortisone tests) and instrumental (culdoscopy, laparoscopy, pneumoperitoneum, etc.) methods of investigation. The results of the latter indicated that the classical Stein-Leventhal syndrome is not well marked in all cases of sclerocystic ovaries. The clinical picture demonstrated a number of types among which 2 fundamental forms were singled out: (1) those with an elevated and (2) with normal or reduced estrogen excretion. The cause of virilization and masculinization is not necessarily the upset adrenal function; they may occur in consequence of disturbed ovarian function. The operative intervention and hormonal therapy resulted in restoration of the menstrual cycle in 16 patients; in 6 cases this was followed by gestation with normal delivery in 4 of them.
