AN  - 281242207
T1  - Surgical treatment of the stein-leventhal syndrome
A1  - Starkova N.T.
A1  - Smirnova S.A.
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome or polycystic degeneration of the ovaries is characterized by hirsutism and dysfunction and enlargement of the ovaries. The results of a surgical method of treatment are presented. Of 30 patients with polycystic degeneration of the ovaries the menstrual cycle was restored in 20 cases, hirsutism was reduced or eliminated in 17 cases, and in 7 patients pregnancy occurred. The data obtained point to the expediency of using the cuneiform excision of the ovaries in this disease. Problems of etiology and pathogenesis of Stein-Leventhal syndrome and indications for surgical treatment of this condition are discussed.
