N2  - The authors have confirmed in a study of the basal temperature records that were kept for a total of 1,471 menstrual cycles by 303 girls and women that in the years following the mena r ehe the majority of menstrual cycles are abnormal. At first the proportion of anovulatory cycles and cycles with an abnormally short corpus lute u m phase to complete and normal cycles is abnormally high. This finding explains why so many women are sterile in the first few years after the menarciie. Nevertheless, it is surprising to find for how many years more abnormal th Ecnormal cycles occur and how long it takes for 'normal' conditions to be established. The optimum proportion of normal cycles is only achieved with the age group 2630 years. With one exception the observations recorded in the literature confirm the findings.
