T1  - THERMAL CHANGES in THE NORMAL MENSTRUAL CYCLE
A1  - Marshall J.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - The basal temperature has been recorded through 1.134 menstrual cycles by 155 healthy fertile women. Twenty cycles were anovulatory, 10 upset by illness, 16 inadequately recorded, and 1,088 showed the rise of temperature which is associated with ovulation. The commonest time for the rise was 13 days before the onset of the next menstruation, but there was a wide variation. The time from the rise to the next menstruation increased slightly with increasing length of the cycle.
