T3  - La arteriolitis obliterante de la ovaritis escleroquistica. Leyes que rigen ia dinamica de la vasomotricidad capilar
A1  - Stajano C.V.
A1  - Scandroglio J.J.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - After a brief summary of the history of sclerocystic ovaritis, the authors discuss the pathogenesis and its vascular substrate, in which there are 3 stages: purely congestive onset, productive processes up to definitive fibrosis, and final stages of focal and diffuse hyalinization. On the basis of experimental studies the authors state 3 fundamental facts to explain the pathogenesis of this disease: the vasculointerstitial origin of sclerocystic ovaritis; demonstration of venous vasodilatation and arteriolar vasoconstriction, and, finally, arteriolitis obliterans. The following conclusions are arrived at: The venous hypertension is reflex in origin and extends only to the parenchyma. At the same time this causes a reflex arteriolar vasoconstriction which leads to sclerosis of the parenchyma. Reymundo - Barcelona.
