T1  - THE DETERMINATION of STEROIDS in CYST FLUID from HUMAN POLYCYSTIC OVARIES
A1  - Giorgi E.P.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - A micro-method was developed for the determination of A4-3-keto-steroids andA-3s-hydroxysteroids, oestradiol-17/3, oestrone and oestriol in small volumes of cyst fluid. The method consists of separation of the neutral and phenolic fractions by solvent partition; fractionation of the neutral steroids by partition and paper chromatography and of the 3 oestrogene by adsorption chromatography after methylation. This technique was applied to cyst fluid from the ovaries of 21 patients, 12 with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, and 9 with other gynaecological disorders. In the patients with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome the steroid concentrations in cyst fluid showed a definite pattern characterized by high concentrations of A4 -androstenedione, low concentrations of progesterone and 17o-hydroxyprogesterone, and small amounts or undetectable oestrogens. In cyst fluid from the ovaries of 9 control patients there were, in general, lower concentrations of A4 -androstenedione and significant amounts of oestradiol-17/3. High concentrations of progesterone and oestrogens were found in the cyst fluid of patients with menorrhagia and endometriosis. (IU, 10).
