N2  - Five patients with Stein- Leventhal syndrome were treated with a highly potent preparation of human pituitary follicle- stimulating hormone and chorionic gonadotrophin. The first 3 were also given dexaxnethasone simultaneously to inhibit the production of adrenocortical steroids. A laparotomy was performed in each case at a different time interval after the commencement of treatment, and fluid was taken from the cystic follicles for determination of ovarian steroids. The results were generally in good agreement with urinary excretion of oestriol and pregnanediol. All responded to stimulation with gonadotrophins, some showing great enlargement of the ovaries and increases in the excretion of oestriol and pregnanediol and little androstenedione in the fluid from the cysts. The histological findings in the ovaries are discussed.
