T3  - Le syndrome de Stein- Leventhal
A1  - Gandar R.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - The morbid anatomy and aetiology are discussed. Mechanical and endocrinological theories are discussed in detail: hypothyroidism, abnormal secretion of gonadotrophins, adrenocortical hypersecretion of androgens, anomalies of ovarian secretion. The symptoms are described and include the following: oligomenorrhoea, amenorrhoea. sterility, enlargement of the ovaries and often hirsutism. Biochemical examinations are discussed in detail. Together with the clinical symptoms they form the basis of diagnosis. Optimal therapy of this syndrome consist of cuneiform resection of the ovaries with puncture of the follicle cysts. Many references are given. van.
