T1  - THE EXCRETION of 17- HYDROXY- 20- OXO- 20- METHYL STEROIDS (21- DESOXY- KETOLS) in HEALTHY WOMEN and WOMEN with ANDROGENIC CHANGES
T3  - Die Ausscheidung der 17- Hydroxy- 20- oxo- 20- methylSteroide (21- Desoxyketole) bei gesunden Frauen und bei Frauen mit androgenen Veranderungen
A1  - Zander J.
A1  - Schroder G.
A1  - Walter B.
A1  - Borth R.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - The urinary excretion was estimated by the method of Appleby and Norymberski. (1) In healthy women, the excretion rate varies with age. Before puberty, the mean values are below 100 mug. /d.; they rise to 300 mug. /d. at 30 yr., then they fall again to less than 100 jig. /d. at the menopause. The limits of normal variation between women of the same age are 60 and 180% of the mean excretion rate (fiducial limits calculated for P *0.05). (2) In congenital adrenocortical hyperplasia, the excretion is markedly higher than normal. During treatment with 100 mg. of cortisone daily, the levels decrease within 4 days to less than 200 Mg. /d. (3) The excretion is within the normal range - (a) in women with hirsutism and normal or slightly increased 17- ketosteroid excretion, associated or not with menstrual disorders, and (b) in cases of the Stein- Leventhal syndrome. (4) In metabolic experiments with 17orhydroxyprogesterone (50 to 100 mg. injected i. m. during the menstrual cycle or after the menopause), 2.0- 3.5% of the amount administered are recovered as urinary 21- desoxy- ketols. (5) In practical importance, the method is similar to the estimation of pregnanetriol. The technique is described in detail. Its reliability is satisfactory, and it helps to simplify considerably the routine operation of steroid assays. (E. 10).
