N2  - A case of Stein-Leventhal syndrome was observed in which a rapid and complete cure was obtained (normalisation of the menses and pregnancy) after chance monolateral ovariectomy. From the findings in the present case and on the grounds of various considerations, it seems doubtful that ovarian surgery represents a selective method of treatment of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome. The hypothesis is suggested that the favourable results obtained.with this method can be attributed to a general mechanism, i. e. due to surgery as such. (X, 3*).
