T1  - THE RELATIVE FREQUENCY of the ANOVULATORY CYCLE in WOMEN
T3  - Ober die relative Haufigkeit des anovulatorischen Cyclus im Leben der Frau
A1  - Doring G.K.I.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - On the basis of a material of 3.264 cycles in 481 women and girls a study was made of the distribution of anovulatory cycles, cycles with pathologically shortened corpus luteum phase and normal cycles over the various age groups. Ovarian function was examined by measurement of Basal Temperature (B.T. ). First, a marked predominance of insufficient cycles manifested itself in the years following the menarche. The optimum of normal cycles is not attained until 26-30 yr. In the 41-45 yr. group normal cycles already show a distinct tendency to decrease until the 4650 yr. group when they occur less than 50% of the time. Among 105 cycles examined post partum by measurement of B.T., 52% of normal and 48% of insufficient cycles were found.
