T1  - PARAOXYPROPIOPHENONE in GYNECOLOGIC ENDOCRINOLOGY - La paraoxypropiophenone en endocrinologie gynecologique
A1  - Gaudefroy M.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - Chemically, POP approximately represents a half molecule of stilboestrol. It may be used to decrease the action of the hypophysis or for potentialization of other drugs such as androgens and nor-steroids. Its effect was studied by examination of smear preparations and endometrial biopsies. The drug was found to be of particular value in 5 situations. In uterus myomatosus. in which the myomata were not submucous or pediculated, these myomata disappeared completely after 3 to 4 yr. of this treatment in combination with androgens or nor-steroids. The principal effect of the POP is its inhibitory action on the hypophysis or the diencephalon. In cases with a single remaining ovary, which may often become hypertrophie and cause a persistent pain throughout the cycle, usually associated with a hyperoestrogenic action, a few months' treatment with POP may result in normalization. In cases of micropolycystic ovaries resulting in a hypei hormonal condition, treatment with POP continued for several years may result in recovery. Success may also be achieved in cases of painful ovulation and of premenstrual syndrome associated with a hyperhormonal condition. Good results may also be obtained in the hyperhormonal conditions of pre-menopause, menopause and pregnancy (e.g. conditions with hypergonadotrophinuria and excessive excretion of pregnandiol). Uyttenbroeck - Antwerp (X, 3).
