N2  - Plasma progesterone levels during the menstrual cycle vary from O to 0.53 mug. per cent in the first half and from 0.6 to 2.1 Mg. per cent in the postovulatory phase. Values found in an anovulatory cycle were somewhat higher (0.18-0.93 mug. per cent) than those found in the first half of the ovulatory cycle. Certain similarities to and differences between the results found by the bioassay and physicochemical methods have been discussed. It is suggested that the gonad is the major source of the progesterone found in the plasma in the absence of pregnancy. (X, 3*).
