T1  - The effects of administration of various steroids with progesterone on the female urinary pregnanediol excretion
A1  - Nakada K.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - In a previous experiment it was reported that urinary pregnanediol levels did not rise following the administration of various synthetic gestagens to anovulatory rabbits and to ovariectomised women, hence these synthetic gestagens could not be converted to progesterone or pregnanediol. The purpose of the present experiment was to determine the variations of urinary pregnanediol levels following the administration of progesterone combined with gestagens (norethynodrel, dimethisterone, norethindrone and chlormadinon) or corticosteroids to similar rabbits or females. The rates of conversion of progesterone to urinary pregnanediol in cases of combined administration of the progesterone with the gestagens were lower than in cases where only progesterone was administered. In rabbits, conversion rates decreased from 15.3% to 5.2%, and in women they decreased from 18.4% to 4.1% (all mean values). The rates of conversion of progesterone to pregnanediol during combined administration of progesterone with triamcinolone to women averaged 32.8%, whereas in the author's previous experiment the rates of conversion to pregnanediol when triamcinolone was administered alone in rabbits averaged 50.7%.
