A1  - Fuster Chiner R.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - Making use of the known cyclic changes which take place in the utero-tubal tract due to activity of natural progesterone, the author investigated the progestational action of oral 17alpha-oxiprogesterone enolic ether in women with persistent anovulation, or evident signs of hypoluteinic cycles. By tonometry of the isthmus, estimating the capacity of the corpus uteri and the utero-tubal tonus with a device designed by the author, and by hysterosalpingography, he demonstrated the changes occurring in the genital apparatus of these women in the estrogenic stage and the progestational stage provoked by the progestogen. These changes were similar to those taking place naturally. Stress is laid on the value of carrying out HSG in the spontaneous or provoked progestational stage when the possible existence of an incompetence of the isthmic sphincter has to be verified in cases of habitual abortion.
