T1  - A case of successful wedge resection of the ovary
A1  - Iwai S.
A1  - Fukuda T.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - A 32-year-old woman, gravida-1, para-1, with the complaint of irregular menstruation in the 7th year after marriage, was diagnosed as having hypoplasia of the uterus and was treated with hormones for a year without success. Ovulation-inducing therapy led to pregnancy, but she aborted in the 4th month. Thereafter, she had secondary amenorrhoea and was sterile. Pelvic examination was normal. She had a monophasic B. B. T., patent Fallopian tubes, no evidence of tuberculous lesions by endometrial biopsy, and normal cervical secretions. Wedge resection of the ovary was performed under the diagnosis of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome unresponsive to hormone therapy. Menstruation began soon after operation, with a biphasic B. B. T., and she became pregnant. She was delivered prematurely of a 1,200 gm. male baby, who died on the 2nd day. Subsequently, her menstrual periods began again.
