N2  - In the first part of their paper the authors deal with the morphological changes observable in connection with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, firstly in relation to the ovaries and the adrenal cortex. They emphasize the role of wedge resection in the case of enlarged ovaries. In the second part of their publication they discuss the hypothalamo-hypophyseal hormone regulating mechanism of the ovaries and the adrenal cortex, stressing in cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome, and of adrenal cortex hyperplasia the pathological steroid bio-synthesis. Lajos - Pecs (X, 6).
