N2  - The over-all incidence of spontaneous pregnancy among 1460 patients seen in a sterility clinic was 23.7%, with a corrected incidence of 20.7%. No spontaneous cures were observed in patients with primary amenorrhea, hypermenorrhea, or anovulatory cycles. The 'basal line of spontaneous cures' is proposed to establish a modality upon which to gage the efficiency of various treatments of infertility and menstrual cycle abnormalities.
