N2  - By means of a hystomorphological and nystoiunctional study of a series of human ovarian tissues removed with wedge resection, the author describes some characteristic aspects which clearly differentiate these ovaries from all other types; the presence of edema and of stroma hypervascularization is responsible for the enlargement, surface tension, and perhaps also for mlcropolycystosis. The contrast observation of 'plisses' (collapsed) follicles in various involutionary phases suggests aprogestative ovula r cycles, and in the author's opinion, firmly indicates an altered metabolism of theca cells, which in turn could be responsible for 'dishormonosis'. This aspect of 'disthecosis' characteristic of enlarged shiny, pearlywhite ovaries or ovaries with aprogestative (anovular or ovula r ) cycles, may also be the basis of hirsutism in subjects with particularly sensitive hair follicles. (X, 3, 5*).
