N2  - A report is given of the case of a woman aged 34 yr., who presented the St einLeventhal syndrome associated with a carcinoma of the uterine body. The view that has been expressed in the literature that this carcinoma may be regarded as a late sequela of the untreated Stein-Leventhal syndrome is confirmed. In view of the danger of the corpus carcinoma associated with this syndrome, every case should be subjected to the wedge excision of Stein. (X, 3, 16).
