A1  - Elias Costa J.D.
A1  - Blanco R.
A1  - Chavez Ortiz P.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - Juvenile dysplasia of the ovary, although having a low incidence clinically, is of not inappreciable importance, because it interferes with the functions of the female physiology and also with those of fertility. Among the symptoms are alterations of the menstrual cycle, with amenorrhoea or polymenorrhoea, always anovulatory cycles, as well as enlarged ovaries (twice the normal size). The medical treatment is usually unsuccessful and therefore it is recommended to proceed to wedge- shaped excision of 3/4 of the ovarian parenchyma. Twenty- seven cases were treated. The function was regularized in 21 of these cases. Pregnancy was obtained in at least 11 of the 15 women who got married. Fuster - Sabadell.
