N2  - By means of paper-chromatography a study was made of the substances in the human ovary during the menstrual cycle, in extra-uterine pregnancy and the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. In contrast to earlier findings oestriol could be determined in the ovary, which proves that oestriol is not a purely extra-ovarian metabolite. During pregnancy oestrogen and oestriol reach high levels. In the Stein-Leventhal syndrome the ovaries contain a large amount of oestrogen. Vaczy - Szekszard.
