N2  - Clomiphen (MRL-41) was used in 50 patients with menstrual disorders (9 times primary, 34 times secondary amenorrhoea and 7 times oligomenorrhoea), Twentysix times (52%) a Diphasic temperature and a menstruation-like bleeding occurred, but not all these cases presented a secretory alteration of the mucosa. In general, 100 mg. were administered daily for 10 days, In 3 casess the patients became pregnant after the treatment (143-year-old patient with primary amenorrhoea). As the commonest side effect in 34% hot flushes during the treatment were reported and in 10% enlarged cystic ovaries were formed; once there was a falling out of the hairs of the head and once an intensification of an existing ichthyosis.
