T3  - Les androgenes ovariens
A1  - Zander J.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - There is no doubt that under physiological conditions the ovary produces gestagens and androgens besides oestrogenes. These hormones are found in the ovary as an intermediate product of oestrogen biosynthesis but they also enter the blood stream. Thus, androgens are true secretion products of ovaries. Under pathological conditions the ovary may produce an increased quantity of androgens. This has been proved for androstenedione and dehydroepi androsterone and probably also for testosterone in polycystic ovaries. Different enzyznic disorders in ovarian hormone biosynthesis may be considered as the cause of the increased androgen formation. At the present time the disorders in 33- hydroxysteroid-deshydrogenase and aromatising enzymes function are more fully understood. (X, 3).
