T1  - THE FIRST MENSTRUAL PERIOD POST PARTUM - Pierwsze Krwawienie miesiaczkowe po porodzie
A1  - Timonen S.
A1  - Lehto L.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - According to several authors the first menstruation after delivery may be regarded as anovulatory (although Elster and G runberge r had a contrary opinion about the subject), while the second menstrual period was often, and the third always, ovula tory. Twenty women were investigated comprising 8 lactating women and 12 nonlactating. Vaginal smears were taken, and the relationship between ovarian response and pituitary gonadotropins was established. The first menstrual bleeding occurred later in the lactating women (after 74 days) than in the non-lactating ones (after 53 days). In lactating women as a rule intermediate cells are dominating during the progestational phase. As to the oestrogen-progesterone balance the vaginal smears showed in the majority a hypooestrogenic anovulatory cycle, and there was an equilibrium between gonadotropin excretion and ovarian response that could be regarded at least as characteristic for the premenstrual phase. In non-lactating women the grouping phenomenon was positive in 50% of cases, the ovarian response was poor, while the gonadotropin secretion was adequate or high. Only 3 women out of the investigated group revealed ovulation (one lactating and 2 non-lactating) which was due to the functioning of corpus luteum. Goiab - Zabrze.
