T1  - Endocrine and metabolic factors in obesity (Japanese)
A1  - Fujiu T.
Y1  - 1963//
N2  - A 23-year-old female complained of irregular menstruation and obesity, but physical examination gave negative results. A low excretion of gonadotrophin, especially FSH, was presumed responsible for the lack of ovulation. Injection of gonadotrophin failed to cause ovulation, but resulted in formation of a polycystic ovary. Following wedge resection of both ovaries the menstrual cycle became regular, and the basal body temperature became biphasic. Histological findings ruled out Stein-Leventhal's syndrome. A partial disturbance in the function of the diencephalon was suggested bv the results of function tests.
