N2  - Some aspects of ovarian physiology and the part played by the ovaries in the SteinLeventhal syndrome are discussed by the author. Two kinds of the syndrome are accepted based on the causal factor. One is localized at the ovaries and the other at the adrenals. It is believed that at the ovaries there is a major or minor blockade at the change androstenedioneioestrone. The hormonal ovarian diseases are only enzymatic troubles and its main example is seen in the S. L. syndrome.
