Y1  - 1963//
N2  - In a pooled sample of ovarian cyst fluid obtained from 5 patients having hirsutism and polycystic ovaries, progesterone, androstenedione and oestrone were identified. In another sample collected from a single ovarian cyst of one of these patients, only androstenedione was found. The ovaries of all these patients revealed morphological features similar to those seen in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. These findings are discussed with regard to biosynthetic disturbances occurring in the Stein-Leventhal ovary.
