N2  - Pneumopelvigraphy permits a good assessment of the anatomical conditions in the small pelvis. In women with Stein-Leventhal syndrome, the uterus is usually smaller, the ovaries are enlarged, with smooth contours, sometimes asymmetrical. Pneumopelvigraphy is valuable in the differentiation of on palpation confusing inflammatory adnexal tumours and of irregularly enlarged ovaries with uneven contours, signs which are commonly not noted in Stein-Leventhal syndrome although they are often associated with similar clinical manifestations. (X, 6, 14*).
