N2  - The oestrogen content of human ovaries during the menstrual cycle in ectopic pregnancy and in different gynaecological diseases was studied. The presence of oestriol was detected during the cycle as well as during pregnancy. The oestrogen values of pregnancy were found to exceed strikingly those of the cycle. especially the increase of oestriol was very conspicuous. In the Stein-Leventhal syndrome the ovaries contained a considerable amount of oestrogen, exceeding the normal values of the cycle. (IlI, 10).
