T1  - The in-vitro biosynthesis of androgenic steroids by human normal and 1stein-leventhal type' ovarian slices
A1  - Lanthier A.
A1  - Sandor Th.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - The tissue slices were incubated in a Krebs-Ringer-phosphate-glucose medium (pH: 7.4) with pregnenolone, progesterone, a-hydroxyprogesterone and androstenedione added as substrates. The incubations were supplied with HCG as cofactor (1,000 I. U./vessel) and the reactions left to proceed for 6 or 24 hr. After incubation, the medium was extracted with chloroform and transformation products isolated by paper chromatography. Individual substances were characterized by Chromatographie mobility studies, preparation of derivatives and spectrophotornetric techniques. The following results were obtained: qualitatively, no difference could be noted between the metabolic activity of ovarian slices of either origin. Quantitatively, 'Stein-Levent hai type* slices showed an accelerated rate of production in all intermediary reactions, especially in the production of androstenedione and testosterone. In addition to the direct intermediaries, four C20 reduced transformation products of progesterone and 17or-hydroxyprogesterone were isolated from experiments involving both normal and micropolycystic ovarian slices.
