N2  - The main conclusion of this survey of psychological test findings is as follows. Whenever the difference between these two groups of patients was statistically significant or approached statistical significance, it was invariably the organic group (the group with organic lesions) which manifested the higher degree of anxiety and the greater personality impoverishment. In all the tests administered in this investigation, the organic-group women were found to be distinctly more anxious, more dependent, and less productive mentally than the psychogenic. The tests leave no doubt that anovulatory women differ from healthy women in being emotionally more tense and disturbed. The emotions play an important role in anovulation.
