N2  - The authors have taken into consideration the data obtained from a clinical and biological analysis of 64 cases of hirsutistn. In these cases they found that the most significant elements appeared to be the cyclic disturbances associated with hi r sut ism, especially amenorrhoea, and the frequent encounter of more or less pathological gynaecographs. Also considered in the light of some biological data, such as deficient ovarian function, these elements demonstrate the more or less evident ovarian pathology which manifests itself through a number of stages from simple hirsutism to the classic Stein-Leventhal syndrome.
