T1  - NEW OVULATION TEST
A1  - De Ovulacso N.T.
A1  - Montera A.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A description is given of a test by which it is possible to predict the period of fertility. A plastic device is described by which vaginal mucus can be collected and which prevents this mucus from coming into contact with vaginal carbohydrates. Then, part of the vaginal mucus collected is placed into contact with a ribbon with which the plastic vaginal device is provided. If the quantity is lower than 0.1%, the colour is pale blue. If it is higher than 0.25% the colour is intensely blue. The intense blue colour indicates high glucose values, which coinc ie with the date of ovulation. The change in colour takes place 1 to 3 days befort and persists until 1 to 4 days after ovulation. A repetition of the colouring or persistence for a longer time indicates a 2nd ovulation. The lack of positivity of the test might favour the diagnosis in cases of absence of ovulation; excess of oestrogene (newgrowth of the stratum granulos urn. polycystic ovary or pregnancy): in these cases the test is constantly positive or positive for a long time. The presence of glucose is explained as being due to the follicular fluid which is believed to be aspirated and eliminated through the tubes and the uterus, In cases of adhesions or obstructions of the tubes, the result was negative. Conclusions are drawn with reference to periodical continence to space pregnancies, or for fixing the days of coitus in order to facilitate pregnancies. When the quantity of glycogen is reduced, the author recommends application of a sterile 0.25% glucose solution in normal saline by a transuterotubal lavage or its injection by puncture of Douglas' cul-de-sac. Gar z on - Bureos.
