T1  - CYCLIC ANOMALIES and STERILITY in WOMEN with HIRSUTlSM and POLYCYSTlC OVARIES. THE PROBLEM of the STEIN-LEVENTHAL SYNDROME
T3  - Zyklusanomalien und Sterilitat bei Frauen mit Hirsutismus und polycystischen Ovarien. Zum Problem des Stein-Leventhal Syndroms
A1  - Stockii A.
A1  - Kubli F.
A1  - Keller M.
A1  - Kaufmann P.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - The symptomatology of the poly cystic ovary syndrome is discussed in the light of 19 cases. It is emphasised that hirsutism, obesity, amenorrhoea. bilateral enlargement of the ovaries and elevation of urinary 17-ketosteroid excretion are not always present. Polycystic degeneration of the ovaries and ovarian dysfunction are the only symptoms observed in all cases. Twelve cases were treated by wedge resection, 4 cases by wedge resection combined with cortisone administration, and 3 cases with cortisone alone. Therapy was successful in 13 cases and failed in 6 cases. 8 out of 13 cases treated for sterility conceived. The authors' principles of treatment are described. The latest results of biochemical investigation, which point to the ovary as the primary source of the disease, are discussed. There is, however, some evidence that different aetiological entities may produce identical symptoms. Reliable methods of further elucidating the causal relationships of the poly cystic ovary syndrome are lacking at present.
