N2  - The authors describe three cases of the syndrome of Mayer-Rokitansky- Kuster associated with right-sided abnormalities of the kidneys, such as hypoplasia, ptosis, and horse-shoe kidney. There was a hyperfolliculinaemic syndrome in one case, and a Stein- Leventhal syndrome in another, with the clinical and anatomical symptoms respectively. An artificial vagina ('neovagina') was made in two cases; either of the Iwo patients was operated on according to the operative procedure described by Bloch. The authors consider the exploratory laparotomy a necessity from the standpoint both of diagnosis and therapy.
