T1  - KETOSTEROID METABOLITESlN STEIN-LEVENTHAL1S SYNDROME after WEDGE-SHAPED RESECTION of the OVARIES
T3  - Metabolitoe cetosteroideos en el Stein-Le venthal traa la seccion cuneiforme de los ovarios
A1  - Bonilla F.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - Determination of the metabolites of the urinary 17-ketosteroids after wedge-shaped resection of the ovaries demonstrated in 3 cases of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome a diminution in dehydrotf/uandrosterone, which had hitherto been considered as being of exclusively adrenal origin. Now, it is known that the disturbance in steroid biosynthesis in polycystic ovaries may lead to the formation of this metabolite, which renders the chromatogram valueless in the differential diagnosis between ovarian and adrenal syndromes. Great variations in the overall elimination of these metabolites may account for another clinical fact, namely the normalization of the genital cycle after wedgeshaped ovarian resection, without alteration of the urinary elimination of these steroids.
