T1  - OVARIAN and ADRENAL MORPHOLOGY in CASES of HIRSUTISM or VIRILISM and STEIN-LEVENTHAL SYNDROME
A1  - Benedict P.H.
A1  - Cohen R.B.
A1  - Cope O.
A1  - Scully R.E.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A large and poorly defined group of women with hirsutism or virilism associated with menstrual disturbances in whom the relative participation of the adrenal cortex and the ovary in the production of the disorder is difficult to assess. Many theories were mentioned. The authors began the study in 1937 which included exploration and biopsy of the adrenal cortex and the ovary. Six cases are reported in detail. This study confirms the coexistence of pathologic lesions in the ovaries and adrenal glands in a number of cases. It does not answer the question as to the relative participation of either in the production of the disorder. The weight of evidence pointing to stimulation of both organs, however, suggests that the pituitary gland or hypothalamus may play a prominent role. Black - Memphis, Tenn.
