T1  - LUTEINIZING HORMONE EXCRETION in THE POLYCYSTIC OVARY SYNDROME
A1  - Taymor M.
A1  - Barnard R.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - LH excretion levels were found to be elevated in 14 of 32 patients with polycystic ovarian disease. In patients with the classical Stein- Leventhal syndrome - notably, enlarged polycystic ovaries - excretion levels were elevated in 50% of the cases. In patients with normally sized polycystic ovaries, elevation was noted in only 18% while elevated excretion levels were also noted in 4 of 9 patients with presumed adrenal hyperplasia. LH excretion levels seemed to be correlated with the size of the ovary and the duration of amenorrhoea. The findings are further evidence that the Stein- Leventhal syndrome is not in itself a specific entity, but rather part of a progressive and, at times, poly glandular, endocrinopathy. (Ill, 10).
