N2  - The index (dehydroe/wandrosterone + 11beta- hydroxy- aetiocholanolone + 11beta- hydroxyandrosterone + 11- keto- aetiocholanolone + 11- keto- androsterone): (aetiocholanolone + androsterone) is smaller than 1 in Stein- Leventhal syndrome, higher than 1 in cases of adrenal hirsutism (urine values). Some of the cases of 'idiopathic' hirsutism is caused by latent hypercorticism: the potential adrenocortical hyperproduction of androgens takes place only under stress conditions. In these cases the index is smaller than 1 in the basal state but becomes greater than 1 after ACTH administration. The results of steroid analyses in 6 cases of ovarian hirsutism, 7 cases of adrenocortical hirsutism and 6 cases of 'idiopathic' hirsutism are presented. Schreiber - Prague (III, 10).
