T1  - Ovarian histology in the stein-leventhal syndrome
A1  - Vaughan Jones R.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - Sections of ovarian wedge resection specimens from 17 cases of the St ein-Le v enthai syndrome were examined and compared with controls. Capsular thickening was inconstant but definite thickening of the theca interna surrounding follicles was present in all cases and marked in 13 cases. In 6 cases there was luteinization of the theca interna. Follicle fluid from 5 of these cases had previously been shown to contain weakly androgenic substances but no oestrogen. The histology in these cases was similar to that in the remainder.
