T1  - A study of urinary excretion of steroids in anovulation
T3  - Etude de l'excretion des steroides urinaires dans l'anovulation
A1  - Varangot J.
A1  - Gedard L.
A1  - Tchobroutsky C.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A study was made of 26 patients with anovulation and normal urinary gonadotrophin excretion. In 11 patients an abnormally high response was found in the 17-ketosteroids, and especially DHA, after stimulation by AGTH. Pregnanediol, pregnanetriol and urinary oestrogens were usually normal but increased after stimulation with AGTH. In 5 patients the urinary excretion of oestrogens was higher than 40 mug./24 hr.; the increase was mainly reflected in the oestriol. A short-term inhibition test was made by means of dexamethasone in 9 patients; in 4 of these it was followed by stimulation with chorionic hormone. No proof was obtained that the disorders were of adrenal or ovarian origin. Regardless of the biological results, 6 patients were given prolonged administration of synthetic corticoids. Five patients responded by ovulatory cycles for which no indication was found in the previous examinations. Wedge resection of the ovaries led to recovery in 1patient, partial improvement in 3 and failure in 1.
