N2  - One month after radical surgical thyroidectomy, 13 out of 28 rabbits had raspberry-like polycystic ovaries. Thyroidectomy increased the content of water, hexuronic acid, and the in-vivo uptake of S<ovid:sup>35</ovid:sup>-labelled sulphate in acid mucopolysaccharides. There is parallelism, on the one hand, between the ovarian contents of hexosamine and hexuronic acid, and on the other, between S<ovid:sup>35</ovid:sup>-labelled sulphate uptake in the ovary and the uptake of S <ovid:sup>35</ovid:sup>-labelled sulphate in the fraction of acid mucopolysaccharides.
