Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A report on 3 ca,e. A very thorough biochemical investigation was made with successively a stimulation with ACTH. an adrenal blockade with dexamethasone and an ovarian stimulation with chorionic gonadotrophin associated with the blockade. It is possible to demonstrate the production by the ovaries of 17-ketosteroid pre-cursors that very likely share in the production of the virilization phenomena. There is a discussion on the limit of Stein- Le ven thai'a syndrome. The possible dissociation of the various element of the syndrome is canvassed: hirsutism and ovarian hyperandrogenism may be absent in authenticated cases of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome, and. conversely, the same hormonal abnormalities may be noted in patients with hirsutism in the absence of the characteristic ovarian lesions of the eyndrome.
