T1  - A new case of 'non-functioning ovaries'
T3  - Un nouveau cas d'ovaires non fonctionnels'
A1  - Klotz H.P.
A1  - Xirau J.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - In 1958 Klotz et al. described the clinical syndrome of 'non-functioning ovaries' characterized by primary amenorrhoea, non-functioning but present ovaries (that is, not responsive to gonadotrophic hormone) and low body height. About 15 cases are now known. Sex chromatin appeared to be absent. In this new case, however, sex chromatin was found to be present in 78% of skin cells, the karyotype being 44 A + XX. One of the X-chromosomes was first diagnosed as qualitatively different from the other (somewhat metacentric and slightly longer). In a footnote (apparently added later) it is stated that 'Miss M. Gautier withdraws her interpretation and does not feel certain about the qualitative X-chromosomal anomaly'. At laparotomy both ovaries were found to be present. Histologically only the right ovary showed aspects resembling Stein-Leventhal's syndrome. The left ovary did not display any trace of ovulation.
