T1  - Controversial aspects of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome
A1  - Stein I.F.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - 'It is twenty-six years since our first publication (and thirty-two years since treating the first patient in this series) on bilateral polycystic ovaries associated with amenorrhea'. 'There has been some question as to whether a syndrome actually exists, the criterion depending upon the pathologist's report of resected tissue. I believe that the syndrome is a clinical entity and that the pathological report is of secondary importance, inasmuch as polycystic ovaries which are quite similar occur in a number of disorders other than Stein-Leventhal syndrome.' (The Editor draws the attention of human geneticists to this controversy (entity or not?) in the light of the work of Netter et al. (see abstract 19) in which karyotypes in Stein-Leventhal's disease are reported as often being abnormal.).
