T3  - Test d'ovulation et dysovulations. Application des norsteroides progestatifs
A1  - Villar J.
A1  - Bernard I.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - This is a discussion of the various methods of determining the time of ovulation: basai temperature (the rise should be distinct and last for at least 72 hr.), vaginal auicai, crystallization, clasrity, 'Spinnbsrkeit' and glucose content of the cervical mucus (optimal pH for the spermatozoa is 6.5), premenstrual endometrial biopsy and the possible role of androgens. It was found that many women considered normally fertile showed endometrial changes. The authors discuss on modern progestational drugs (norsteroids), their chemistry and the oestrogen-progesterone ratio in these preparations, as well as their inhibiting effect on ovulation, and report on administration of progestational substances to 7 patients with amenorrhoea, 21 with meno-metrorrhagias, 11 with infertility (including anovulation) and patients with corpus luteum insufficiency and endometriosis. Administration of norsteroids is still in the experimental stage, though the industry can supply the clinician with a multitude of synthetic varieties.
