T1  - Female sterility. Evaluation of diagnostic teste and treatments
T3  - La sterilite feminine. Evaluation des epreuves diagnostiques et traitements
A1  - Simard R.
A1  - Lapointe R.
A1  - Van Gampenhout J.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - When dealing with sterility, we must proceed to a detailed history of both partners, and check first the fertility index of the male factor. As known, afterwards the woman must be submitted to many basic tests to find the factor involved. The uterosalpingogram is a basic test not only to establish the patency of the tubes but also to reveal any possible lesion which might otherwise have been overlooked. This examination is done on a large scale in the authors' clinic and has made it possible to establish an accurate diagnosis in a great number of cases and consequently to administer without delay the appropriate medical or surgical treatment. Tubal insufflation for instance has the advantage that it can be repeated after many consecutive cycles without danger, and in fact in some cases freed the occluded tubes at the ampulla portion. Menstrual disorders constitute a great factor contributing to 15% of infertility cases. Ovulation tests must be performed and if an anovulatory cycle is proved, endocrine treatment must be given and checked by endometrial biopsies, basic temperature and vaginal smears. Surgical treatment of ovarian and' uterine tumours in most cases have a good prognosis with regard to fertility. Tubal surgery, partial resection or implantation is still a great problem according to the end results.
