T1  - An evaluation of etiologic factors and therapy in 555 private patients mth primary infertility
A1  - Jones G.S.
A1  - Pourmand K.
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - The material for this study was classified according to n aetiological factors: tubes, ovaries, semen, cervix, uterus, endometriosis, age, nutrition, neuropsychological state, intercourse, and unknown. The most effective therapeutic measures were: the X-ray and Rubin's test in the tubal group; the wedge resection operation % for correction of the Stein-Leventhal's syndrome; cortisone for adrenal dysfunc- * tions; progesterone for the luteal phase defect; methyltestosterone for relief of pain in endometriosis; donor insemination when infertility was due to male factors. The duration of infertility was found to be of importance. Prior to 2 yr. of infertility the pregnancy rate was better than after 2 yr. Comparisons of groups of patients, uniform as to age, showed that 30 yr. was more iikely to be the breaking.
