T1  - Clinico-morphological features of anovulatory haemorrhage accompanied with hyperplasia of the endometrium (Russian text)
A1  - Vishnevskaya L.G.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - The investigation of 100 patients with anovulatory haemorrhage and hyperplasia of the endometrium revealed that this condition was preceded by primary and prolonged secondary sterility; in mpst cases the haemorrhage was prolonged and not very intensive, with transitory aggravations and intermissions. Spontaneous arrest of the haemorrhage was not observed as a rule. Severely changed hyperplastic mucosa resisted complete detachment for a long time, such detachment being confined to small dystrophic and necrotic parts of the superficial layer. Detachment is hindered by the solid, fibrous reticular argyrophil structure of the hyperplastic mucosa in which signs of regeneration and growth were constantly evident. The results of this investigation indicated that the duration of the haemorrhage does not represent the degree of detachment, nor is the cessation of haemorrhage a sign of complete detachment.
