A1  - Muller P.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - 'Dynamic examination of the corpus luteum' according to JayIe is discussed. The test consists of administration of 2 times 10,000 I. U. c h or ionic gonadotrophin within 48 hr. Prior to the test and 7 days afterwards the oestrogene and pregnanediol are determined. The findings permit conclusions on a corpus luteum insufficiency, oestrogen insufficiency or pituitary disturbance. A short discussion is given on Rydberg's scheme of treatment. Complications are cystic degeneration and ruptured ovarian cysts with intraperitoneal bleeding. Polycystic degeneration of the ovaries should be excluded by laparotomy or laparoscopy before Jayle's test is carried out>> since the chance of the above-mentioned complications is high in such patients.
