N2  - 1177. Allyloestrenol was studied for its effect on primary and secondary amenorrhoea, anovulation, irregular shedding of the cndometrium, premenstrual tension, and threatened or habitual abortion. The progestational effect was good in all of the groups. Allyloestrenol is not excreted as pregnanediol in the urine. In the doses used, the preparation had no inhibitory effect on the adrenal cortex, the plasma hi stamina se activity did not increase, and it had no demonstrable androgenic or other side effects.
