T1  - Thecoma and polycystic disease of the ovaries
A1  - Evans T.N.
A1  - Riley G.M.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - A nulligravida aged 32 years showed amenorrhoea of 2 years' standing. There was no hirsutism. The right ovary was 2x5 cm. in size, the left ovary was not palpable. The urinary excretion of oestrogene, gonadotrophins, pregnanediol, 17-ketosteroids and pregnanetriol was normal. The endometrium was in the proliferative stage. The right ovary was removed and the left ovary was subjected to wedge resection. In the right ovary, a solid yellow tumour was found, which proved to be a thecoma. The resected fragment of the left ovary showed phenomena that were characteristic of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome: fibrosis of the tunica albuginea, follicular cysts with hyperplasia of the theca interna. The first menstruation ensued 27 days after the operation. Attention is called to the similarities between the pathology of the tbeca-cell tumour and that of polycystic ovary; it is suggested that thrsc conditions may have the same endocrine-logical pathogenesis, viz. an abnormal stimulation by gonadotrophins.
