A1  - Jacobs W.M.
A1  - Friedinan J.A.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - Report on 12 cases, in whom the ovaries showed the macro- and microscopic picture of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. All these patients had excessive and repeated metrorrhagia. Wedge resection of the ovaries was effective in all but three, after all other therapy had failed. The authors suggest that the hyperplastic theca cells produce either androgens (with amennorrhoea and defeminization) or oestrogens (with metrorrhagia and no defeminization) or both. (One patient had acne + mild hirsutism + intermittent bleeding.).
