Y1  - 1961//
N2  - MER-25 (1-p-2-diethylaminoethoxyphenyl)-1-2-p-methoxyphenylethanolblocks the response of oestrogen target organs. Previous experiments showed good results in mastodynia associated with chronic cystic mastitis although remissions of more than 4 months could not be obtained with doses of 1 g. daily. No effect on endometriosis was observed. This article deals with the results of MER in endometrial hyperplasia and carcinoma in three patients. In all cases endometrial biopsy showed normal or atrophie phase, after some weeks of daily dos es of 1-1.5 g. One case of early carcinoma of the corpus was not influenced. After MER (500-800 mg. p. d.) a rise in the total oestrogens and of oestradiol was observed. FSH excretion increased. After oophorectomy oestrogens were increased but the oestradiol values were still higher. FSH was not influenced after oophorectomy. In patients with Stein-Leventhal syndrome and anovulatory cycles MER induced ovulation in doses of 750 mg. daily during 3-5 months. Of the 4 cases, 2 became pregnant. The authors conclude that MER causes a change in the metabolism of oestrogens. When the ovaries are present intermediary products are liberated which influence the hypophysis and stimulate this organ to release LH. Ten Berge - Blaricum (X, 3).
