N2  - Gynaecographic examination was carried out in cases of primary amenorrhoea and of hirsutism without additional hysterography. Among the cases of amenorrhoea there were 2 of uterine aplasia, 4 of gonadal agenesis, and 2 of gonadal hypogenesis. In all cases the gynaecography clearly revealed the small size of the genital organs. The cases of hirsutism are subdivided into 3 groups: with normal ovaries, with ovaries slightly enlarged and with large ovaries; the increase in size is always bilateral. However, the size of the ovary is not all-important and many hirsute women have cortical fibrosis of the Stein-Leventhal type while the size is normal.
