N2  - It is held that psychogenic anovulation is a warning of tension and unrest within the patient's emotional life. It should be regarded as a symptom rather than as a treatment-end in itself. It is possible for the patient to have such a problem in addition to organic causes of anovulation. The authors' programme is aimed at routine inquiries in this fashion so that one is not lulled by the presence of organic pathology into feeling that this guarantees the serenity of the patient's emotional life. The experiences to date have been most rewarding.
