N2  - Thyroidectomy in rabbits brought about enlargement of the ovaries. Four out of 10 thyroidectomized animals presented polycystic ovaries consisting mostly of giant follicles. The increased ovarian weight was due to an increased content of water which was accompanied by an increased concentration of hexosamine. Microscopic examination revealed a hypertrophy of the follicular tissue. The fluid of the large follicles, staining metachromatically with toluidine blue had a high content of acid mucopolysaccharides. The graafian follicles of the thyroidectomized animals showed an increased uptake of S<ovid:sup>35</ovid:sup>. whereas developing follicles, with a high production of metachromatic substance incorporated only negligible amounts of S<ovid:sup>35</ovid:sup>.
