T1  - A case of porcelain ovaries in a girl prior to the menarche
A1  - Dieulafe R.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - A report is given of the case of a girl aged 12 yr., who was subjected to an emergency operation for torsion of the right adnexa with an ovary the size of a tangerine. The left ovary was somewhat larger than normal. The histological examination revealed all the features of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. It is concluded that the early manifestation of this syndrome constitutes an argument in favour of a congenital and genetic origin of the disease.
