T1  - Influence of overian function on the fibrinolytic enzyme system. i. ovulatory and anovulatory cycles
A1  - Turksoy R.N.
A1  - Phillips L.L.
A1  - Southam A.L.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - Over a period of one to some months at several moments determinations were made of the nbrinogen, the free profibrinolysin, the total profibrinolysin, and the antifibrinolysin levels of 10 normal women, 11 anovulatory women, 2 castrated women and 2 normal young men. The levels were constant in the men and in the castrated women. In the ovulatory group the levels were strongly influenced by the menstrual cycle: there was an increase in profibrinolysin and antifibrinolysin, followed by an increase of fibrinogen at the time of ovulation. Another elevation was seen 3-6 days before menstruation. There was a premenstrual decline of the levels and an increase after the beginning of the menstrual period. Fibrinogen levels varied from 180-355 mg. in the ovulatory ,group and from 250-517 in the anovulatory group, the latter without cyclic influence. It is thought that the alteration in the levels in the ovulatory group is related to the alteration of urinary oestrogen excretion. The time of ovulation was determined with endometrial biopsy and temperature chart.
