A1  - Greenblatt R.B.
A1  - Barfield W.E.
A1  - Jungck E.C.
A1  - Ray A.W.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - MRL/41, an analogue of the nonsteroid oestrogen, chlorotrianisene, was evaluated in the human female because it was shown to possess pituitary gonadotrophininhibiting and antifecundity properties in rats. Although structurally related to a hormone-like chemical agent, this compound does not exhibit oestrogenic, propestogenic, or androgenic activity in the human. Studies with this drug were initiated primarily because of its potential as an antifertility agent. Contrary to expectations, some unsuspected and interesting biological activities were observed, one of which was the induction of ovulatory-type menses in amenorrhoeic anovulatory females.
