N2  - Nine cases of anovulation (without other factors of sterility) are presented in which aetiological therapy was used in 6 (hypothyroidism, suprarenal dysfunction and state of anxiety) and in 2 cases with undetermined causes progesterone was administered. Of these cases, 7 became pregnant and I did not, but the cycles became ovulatory (she continues to receive treatment). In all these cases tests were made of gonadotrophin, which was found to have decreased only in 3 women, who became pregnant. Therapy by gonadotrophin was never used.
