T1  - Urinary pregnanetriolone in the diagnosis of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome
A1  - Shearman R.P.
A1  - Cox R.I.
A1  - Gannon A.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - In 16 patients with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome - confirmed by histological examination of the removed ovarian tissue - the urinary excretion of several hormones was determined. The urinary levels of the 17-ketosteroids, of the 17-ketogens and of pregnanetriol were the same as in healthy women. The excretion of pregnanediol did not differ from that in the proliferative phase of the normal menstrual cycle. Pregnanetriolone was found in all patients in quantities of 0.01 to 0.3 mg. per 24 hr. This substance is not found in healthy women, but it is present in cases of adrenocortical hyperplasia and possibly also in other abnormalities of the adrenal cortex; however, in these cases there are also abnormalities in the excretion of the 17-ketosteroids and of the 17-ketogens. The authors regard the test of pregnanetriolone in the urine as a valuable aid in the diagnosis of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome.
