T1  - The indications for wedge resection of the ovaries
T3  - Les indications de la resection cuneiforme des ovaires. A propos du soi-disant syndrome de Stein-Leventhal
A1  - Varangot J.
A1  - Tchobroutsky C.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - A report is given on 22 cases of wedge resection of the ovaries performed to correct anovulation. Regular menstrual cycles with, probably, ovulation were observed in 17 cases. An attempt was made to determine which patients can benefit from wedge resection. No valid criterion was found for preferring surgical treatment to corticoid therapy. The clinical signs, coelioscopy, determinations of FSH, 17-ketosteroids and dehydroandrosterone offer no information. Among the successfully treated patients some had ovaries of normal size, some had low FSH levels and others had adrenal hyperandrogenism.
