T1  - PNEUMOPELVIGRAPHIC DIAGNOSIS in GYNAECOLOGICAL ENDOCRINOLOGY
T3  - Pneumopelvigraficka diagnostika v gynekologicke endokrinologii Silinkova
A1  - Malkova E.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - Pneumopelvigraphic examinations were performed in 70 women, mostly for sterility and endocrine disorders. A normal finding of the uterus and ovaries was confirmed in 10 patients, inflammatory changes of the adnexa in 6, t u mo r ou s u ter iovarian processes in 9, trophic disorders - poly cystic degeneration of the ovaries - in 24, developmental anomalies in 21. Pneu mope Iv igraphy renders it possible to evaluate far more accurately the shape and size of the ovaries than palpation and in many instances it is decisive for diagnosis and therapeutic planning. Particularly important are the results obtained as regards the differential diagnosis of adrenal or ovarian aetiology of some endocrine syndromes and the classification of developmental disorders. Assessment of the gonad doses during pneu mope Iv igraphy indicates that these doses can be reduced by using a suitable technique. The diagnostic value outweighs the hazard of radiation, provided every examination is clinically indicated and correctly carried out.
