T1  - THE SYNDROME of STEIN and LEVENTHAL. a NEW BIOLOGICAL STUDY and PERSONAL CONCEPTION of THIS SYNDROME (French text)
A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Yaneva H.
A1  - Mauvais-Jarvis P.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - The present authors believe that the syndrome is not sufficiently well-defined and offer their own strict criteria: hypomenorrhoea must be extreme with at most 4 or 5 periods per year and also progressive; sterility is the rule; luteal insufficiency as shown by a mono phasic temperature, negiible pregnanediol excretion and absent secretory change in the endometrium; hirsutism and obesity are not essential elements; the ovaries are enlarged and hard and smooth, their size is constant and they are not tender; finally dramatic cure following ovarian resection is the ultimate diagnostic proof. Histological criteria are also described, amongst them being: the covering is of an even thickness, the cysts are not large but of similar size throughout the ovary, corpora lutea and aibicantia are absent, the primitive follicles are characteristically aligned regularly under the capsule. After describin various hormonal studies, the authors postulate that this syndrome is a minor form of congenital ovarian dysgenesis.
