T1  - Research on the Stein-Leventhal disease
T3  - Recherches sur la maladie de Stein et Leventhal
A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Mauvais-Jarvis P.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - It is shown that it is possible to describe the criteria which define the Stein-Leventhal disease. Each symptom is studied and criticized, and at the end of this criticism, a clinical picture emerges. The definition suggested in this, way may be somewhat restricted but it certainly corresponds to a well-defined disease. The authors have studied the histology and biology of this disease. The latter was determined by dynamic tests during which they performed an inhibition of the corticosuprarenal at the same time as a stimulation of the ovaries. In the course of the disease the abnormal secretion by the ovaries of the precursors of the urinary 17-ketosteroids could be demonstrated. Beyond the limits of the disorder, there are series of graded forms among which the authors stress certain types of gonadal dysgenesia. The authors suggest the hypothesis that the Stein-Leventhal disease is probably a genetic, gonadal condition, which lies at the extreme limit of the gonadad dysgenesis.
