T1  - Fibrocystic mastopathy; morbid-anatomical findings in an unusual clinical case
T3  - Considerazioni sulla mastopatia fibro-cistica: Reperti anatomo-patologici di un singolare caso clinico
A1  - Burlina A.
Y1  - 1961//
N2  - A description is given of a case of fibrocystic mastopathy, on the left side, which occurred in a woman aged 41 yr. who 2 yr. previously had been subjected to operation for carcinoma of the right breast. Post-mortem examination revealed metastases along the right mammary artery, with spread to the liver, and a cystic right ovary; furthermore, the left breast was invaded by neoplastic epithelial elements. First of all the author rejects the supposition that the solid carcinoma of the right breast might have developed a fibrocystic substrate. With regard to the genesis of the fibrocystic mastopathy, he confirms the pathogenic conception of hyperoestrogenism. In the case here considered, the cystic ovary might have been regarded as proof of the hormonal imbalance, save for the fact that the cystic mastopathy had had its onset in a period when the patient had been treated for more than two yr. with testosterone and for many months with paraoxypropiophenone in large doses, in other words, had had anti-oestrogenic treatment. The histopathological aspects of the glands with internal secretion are described, and it is recalled that it has been demonstrated experimentally that it is possible for the ovary in vivo to transform testosterone into oestradiol; the hypothesis is advanced that the /Miraoxy-propiophenone might have exerted a favourable effect in the genesis of the fibrocystic mastopathy. In conclusion it is stated that in the interpretation of this condition we must presume the existence of endocrine imbalances of more complex nature than just hyperoestrogenism.
