T1  - Ovarian tumors and cysts associated with sexual precocity. report of 3 cases and review of the literature
A1  - Everlein W.R.
A1  - Bongiovanni A.M.
A1  - Jones I.T.
A1  - Yakovac W.C.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Three cases of ovarian tumours are presented, associated with isosexual precocity. In the first 2 cases, it concerned granulosa cell tumours, which were removed; the girls did not have a relapse. In the 3rd case, a luteinizing cyst was found, a sclerous ovary, covered by a shell as in the 'Stein-Leventhal syndrome'. The removal produced the regression of the symptoms of precocity. There are many difficulties in distinguishing this disease from constitutional precocity. The follow-up examination of all published cases demonstrates the urgency of laparotomy in doubtful cases. In the 3rd case, the relation between ovarian cyst and isosexual precocity is of the constitutional type. These cysts must be treated not by ovariectomy, but with drugs.
