N2  - The crystallization test was used for hormonal diagnosis in 200 women. This test makes it possible to distinguish phases of the menstrual cycle, assess the ovulation, divulge anovulatory and 'hidden' cycles, effect differential diagnosis of pregnancy and amenorrhoea of diverse origin, and helps to elucidate the ovariogenic and endometrial nature of amenorrhoea. The test is also important for the control of hormone therapy. It supplements cytological studies of vaginal smears.
