T1  - Limitsop stein-leventhal's syndrome. six cases of amenorrhoea and menstrual disturbances treated by wedge-shaped resection of the ovaries
T3  - Des limites du syndrome de Stein-Leventhal. Six cas d'ame norrhee et de troubles des regles traitees par resection cuneiforme des ovaires
A1  - Vignalou J.
A1  - Jamain B.
A1  - Plouin S.
A1  - Letessier A.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Although there exists a clinical unity of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome and although increase in the volume of the ovaries is constantly found in it, there does not exist a corresponding biological entity. From the endocrinological point of view, the pictures studied by the authors could be classified under various headings. Therefore, it would seem difficult to try and define the syndrome by its hormonal conditioning. On the other hand, histological study always shows, be it in various proportions, sclerosis of the albuginea, cystic follicles and luteinization of the theca interna. But these pictures do not necessarily imply that operation will give rise to clinical disturbances. Therefore, the cure cannot be ascribed with certainty to the removal of the mechanical obstacle. Thus, tor the confirmation of the syndrome only the clinical picture and the large ovaries, 'the landmarks of the diagnosis', should be kept in mind. Stress is laid on the major importance of coelioscopy, which makes it possible to demonstrate the existence and degree of the thickened ovarian surface . the size of the ovaries, their volume as compared with that of the uterus. At the same time, it makes it possible to rule out atrophie ovaries which would not respond to surgical treatment.
