T1  - Hirsutism: Its relationship to ovarian pathology
A1  - Becker S.F.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Four patients, aged 21 to 29, with hirsutism, apparently related to ovarian pathology, are described. No pituitary or adrenal abnormality was found but polycystic ovaries were present in all cases and wedge resection of the ovaries was carried out in all four cases. Hirsutism, however, persisted although in one case the menses became more regular. In one case, in addition to ovarian wedge resection, pituitary-ovarian radiation, steroids and cyclic oestrogen/ progesterone therapy were tried but without alleviation of the hirsutism. It is concluded that more study of the problem will be required before effective treatment of hirsutism is available.
