T1  - Therapeutic results obtained in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome
T3  - Resultats therapeutiques obtenus au cours du syndrome de Stein et Leventhal
A1  - Kologlu S.
A1  - Esendal A.
A1  - Kandemir E.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - This article deals with 4 cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome. Three patients were treated by corticoids without significant results; thereafter 2 cases were treated by ample wedge resection with remarkable results, the other 2 were treated by less extensive resection and the results were disappointing. Wedge resection should be performed as soon as the diagnosis is made. The resection should be ample, only the hilar parts of the ovaries should remain. Hormonal treatment has its indications if surgery fails. Medical treatment does not influence the hirsutism.
