T1  - Results of bilateral ovarian wedge resection
A1  - Plate W.P.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Report on the results of 114 cases of wedge resection of the ovaries for menstrual disturbances. Postoperative follow-up was possible in 111 patients. A regular cycle was observed in 62 cases (56%). In 62 cases the marriage had been sterile prior to the operation; after the operation 20 of the women (32%) became preg-nant. The author recommends the wedge resection in the first place for cases of anovulatory cycle and of secondary amenorrhoea. In cases of hirsutism the operation had very little effect. Mention is made of the various theories that have been advanced to explain the favourable effect of the wedge resection, and the author explains why no effect was obtained in hirsutism. For the application of the wedge resection it is a condition, that the excretion of gonadotrophins and oestrogens is normal, while the excretion of the 17-ketosteroids must be normal or may be slightly increased. Palpability of the ovaries is not regarded as a condition.
