T1  - Ovarian function in fibromyoma of the uterus examined with histochemical methods
T3  - Alcune considerazioni sulla funzionalita ovarica nel fibromioma uterin indagata con metodiche istochimiche
A1  - De Laurentiis G.
A1  - Forleo R.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - A study was made of the ovaries of 10 women aged between 38 and 50 yr., all of them with regular menstruation, with fibromyoma of the uterus; the tissue findings were compared with the hormonal pattern. The histological and histochemical criteria on which the assessment of ovarian function was based were: (1) the presence, the degree of development, and the histo-functional condition of the theca interna; (2) the presence or absence in the walls of cysts (if any), of signs of histo-functional activity; (3) the characteristics of the cortical layer of the ovary (abundance of cellular elements, tendency to thecomatosis). From the collected data obtained and their correlation with the clinical and laboratory findings, it can be concluded that the presence or absence of cystic formations in the ovaries of patients with fibroma does not in itself signify a constant increase of the oestrogenic activity of the ovaries. Also, the macroscopic finding of micro-polycystic ovaries does not always correspond to an enhanced hormonal activity. It is only on the basis of the combined histo-functional data together with the endocrinological data that we can assess the hormonal condition in each individual case.
