N2  - A description is given of 4 patients; all had oligomenorrhoea and anovulation. Bilateral ovarian resection led to appearance of an ovulatory cycle, 3 patients became pregnant. A review is given of the clinical symptoms, the anatomical changes in the ovary, the hormonal state, pathogenesis and treatment. The author supposes the syndrome to be a 'dysneurovary', favourably influenced by the operation. It is pointed out that as early as 1927, Cotte induced an ovulatory cycle by resection of sclerocystic ovaries without the anatomical changes described in Stein-Leventhal syndrome. This is proved by a description of 2 cases.
