N2  - The article gives a survey of the most important conceptions on symptomatology, pathological anatomy, endocrinology and therapy of the syndrome. The author gives a summary of the results of wedge resection of the ovaries for anovulation from 1949 to 1959: of 107 women who were submitted to the operation 54 were restored to an ovulatory cycle. The indications for this operation are discussed.
