N2  - 17alpha-Ethinyl-19-nortestosterone ('norlutin') was given to 6 patients with dysfunctional uterine bleeding due to anovulation in doses of 2.5 mg. daily for 4 days. All experienced withdrawal flow within 7 days, but seemed somewhat delayed. 17alpha-Methyl-19-nortestosterone ('methalutin') was given in 21 cycles to 16 patients, in doses of 2 mg, daily. Withdrawal flow occurred within 6 days after cessation of treatment in all but 2 patients. One patient, with X-ray castration, was primed with oestrogen, then given 2 mg. methalutin for 4 days. Biopsy showed oedema of the stoma and basal vacuolization.
