N2  - The Stein-Leventhal syndrome is characteristically seen in young women of 15-30 yr. with secondary amenorrhoea, infertility, hirsutism, bilateral enlarged and polycystic ovaries and normal 17-ketosteroid and follicle stimulating hormone levels. The author reports 3 cases in which menorrhagia was a symptom and 2 of 87 cases of observed endometrial carcinoma in which the ovaries presented the gross features of the disease.
