T1  - VARIATIONS of ENZYMATIC ACTIVITIES (GOT, AL, LD) in THE HUMAN OVARY under NORMAL and PATHOLOGICAL CONDITIONS (Italian)
A1  - Lo Stumbo F.
A1  - Rio F.
A1  - Serra E.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Under normal conditions, the human ovary shows a considerable increase of aldolase (AL) and lactic dehydr o genase (LD) in pregnancy. After the menopause glutamic-oxalacetic transaminase (GOT) and LD show a marked decrease whereas AL is increased. In cases of polycystic ovary and in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, the enzymatic activities showed a similar behaviour: decrease of GOT and of LD and an increase of AL in cases of neoplasm of the uterus LD was always increased. These findings are discussed in connection with the modifications of the metabolic activity of the ovaries in the conditions considered.
