AN  - 280886769
T1  - THE HISTOLOGICAL STUDY of the TUNICA ALBUGINEA in POLYCYSTIC DEGENERATION of the OVARIES (Italian)
A1  - Fiocchi E.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - In polynnicrocystic degeneration of the ovary a thickening of the tunica albuglnea has often been described. In the ovaries in 4 cases (2 cases of polymicrocy stic degeneration, 1 case with a large follicular cyst, and 1 ovary from a woman in the menopause), a genuine thickening of the albuginea as well as marked hyperplasia of the cortical stroma was present which completely disorganized the normal structure of the cortical layer. The primary follicles had almost completely disappeared and the tunica albuginea itself was of abnormal appearance and hardly recognizable in the first case, owing to an arrangement of the nuclei transverse to those of the sabcaps lila r zone. In the other 3 it formed part of the fibrotic cortical laypr. The presence of an ovarian epithelium could not be observed in any of the cases. It is concluded that the failure of the cystic follicles to rupture is to be attributed not so much to the thickening of the tunica albuginea as to the connective-tissue hyperplasia of the cortical stroma. Camplani - Bergamo.
