AN  - 280788001
T1  - Is there a stein-leventhal syndrome?
A1  - Roberts D.W.T.
A1  - Haines M.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - The authors have studied 21 patients, including 7 with the typical histological findings of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, infertility, irregular periods, and hirsutism; a second group of 7 in whom, in addition to the typical ovarian findings, a corpus luteum was also found; and a control series of 7 patients in the same age group with varying indications for operation. In no case, in any of the groups, was hyperplasia of the theca interna found in cystic follicles. Granulosa cells were present in all cases, and were scanty in only one in group 1 and one in group 2. The uniformity of the ovarian findings in all three groups of cases leads to the conclusion that the Stein-Leventhal syndrome does not appear to be a well-defined entity.
