T1  - Acanthosis nigricans and endocrine disease
A1  - Winkelmann R.K.
A1  - Scheen Jr. S.R.
A1  - Underdahl L.O.
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Of 57 patients seen at the Mayo Clinic between 1935 and 1956 diagnosed as having acanthosis nigricana, 18 patients had associated malignant diseases. Seven patients were considered to have congenital acanthosis nigricans. Twenty-nine cases were diagnosed as benign acanthosis nigricans; 9 of which were associated with endocrine diseases (pituitary adenomas with gigantism, and acromegaly, Stein-Leventhal syndrome, Addison's disease and diabetes). The reports of these 9 cases are given. Obesity was not a constant factor. The sex distribution was equal. Hormonal treatment did not produce a consistent change in acanthosis nigricans.
