N2  - The object of this study was to obtain a correct determination of indications for the treatment of menstrual disorders by prednisone. Administration of prednisone to patients with menstrual disorders is indicated in the following cases: (1) secondary amenorrhoea refractory to bilateral wedge resection of the ovaries; (2) hirsutism associated with anovulatory menses; (3) congenital adrenocortical hyperplasia.
