A1  - Dominguez-Adame
A1  - Cobos M.
Y1  - 1959//
N2  - Virilization in women may have a non-blastomatous ovarian origin. The ovary contains follicular microcysts with associated thecal reaction. In agreement with Plate it is considered that Stein-Leventhal's syndrome and the syndrome of ovarian hyperthecosis are one and the same process, or at least stages in the development of one and the same disease. It is advisable to distinguish between the syndrome of slight adrenal hyperactivity and virilization of ovarian origin. The distinction is difficult but necessary because the treatment is entirely different. The treatment most accepted today is wedge resection of the ovaries. The use of cortisone in these cases still awaits further experience.
