N2  - Description of a case of Stein-Leventhal syndrome which showed an increase in 17-ketosteroida concerning mainly the adrenal peak III (chromatography). The disease was cured by wedge resection of the ovaries. The adrenal gland probably plays an important role in the process. In this case, the adrenal cortex has a specifically genital action and an action on the vascular connective tissue. The ovarian mesenchymal cell appears to be sensitive both to the genital and adrenal hormones. Consequently, Stein-Leventhal syndrome is believed to be related to a disturbance in the enzymatic equipment and to be of congenital origin. Bedrine - Lille (X, 3).
