N2  - Fifty cases of polycystic ovaries with hypertrichosis are discussed and thr psychical factors considered. The hair growth increases in patients with emotional conflicts or in those who feel unprotected. During the psychological examination an anguished state and psychical depression of the patients were noted as well as an unconscious wish to be or to act as a man. These patients were divided into 2 groups. The first was treated with prednisone or prednisolone and in some patients a wedge-shaped resection of the ovaries was performed. In the 2nd group hypnoanalysis was applied, followed in some cases by prednisolone and partial resection of the ovaries. The results obtained with the srcomi group proved to be better than those obtained with the first group. Foix - Buenos Aires (X. 3. 8).
