N2  - Four distinct aetiological factors which cause infertility and which are diagnosable by endometrial biopsy have been presented. These are the anovulatory cycle, endometrial insufficiency, tuberculosis, and unsuspected previous abortion. Among 2000 biopsies taken, 1134 were from patients who underwent complete fertility studies. Eliminating the cases in whom other discoverable factors were found, a residue of 24.8% of the 1134 biopsies revealed the primary cause of the real or apparent infertility. Endometrial biopsy is thus clearly shown to be a most valuable tool in the complete systematic study of the infertile patient.
