N2  - A summary of post coital findings in patients with normal vaginas and those with non-specific infections, and husbands with normal or low semen volumes are studied. Persistently favourable cervical secretion is found in anovulatory cases or delayed ovulation because of persistent oestrinism in which the mucus remains thin for many consecutive days. Vaginal Infections associated with increased pH apparently do not alter the posteoital findings. Low semen volumes probably do not adequately buffer acid vaginal secretions. Stewart - Seattle, Wash.
