N2  - In 12 cases of young women with bilaterally enlarged ovaries and in 5 with only one enlarged ovary, all showing a Stein-Leventhal-like syndrome (without histological confirmation), repeated assays of 17-ketosteroids, 17:21-dihydroxy-20-ketosteroids, pregnanediol and pregnanetriol were done. In 12 cases the response of 17keto- and dihydroxyketosteroids to the i.v. infusion of 20 I.U. of ACTH was measured. Eight patients showed high values of 17-ketosteroids and 3 of these patients responded poorly to ACTH ('basal hyperandrosteroidism'). Two other patients with high 17-ketosteroids showed a high pregnanetriol excretion (adrenogenital syndrome). Hirsutism was more pronounced in patients with high 17-ketosteroid excretion. The convenience of repeated assays of 17-ketosteroids in cases of polycystic ovaries is stressed.
