N2  - Reference is made to 3 cases (hilus-cell adenoma, hypernephroid ovarian tumour, granulosa-cell tumour) and the Stein-Leventhal syndrome is discussed. A distinction is made between the genuine and the pseudo-syndrome. The former is treated by a bilateral wedge resection, the latter by administration of cortisone or prednisone. In the true Stein-Leventhal syndrome, the 17-ketosteroid values are no r ma U but Chromatographie separation reveals a predominance of androsterone and aetiocholanolone. In the pseudo-form of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome the 17-ketosteroid level is at the upper limit of normal, fractionation reveals an increase of androsterone and aetiocholanolone in part of the cases> but also an increase of dehydroepiandroaterone. Chemo-morphological studies of section preparations do not yet permit an unequivocal determination of ovarian androgens. Gruhberger - Vienna (III, 10, 16).
