N2  - Two related cellular systems, both originating from the mesenchyma. viz. the cells of the theca interna in the parenchyma and the cells of the ovarian hilus, can. under the stimulating influence of the luteinizing gonadotrophic hormones combined with that of the cellular enzymes, as well as in certain physiological and pathological conditions, produce androgenic substances. It is possible that certain disturbances of gonadotrophin production or of steroid synthesis are responsible for the hirsutism in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, and these disturbances very probably also cause the symptoms of virilization in patients of the female sex exhibiting Turner's syndrome. (Ill, 10).
