N2  - The theca-cells and the hilus-cells of the ovary are able to produce androgens under stimulation of ICSH and with the cooperation of specific enzymes of the ovary. Changes in the secretion of gonadotrophins and in the biosynthesis of steroids may be responsible for hirstism in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. It is very likely that they are also responsible for the masculinizing symptoms in female determined individuals with Turner-Albright's syndrome.
