T1  - Is there a causal relationship between pathological prenatal stimulation of the ovaries and later menstrual disturbances?
T3  - Bestehen ursachliche zusammenhange zwischen pathologischer pranataler stimulierung der ovarien und spateren regelstorungen?
A1  - Stange H.-H.
A1  - Rumphorst K.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - The ovaries of neonates, born of toxaemic mothers, contained many cystic follicles, haemorrhagic follicles and atretic follicles. There was strong vascular injection, a well developed tunica albuginea and considerable theca-hyperplasia. The cause of this is thought to be the increased titre of chorionic gonadotrophins in toxaemia. It is assumed that such ovaries are permanently injured, thus functioning will be more or less impaired later. In many patients with polycystic ovaries, the mother had had toxaemia during the pregnancy concerned. Several sexually mature women, whose mothers had had a toxaemia also proved to have menstrual disturbances.
