N2  - From the results of wedge-resection of the ovaries in 20 patients with ovarian hyperthecosis, it is suggested that the main causative factor of the disease is not the ovarian changes. A disturbance of the hypophyseal-hypothalamic system is presumed to be of primary importance in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome and to give rise to insufficient production of the 3rd gonadotrophic hormone, the luteo-mammotrophic hormone. In the absence of this hormone no florid corpus luteum develops and this explains the menstrual disorders.
