T1  - A test for ovulation by determining the urinary vitamin C excretion
T3  - Test ovulatorio col dosaggio della vitam. C urinaria
A1  - Massano A.
A1  - Musso G.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - The ovulation test of Fillay, based on quantitative determination of ascorbic acid in the urine after its administration, has been subjected to a control study: in 50 women with a regular menstrual cycle, in 10 women with certainly anovulatory cycles, in 20 pregnant women, in 15 puerperal women, in 5 cases of abortion, in 15 patients with amenorrhoea due to surgical castration and in 5 prepuberal girls. Other examinations were also carried out: basal temperature, vaginal pH, vaginal smear, biopsy of the endometrium etc. Vit. C was administered in doses of 500 mg. from the 10th day after the beginning of the flow until the next cycle. The quantitative determination was carried out by the method of Jetzler and Niederbergher in urine samples collected after 3-6 hr. In the patients with normal menstrual cycles there was always a decrease of the ascorbic acid level of the urine on the 14th-16th day after the beginning of the flow; in the certainly anovulatory cycles and in the prepuberal girls the excretion of vit. C remained constant. A decrease of the level was seen during the first few months of pregnancy, whereas there was an increased excretion of vit. C near and at term. The excretion was diminished during the first few days of the puerperium and in those cases of abortion in which there were still active chorial elements present. The patients with amenorrhoea due to surgical castration were subjected (at 15-day intervals) to treatment with oestrogens, progesterone and LH: it was found that whereas ocstrogens favour the excretion of ascorbic acid, progesterone and LH decrease it.
