T1  - Ergot and the non-pregnant uterus
A1  - Garrell W.J.
A1  - Moir J.Ch.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - The effect of ergot preparations on the intact non-pregnant uterus has been recorded mechanically in 33 cases. In the first half of the menstrual cycle and during anovulatory cycles the only response is a slight increase in uterine tone. In the second half of normal cycles and during menstruation after ovulation, ergometrine induces an Oxytocic effect. There is little evidence to support the use of ergot preparations in the control of haemorrhage from the non-pregnant uterus.
