N2  - The divergences from the normal Diphasic temperature curves and the hormonal factors influencing this phenomenon are discussed. Atypical curves are usually the consequence of anovulatory cycles. In normal, fertile women these represent 2-3% of all cycles. In women younger than 20 yr. (nursing trainees), some 45% of all cycles proved to be anovulatory. It was only in 3% of all recorded cycles that the temperature curve did not make it possible to assess the nature of the cycle.
