Y1  - 1958//
N2  - In 4 patients with secondary axnenorrhoea prednisone administration had no success. In 7 patients with secondary amenorrhoea who previously had been submitted to wedge-excision of the ovaries without success prednisone had effect in 4 cases, m 3 patients with hirsutism and occasional anovulatory bleeding, prednisone caused regular ovulations and one patient became pregnant. In other menstrual disorders it did not meet with success: only in a case of congenital adrenal hyperplasia and in a case of primary amenorrhoea prednisone caused a few anovulatory bleedings. 17-Ketoeteroid excretion diminished in all patients. Out of 12 patients in whom the excretion of gonadotrophic hormones was determined, 10 proved to have no increase during the prednisone treatment, while 2 showed an increase. In 9 patients in whom the oestrogen excretion was determined, once an increase and once a decrease was found; the others showed no appreciable changes in the output. No influence on the cytology of the vagina was found, nor was there an influence of the fern reaction of the cervical mucus.
