N2  - The modifications of the oocytes taken from the ovaries were examined by a personal technique. Not one of the oocytes was normal. The average diameter, measured on the zona pellucida, was 80 mu. The ovular protoplasm showed profound alterations. It had lost its normal spherical shape, being instead semilunar or wrinkled. In the perivitelline space, which was of necessity large, there was amorphous detritus present, originating from processes of cytoplasmatic disintegration. The zona pellucida,on the other hand, was in a perfect state of preservation, and the peri-ovocytary cells could also be regarded as normal, except that they were more widely dispersed than usual.
