N2  - Ncrethynodrel was given to 54 patients who were under treatment for infertility. End omet rial biopsies were obtained on the 25th day of the menstrual cycle before and after treatment. Thirty-four patients received 10 mg. daily from 10 to 20 davs. Twenty patients were given 20 mg. tor 10 Io 20 consecutive days. When medication was started on the 4th day of cycle and continued for 20days, the glands were arrested in the early follicular phase. The glands were lined with either high or low columnar epithelium with minimum secretion. Strom a was cellular with some oedema. There were some haernorrhagic areas. When 10 ing. were given on the 12th to 30th day, the glands arrested at the late proliferative phase became dilated and cystic. The epithelium was flattened. The strcma was oedeinatous. In anovulatory cycles and secondary amen or r hoe a the amount of oedema of strom a and of secretion was influenced by the size of the dose. Some of the anovulatory group ovulated after 2 or 3 months of treatment.
