T1  - The apparent relationship between the Stein-Leventhal syndrome and endometrial carcinoma
A1  - Sorkness J.
A1  - Swenson A.
A1  - Lucy R.E.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - Since 20 yr. it has been known that oestrogens may exert a carcinogenic action. In 1951 C. S. Dockerty reported a relationship between the occurrence of endometrial carcinoma and the Stein-Leventhal syndrome, and again in 1957 he suggested that this relationship may depend upon the amount of oestrogens, secreted by the hyperplastic theca interna of patients with this syndrome. A review of the literature on the syndrome is given and a case with endometrial adenocarcinoma as a late complication is presented.
