T1  - The repudiation of low-dosage irradiation of the ovaries
A1  - Israel S.L.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - The author, for many years a protagonist of irradiation of the ovaries in the treatment of menstrual abnormalities and anovulatory sterility, re-evaluates the gynaecologist's arguments pro and those of the geneticist contra such treatment. He is now convinced of the correctness of the latter's view: 'we cannot help but be persuaded morally to discontinue low-dosage irradiations of the gonads, even if the hazards are theoretical and are minimized by the fact that such therapy is applied to but few women of the world's population'.
