T1  - Meno-metrorrhagia of young girls and their treatment by insulin
T3  - Quelques documents sur les menometrorragies des jeunes filles et leur traitement par l'insuline
A1  - Mathieu J.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - Twenty-four girls of school age were treated for meno-metrorrhagia by insulin (according to Vogt and Cotte) associated with vit. C, vit. K, Ca, transfusion (in 3 cases), curettage (in 7 cases). Three times operation was judged necessary: once hysterotomy for fibroid polyp, once hysterotomy without an objective lesion, once resection of a large cystic ovary. In 11 cases the menstruation became entirely normal. In 9 cases some disturbances of the cycle and of blood loss continued, without really pathological character. In 4 patients treatment failed (twice the hysterography showed a cavity deformed by multiple sub mucous myomas). The majority of menstrual troubles in young girls are functional and good results are obtained in 80% of the cases by prolonged medical treatment after elimination of organic lesions (polyp, sclero-cystic ovary, retroversion of uterus). Insulin is the chief agent of this conservative therapy. Oestrogens are to be reserved for hypoplastic uteri.
