T1  - Juvenile hypothyroidism with precocious sexual development
A1  - Silver H.K.
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - The combination of juvenile hypothyroidism and certain manifestations of precocious sexual development in a girl aged 6 years and 10 months is reported. When first examined, at the age of 7 years and 10 months, urinary gonadotropin was elevated to adult levels and 30% of the cells in the vaginal smear were of the cornified squamous variety. Biopsy of enlarged cystic ovaries disclosed findings similar to those in the ovaries of adults with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome or in response to administration of gonadotropin. The patient became euthyroid during treatment with desiccated thyroid. Although periodic vaginal bleeding then ceased and the vaginal smear no longer contained cornified squamous cells, the enlarged nipples did not regress and increased excretion of urinary gonadotropin continued.
