T1  - Treatment of amenorrhoea and infertility by X-rays by Kaplan's method
A1  - Rabau E.
A1  - Likwornik J.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - Menstrual disorders and infertility have been treated with low doses of X-radiation on a large scale during the past 20 yr. Excellent results as well as failures have been reported. It is not known whether the treatment causes stimulation or destruction of the gland tissue. While it has not been possible to demonstrate stimulation, it is not likely that the small doses of radiation are capable of destructive action in most cases. In 3 cases of Stein-Leventhal syndrome no destructive action whatsoever could be proved. In contrast to many enthusiastic reports, the authors did not get favourable results in 40 cases treated despite correct indications and techniques. Only 3 cases of pregnancy during the first 6 months after radiation were observed, less than the usual incidence of pregnancy in a random series of sterility cases. It therefore is felt that this therapy has acted in the hands of others more as a powerful placebo than by specific action. There are also negative aspects to this treatment. In 3 cases definite climacteric changes occurred in only 1 of which the patient recovered to a certain extent. This treatment must be subjected to further trials before it can be accepted as a satisfactory form of therapy for menstrual disorders and sterility.
