T1  - Histological aspects of the hypophysis in neonates with congenital micropolycystic ovaries
T3  - Aspetti istologici dell' ipo_fisi in neonate con ovaio micropolicistico congenito
A1  - Savi C.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - Findings in cases of congenital micro poly cystic ovaries were applied to the study of the relationships between the anterior lobe of the hypophysis and the ovary. For Interpretation of the histology of the hypophysis, known physiopathological data from the literature were naturally taken into account, and full reliability was assumed for the current methods of determining the various hypophyseal cell-types. The material for this study consisted of 18 full-term foetuses, in 6 of which the ovaries showed follicles with signs of maturation. The hypophyses of foetuses with wholly quiescent ovaries, which were used as controls, showed the presence of all types of cells, with as a rule the following distribution: most of the cyanophil cells were found in the central, lateral and ventro-caudal regions; acidophil cells were found in various arrangements, mostly in the inferolateral regions; between the 2 groups were small chromophobe elements. It is noteworthy that only about 50% of the cyanophil cells reacted positively to fuchsin. In foetuses with micropolycystic ovaries, where the oophoric follicles showed various stages of maturation, there were distinctly more cyanophil s-fuchs in-positive cells. It is concluded that in these cases there is a blocking action against the appearance of cyanophil ofuchsin-negative cells, supposedly originating from extra-foetal gonadotrophins, as the latter type of cell is considered to be the cite of gonadotrophin secretion.
