T1  - Treatment of anovular cycles with progesterone
T3  - Tratamiento de los ciclos anovuladores con progesterona
A1  - Bonilla F.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - Seventy-three cases of sterility, of which 50 with anovular cycles and 23 due to corpus luteum deficiency, were treated with 10 mg. of progesterone on the 16th, 19th and 22nd day of the cycle. The total dose of 30 mg. was not exceeded in any case. In the 42 cases in which the results were controlled, 14 pregnancies (33%) were observed. Intolerance to the drug remained practically reduced to slight articular pains, elevation of temperature of 0.3 to 0.4, and to haemorrhages due to hormonal deficiency, which was the most frequent phenomenon and was observed in 28.5% of the cases. In view of the simplicity of the method it is believed that this drug should be tried in all cases of sterility of ovarian origin.
