N2  - Fifty-eight patients with micropolycystic ovaries were studied after wedge resection Forty were observed during variable periods up to 6 yr. 75% were cured and 42% became pregnant. The clinical picture, the preoperative examination of the endometrium and the histology of the partially removed ovary make it possible to prognosticate sterility in these patients. Those patients presenting metrorrhagia, glandular hyperplasia in the endometrium and those whose partially removed ovary does not present ovulation scars have an unfavourable prognosis.
