N2  - In a series of 80 sterile women, a single vaginal smear was taken on the 24th-26th day of the cycle. On the same day, endometrial biopsy was obtained and pregnanediol was estimated in the urine. In 61 cases, the vaginal smear was of the ovulatory type and corresponded in 85.4% with the other tests. Histology failed in 8.3%, while cytology failed in only 2.8%. In 14 cases, the smear was of the anovulatory type. Among these the endometrium was proliferative in 9 cases, secretory in 4, but in only one case of the latter was pregnanediol present in the urine. In one case, the endometrium did not permit any conclusion (tb endometritis), but pregnanediol was present. The authors believe that the single vaginal smear can be applied on a large scale.
