T3  - Steinuv-leventhaluv syndrom
A1  - Kucera F.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - The author reviews 26 operated cases. All of them had anovulatory or irregular bleeding; in 69% menstruation became regular after operation, 34% became pregnant. The main cause of this syndrome is a disturbance of receptivity of the ovary with cessation of ovulation, and, in consequence of this, an upset neuro-hormonal balance between ovary and hypophysis. The author stresses the progressive character of the syndrome, which may lead to premature menopause, and, in some cases, to cancer of the body of the uterus.
