T1  - Observations on the polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Keettel W.C.
A1  - Bradbury J.T.
A1  - Stoddard F.J.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - Thirteen patients suspected to have polycystic ovaries were given F.S.H. i.m. for 6 days. In all but one, marked enlargement of the ovaries occurred. Controls consisted of (1) 15 patients aged 18 to 30 yr. in whom eugenic sterilization was to be performed. The ovaries in 10 of these revealed no change and in 5 slight enlargement due to 2 to 4 cystic follicles was observed; (2) 11 patients presenting various gynaecological problems in whom no enlargement of the ovaries could be detected at the initial examination. None of these evidenced increase in ovarian size following administration of F.S.H., and (3) 10 pregnant or parturient among whom 8 revealed no ovarian enlargement; in 1 slight increase occurred, and in 1 there was marked enlargement. In 10 of 11 patients with polycystic ovaries, L.H. excretion in the urine was elevated. It is proposed that assay of L.H. in the urine and a course of F.S.H. injections offer diagnostic aids in suspected cases of polycystic ovaries.
