T1  - How should the so-called Stein-Leventhal syndrome be defined?
T3  - Comment definir le syndrome dit de Stein-Leventhal?
A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Lambert A.
Y1  - 1957//
N2  - After the numerous variants which have been introduced into the original conception and which have led to a certain confusion are recalled, an attempt is made at classifying the Stein-Leventhal syndrome among the more general heading of ovarian dystrophies. It is proposed that the following signs be necessary for the diagnosis: permanent oligomenorrhoea, with, at least once a year, a cycle of more than 30 days; ovulation becoming rarer and rarer (not more than 3 per yr.); firm and smooth ovaries, of a fairly constant volume; ineffectiveness of cortisone and its derivatives; spontaneously progressive nature of the syndrome; onset of the disturbances before the age of 20; the finding of white, smooth and pearly ovaries on operation or on coelioscopy. This tentative definition is undoubtedly praiseworthy, but its arbitrary and probably transitory nature should be recognized.
