T1  - Some observations on the human myometrial cycle
A1  - Garrett W.J.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - Uterine activity has been recorded by an intrauterine balloon method in 62 normal women (80 records) and in 6 women having anovulatory cycles. Rapid feeble contractions or A waves, recorded throughout the menstrual cycle, show a marked increase in frequency at the time of ovulation. Other slower and much more powerful uterine contractions or B waves were also recorded in the course of normal menstrual cycles. The B waves arose independently of the rapid A waves and were only seen in the post-ovulatory period and during ovulatory menstruation. The evidence to date suggests that the A-wave activity is under oestrogenic control, whereas B-wave activity is governed by progesterone.
