A1  - Mundi F.E.
A1  - Scarella C.A.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - Twelve cases of sclero-cystic ovaries (Stein-Leventhal syndrome) are analysed. The authors stress the fact that in 6 cases recent corpus lutea were found at operation and in the other cases signs of old luteinization were common. This agrees with the frequent clinical finding of signs of incomplete progestational effect on the basal temperature and on the endometrium and lead the authors to include in the syndrome every case of enlarged polycystic ovaries with no signs of ovulation or with incomplete progestational effect. Other symptoms were: amenorrhoea in 11 cases, pelvic pain in 11 cases, sterility in all married patients, obesity in 6 cases and virilism in 7. The 17-ketosteroids were normal or slightly elevated (up to 16 mg. per 24 hr.). Diagnosis of the ovarian enlargement was not made on clinical examination but on the findings of pneumogynaecography. No relation was found between clinical picture and the results of wedge resection which were excellent in 6 cases, fair in 3, and poor in 3.
