A1  - Cooke W.R.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - The author has treated 33 cases of endometriosis by massive stilboestrol dosage. In all cases cyclic pain was relieved. In all cases only actual cysts and some fixation of organs by adhesions could be palpated after 3 months of treatment. Eight of the 33 patients have each borne a child since. Six of these patients had never before been pregnant. Diagnostic criteria for endometriosis are presented, and the technique of the massive stilboestrol treatment is given.
