N2  - The arguments for and against irradiation of the human ovaries are presented. An analysis of the results obtained with low dosage irradiation of the pituitary and ovaries in 104 patients is presented. Of 88 married, completely treated, followed patients, 46 became pregnant and 22 more ovulated but did not become pregnant. Fifteen patients either became amenorrhoeic or remained so. Illustrative case reports are presented.
