N2  - Study of 70 patients, using skin biopsy, blood smears and oral smears. The blood smears were often difficult to interpret. In pseudohermaphroditism the genetic sex correlates with the gonads present. In true hermaphroditism the chromatin pattern may be either male or female. Cases of ovarian agenesis frequently show male genetic sex. Of 4 cases of polycystic ovaries (Stein- Leventhal syndrome) 3 showed male genetic sex. In ail other endocrine syndromes the genetic sex corresponded with the differentiation of the gonads and not with the somatic picture. References 40. Pinto - Buenos Aires.
