A1  - Do Amaral Ferreira C.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - A discussion of the therapeutic effects of X-ray stimulation of the hypophysis and the ovaries in cases of ovulatory disturbances and the literature up till now is presented. The cure rates vary between 50 and 100% in cases of amenorrhoea and from 30 to 70% in the cure of sterility. Statistical data on endometrial biopsy are presented. Of 47 cases studied 19 cases had anomalous ovulation and 28 were anovulatory. Among these, 35 received hormonal therapy; the disturbances of ovulation were corrected in 7 cases, with 3 subsequent pregnancies (20%); 14 were submitted to X-ray stimulation of the pituitary and ovaries of which 6 patients began to ovulate and 4 became pregnant (21.4%). The 4 pregnancies following X-ray stimulation are summarized.
