T1  - Regeneration of the human endometrium after labour
T3  - La regeneration de l'endometre humain au cours du post-partum
A1  - Vokaer R.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - In more than 500 patients, the regeneration of the endometrium post partum was studied by endometrial biopsy. In the first stage (1st to 5th day) a new surface epithelium develops from the remnants of the glands. In the next stage (5th to 25th day), there is a proliferation of glands and stroma; the cells show mitoses. These changes are not due to hormonal influences: no oestrogenic stimulation is demonstrable in the vagina. Only in the 3rd stage (25th-45th day) is the influence of hormones noticeable and has the function of the ovary begun. If there is no lactation, the normal menstrual cycle reappears after the 45th day. If there is lactation, the endometrium remains inactive. In some cases, anovulatory or ovulatory cycles may develop.
