A1  - Clavero Nunez A.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - A review is given of the histories of 294 married patients who came for consultation before they had been married for one year; 9.5% were found to be normal. There was impediment to insemination in 6.1%; 12.9% had gynaecopathies (myoma, endometriosis, etc.) and 4.4% genital tb; 9.3% presented a male factor, 9.1% an ovarian factor (anovular cycles) and 33.3% only a cervical factor. It is considered that the causes of primary conjugal sterility are approximately the same qualitatively and quantitatively, whatever may be the time at which they are discovered. Many are present before marriage (genital tb, anovulatory cycles, azoospermia, etc.). It is believed that no time should be indicated at which the study of sterility in marriage should be started.
