A1  - Scebba G.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - Report on a case of Brenner tumour in a large pseudomucinous cystadenoma of the ovary, in a woman aged 72 yr. The problem of the relationship between the 2 ovarian neoplasms is discussed, and it is stated that the pseudomucinous cysts frequently found in the vicinity of a Brenner tumour are not the product of muciparous differentiation of the Brenner epithelium or of regressive cytolytic phenomena, but of the simultaneous twofold development, paramalpighian and pseudomucinous, of the undifferentiated cells which constitute the tumoral matrix. The Brenner tumour therefore has a dysontogenetic nature. It is assumed that both ovarian formations are due to neoplastic proliferation of pluripotent embryonal elements of the mesodermal blastema genetically connected with the primary coelomic epithelium.
