N2  - Report on 2 sisters aged 24 and 20 yr., respectively. The elder had menstruated from the menarche (at the age of 16) at approximately 6 months' intervals. Since one year she has menstruated every month after progesterone treatment. She had a good libido, but no orgasm. Since puberty she has had hypertrichosis on arms, legs and face. 17-Ketosteroids: high-normal. FSH excretion: normal. Other hormone metabolites: no peculiarities. A wedge-shaped resection of both ovaries was carried out, approximately one-fourth of the ovarian tissue being removed. There were multiple small follicular cysts and marked hyperplasia of the theca with luteinization. After the operation ovulations occurred again (vaginal smears and biphasic basal temperature curve). On account of slight hypothyroidism the patient was given thyroid powder. The patient thinks that the hirsutism has somewhat decreased. The younger sister presented the same symptoms. (Another 2 sisters had normal menses and no hypertrichosis.) Also in this patient there were no marked disorders in the excretion of FSH and 17-ketosteroids. In this case too, a wedge-shaped resection of the ovaries was carried out, three-fourths of the ovarian tissue being removed. The findings and therapeutic result were the same. Only, no change was noticed in the hypertrichosis.
