Y1  - 1956//
N2  - Report on 2 cases of endometriosis, the first in an appendicectomy scar, the second in an ovary. In both cases the ectopic endometrium revealed cyclic changes characteristic for the proliferative phase. There were haemorrhages and shedding of the epithelium, but no secretory activity was found. This would point to an anovulatory bleeding (monophasic cycles) in these endometrium islands. In a third case there was an ectopic endometrium within the uterine wall (adenomyosis) in a 62-year-old climacteric woman. The glands in the endometrium islands showed the typical picture of glandular-cystic hyperplasia.
