T3  - Anovulationens klinik och behandling
A1  - Bergman P.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - A survey is given of anovulation of hypophyseal and ovarian genesis illustrated with examples of its varying clinical picture: regular anovulatory cycles, metropathia haemorrhagica cystica (MHC) and amenorrhoea. In the department of gynaecology in Malmo treatment of cases of MHC in patients below 45 yr. consisted first of curettage, which in 35% of the cases resulted in a normalization of the menstrual time-table. When curettage produced no result or only a temporary effect, the patients were treated cyclically with chorionic gonadotrophin (as a rule 1500 I. U. daily for 3 days in succession). Of 110 patients treated with gonadotrophin, 99 responded with ovulation. About half of them had recurrences on withdrawal of treatment. Among the 11 patients refractory to chorionic gonadotrophin therapy, 2 had granulosa cell tumours (ovarian function restored after the tumour was removed), 3 showed Stein-Leventhal's syndrome (normalized after wedge-resection of the ovaries), 1 had hypothyrcidism (normalization after thyroid therapy), and 5 who passed through the menopause during the following 6 months. Of the 361 women with MHC, 29 were married, childless and below 40 yr. of age. Fifteen of them became pregnant (after curettage, chorionic gonadotrophin therapy, operation for granulosa cell tumour or Stein-Leventhal syndrome or thyroid therapy).
