N2  - Oestrogens are not merely dependent on the F.S.H.; the relation F.S.H./oestrogens is variable. Preponderance of F.S.H. causes anovulation and stimulation of the follicle of de Graaf. Some experiments are discussed, in which hypo-oestrogenism caused cystic degeneration of the ovaries; when the equilibrium is not too much disturbed, addition of some oestrogen may reestablish the relation F.S.H./ oestrogens, which results in ovulation and formation of a corpus luteum. Cyst formation might be an attempt to restore the hormonal relations.
