N2  - In a 13-year-old patient, who received high doses of serum and chorionic gonadotrophins an acute abdominal condition occurred due to rupture of ovarian corpora lutea. The syndrome of a too strong stimulation of the ovaries by serum and chorionic gonadotrophins is discussed (abdominal tension, mild pain in the lower abdomen and enlargement of the ovaries, symptoms which may get worse and may lead to rupture of greatly enlarged polycystic ovaries). All patients treated with gonadotrophins should be kept under observation as the hyperstimulation depends on the sensitivity of the ovaries and not on the amount of gonadotrophins. At the slightest symptom of alarm, treatment should be discontinued.
