T1  - Induction of ovulation with progesterone in various forms of anovulatory cycles
T3  - Die auslosung der ovulation durch progesteron bei den verschiedenen formen der anovulatorischen blutung
A1  - Rus W.
Y1  - 1956//
N2  - Thirty-five women in whom studies over a period of 6 months had constantly revealed anovulatory cycles were given progesterone with a view to inducing ovulation. A distinction is made between a primary form (delayed menarche, constant anovulatory cycle without known cause) and a secondary form (initially normal cycle, then, after a delivery or abortion, or after a psychic trauma, anovulatory cycles). On the last day of the haemorrhage 20-30 mg. depot-progesterone were administered and, depending on the pre-ovulatory peak, on the 8th day 30-35 mg. more. Five of the 14 women with the primary form and 16 of the 21 with the secondary form developed a biphasic cycle, (controlled by basal temperature, endometrial biopsy and Douglasscopy). Six of the women became pregnant.
