N2  - Out of 443 cases of hypertrichosis in women, obesity was observed in 40%; 70% of these had menstrual disturbances. The principal changes were polycystic ovaria (25%). The 17-ket oster old s were found to be increased in 56.7% of the patients; 16% had struma. The combination adrenal hyperfunction - ovarian disturbances - obesity - struma is sufficiently common to think of a hypothalamic connection. It is not known whether obesity has a purely endocrine origin or is due to a disequilibrium of the balance, caused by an increase in appetite.
