N2  - A concise description is given of the somatic, hormonal and psychological characteristics of puberty and of the various aetiological forms of retardation. Reference is made to delayed puberty due to nutritional disturbances, to lesions of the CNS and of endocrine origin. The latter may be due to lesions of the ovary (agenesis, masculinizing tumours, sclerocystic ovariitis), to hypothyroidism, to hypophyseal disturbances (hypophyseal insufficiency or hypophyseal hyperactivity of puberty) or to adrenal hyperplasia.
