T1  - Ovarian function following interruption of pregnancy
A1  - Nishijima G.
A1  - Saito J.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - The resumption of menstruation following spontaneous abortion and artificial termination of pregnancy has been observed. A total of 256 abortions induced mainly for social and economic reasons showed a variation in the length of the first post-abortal cycle according to the duration of pregnancy at the time of interruption. After abortion in the first trimester the average length of the first menstrual cycle was 40 days, in the 2nd trimester about 50 days and in the 3rd, 65 days. There appeared to be no correlation between these figures and the length of the progestational cycle. It is considered that three quarters of these post-abortal cycles were ovulatory and only one quarter anovulatory.
