T1  - The histological structure of the ovary in cases of virilism
A1  - Westman A.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - The author has analysed the histological structure of ovaries in 2 series of cases: one with menstrual disturbance associated with hirsutism and virilization (15 cases) and another without symptoms referable to an endocrine lesion (21 cases). In the latter series the patients were operated on on account of follicular cysts, oophoritis or polycystic ovaries. Hypertrophic theca cells were found in 7 cases of the former series and in 8 cases of the latter. The findings do not support the view that an increase in the number of theca cells is the primary cause of menstrual disturbance associated with virilism.
