T1  - Post-partum amenorrhoea
T3  - Postpartale amenorrhoe
A1  - Sas M.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - In 11 post-partum cases after cessation of breast feeding and also in 4 post-abortum cases there was a period of amenorrhoea lasting from 3 to 13 months. There were no clinical symptoms nor anamnestic data suggesting pituitary hypofunction (Sheehan's syndrome). Hormone assays showed a normal excretion of FSH, oestrogen, and 17-ketosteroids. There was no pregnanediol excretion in the urine. Thus the cause of amenorrhoea was a deficient production of LH due to the lack of impulses from the hypothalamus. The treatment with chorionic gonadotrophins (500 I. U. daily for 10-15 days) was successful in establishing an anovulatory bleeding at first and a regular menstrual cycle later on.
