A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Lambert A.
A1  - Aschheim P.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - Most women with excessive 17-ketosteroid excretion have scanty and irregular periods or anovulatory cycles as determined by endometrial biopsy or basal temperature. This applies not to anovulatory cycles at puberty, premenopause and in the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. Five sterility cases have been treated by cortisone after failure of other methods and resulted in pregnancy. Only oral treatment was used, 1st week 75 mg., 2nd and 3rd week 50 mg., further 25 mg. Prolonged treatment seemed useless. The mechanism of action is discussed.
