N2  - Based on the lower pressures obtained during the luteal phase in normal patients as well as the decrease in frequency and amplitude of the contractions tubal insufflation was performed during the entire cycle of patients with sterility due to anovulation. Anovulation was confirmed in all 42 patients by endometrial biopsy. In spite of the lack of luteal hormone all studies revealed a lower pressure and decrease in frequency and amplitude of the contractions during the second half of the cycle, In cases of cystic hyperplasia of the endometrium no increase in pressure and motility was recorded.
