T1  - Pneumocography as an aid in the diagnosis of gynecologic disease
A1  - Abrams B.S.
A1  - Hughes A.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - Contraindications to the injection of gas into the peritoneal cavity are the presence of inflammatory disease or a pelvic tumour completely filling the pelvis. The patient's bowel and bladder are emptied and about 800 to 1,000 ml. of carbon dioxide are injected through the abdominal wall. The procedure was used in 161 instances where the patient was awaiting pelvic surgery for various indications such as uterine or adnexal tumours, ectopic pregnancy, and cystic ovaries. There was a high degree of correlation between the pre-operative diagnosis and the actual pelvic findings. The authors find the method helpful in stout patients where bimanual examination is inconclusive. The procedure is a safe one and is an adjunct in the diagnosis of gynaecological disorders.
