N2  - In several cases of Turner's syndrome marked psychological benefits had been observed under oestrogen therapy. Breast development, growth of pubic and axillary hair, maturation of the external genitalia and the occurrence of regular periods produced psychic changes as these women began to regard themselves as normal. In a 27-year-old patient, whose case history is described, a dramatic response occurred under combined hormone and psychotherapy. The author was convinced that most of the improvement was produced by the oestrogens, but could not exclude the positive value of a good transference.
