T1  - 'Micronized' stilboestrol and vitamins in the treatment of endometriosis
T3  - Endometriosis. Tratamiento con stilbestrol micronizado y vitaminizado. Nuevo aporte preliminar
A1  - Karnaky K.J.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - Report on 75 cases treated with 'micronized' stilboestrol (combined with daily administration of vitamins), the dosage being progressively increased to 100 mg. daily, divided into 4 doses of 25 mg. When haemorrhage or metrorrhagia occurred during treatment, 2-4 tablets containing 25 mg. of oestrogens were given every 15 min. until the haemorrhage had been controlled. Some patients required 150-400 mg. to continue in a condition of amenorrhoea. When oestrogens have been administered over a sufficient period, it is advisable to reduce the dosage as follows: 3 tablets of 25 mg. one night, 2 the next, then 1 tablet, 3/4, 1/2, 1/4, and finally, discontinue treatment. Administration of vitamins and a diet including large quantities of vegetables, which contain a large amount of folic acid, are essential. In the event of nausea or vomiting, nembutal suppositories or 0.5 g. of pentolin are given every one or two hours. Sour milk is useful in controlling toxic reactions.
