T1  - Medical treatment of complications of unilateral ovariectomy
T3  - Le traitement medical des troubles de l'ovaire unique
A1  - Boulard Cl.
A1  - Gautray J.P.
A1  - Pecollo H.D.
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - Complications of unilateral ovariectomy may be hypomenorrhoea, hypermenorrhoea, dysmenorrhoea, menometrorrhagia, sterility and frigidity. They are attributable to disturbance in the relationship between the hypophysis and the ovary. If the remaining ovary is normal, there are no disturbances, and after a transient period of hyperactivity it shows normal function. Nevertheless, many unilateral ovariectomies are carried out for 'sclerocystic ovaritis', in which case the other ovary is not normal either, with consequently a disturbed relationship between the hypophysis and the ovary. The therapy of these complications should be aimed at the restoration of normal hypophyseal-ovarian relationships, for which purpose combined treatment with para-oxypropiophenone, gardenal, largactil, thyroxine, choline derivatives, ultrashort-wave irradiations and physiotherapy can be used.
