N2  - A description is given of the macroscopic and microscopic features of a case showing an enormous lymphangioma of the skin, occupying the left half of the body of a 2-month-old female infant since birth. Cysts of similar histological structure were found at autopsy in the descending colon and the transverse colon; there was also a cystic ovary and the bronchopulmonary lymph nodes and the para-aortic retroperitoneal lymph nodes showed cystic changes. The neoplasm was interpreted as a generalized malformation.
