T1  - Sterility and ovarian pathology
A1  - McGoogan L.S.
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - The mechanisms producing sterility in various pathological conditions of the ovary are surveyed. Ovarian pathology contributes only a small percentage of the overall causes of sterility. A review of the literature disclosed that endometriosis and bilateral polycystic ovaries occurred in 5.9% of sterility cases. This percentage was 3.7% in the author's practice. A plea is made for more accurate studies in which all the factors of the sterility problem are evaluated. In the author's evaluation 10% of the women operated upon for bilateral polycystic ovarian disease became pregnant, as did 68.9% of those with pelvic endometriosis. Following surgery for ovarian endometriosis, 55% of the patients became pregnant.
