T1  - New data on luteal function in infertility and habitual abortion
T3  - Donnees nouvelles sur l'exploration de la fonction luteale dans la sterilite et les avortements a repetition
A1  - Jayle M.F.
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - Apart from progesterone the corpus luteum secretes other hormones, as is shown by Hooker-Forbes' serum test, e.g. 2-dehydroprogesterone, which is twice as active as progesterone. However, the corpus luteum also produces oestrogenic substances, which play an important part in the development of the fertilized ovum before and after nidation. The determination of the metabolites of the oestrogens should be completed by that of the 17-ketosteroids. The androgenic function of the adrenal cortex may interfere in the ovarian cycle. Hyperandrogenism may be the cause or the result of the disturbance of the luteal function or it may cause abortion in the beginning of pregnancy. In the urine the content of 3alpha-steroids, pregnanediol, 17-ketosteroids, creatinine and oestrone can be determined. As regards the influence on the endometrium, the function of the corpus luteum is normal if with a secretory type of endometrium a normal content in oestrous substances and catabolites is found. Insufficiency of the oestrogenic function of the corpus luteum is a significant factor in endocrine abortion. Luteal insufficiency may be due to a disturbance in the trophoblast, and is rarely the cause of endocrine abortion. In some cases there is a probable relationship between endocrine sterility and insufficient production of oestrogenic substances by the corpus luteum, Adrenal hyperandrogenism is also a factor which has to be borne in mind in patients with habitual abortion.
