T1  - A case of Stein-Leventhal's syndrome
T3  - Sindrome de Stein-Leventhal. Apresentacao de um caso
A1  - Gomes K.
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - This case was observed in a virgin aged 20 and was characterized by menstrual disorders (at first irregular bleeding, than hypomenorrhoea), hypertrichosis and polycystic ovaries. As the treatment with oestrogen did not produce favourable results, resection of the ovaries was performed with the removal of about one half of each ovary. Normal menstruation was established but the hypertrichosis persisted. The histological examination of the removed ovarian tissue confirmed the diagnosis of polycystic ovaries. It is suggested that the cause of hypertrichosis in this syndrome is extra-ovarian.
