A1  - Netter A.
A1  - Henry R.
A1  - Thevenet M.
A1  - Maschi
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - Six cases of 'hyperandrogenic' amenorrhoea of which 4 with hypertrichosis, one with acne, 3 with a masculine habitus and 1 with hypertrophy of the clitoris were studied. The vulva and uterus were normal in all cases. The vaginal smear was not regressive. Urinary gonadotrophins were normal. A study of the 17-ketosteroids indicated that they are of gonadal and not of adrenal origin. Therefore, besides hyperandrogenism from adrenal origin (adrenal tumours, functional hypercorticism) there is a hyperandrogenism from ovarian origin which may be due to polycystic ovaries, The treatment consists in administrations of cortisone or wedge-resection of the ovaries.
