T1  - Disturbances of menstruation and pulmonary tb
T3  - Alteraciones menstruales y tuberculosis pulmonar
A1  - Di Paola G.
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - Sclerocystic ovaries are frequently observed in pulmonary tb, Amenorrhoea is the most frequent disturbance in these cases, especially at the onset of the disease or during a progressive attack, Amenorrhoea usually is due to failure of the follicles to mature completely, which leads to brief monophasic cycles, There is a sustained but slight oestrogenic action and no uterine haemorrhage occurs, as the oestrogenic stimulation is unable to cross the threshold of endometrial response, Menstruation has an adverse effect on the course of the tb, Tb endometritis may be either follicular, with tubercles disseminated in a functioning endometrium, or caseous, with complete destruction of the endometrium, In the former case menstruation may be normal or be absent, while amenorrhoea, caused by destruction of the endometrium, may occur in the latter case.
