N2  - Stress is laid on the selection of the cases, the fundamental indication being the anovulatory cycles in which hormonal treatment has failed. One should make sure that there is no pregnancy. Sexual abstinence for 3 months after. Patients under 17 and over 37 yr. of age should not be irradiated. Fortysseven observations are presented, divided as follows: oligomenorrhoea: 28, with 90% of good results; amenorrhoea for more than 3 months: 13, with 17% of good results. In sterility 50% of good results, with 28 parturitions and 5 abortions.
