T1  - Psychogenic sterility
T3  - Psychogene sterilitat
A1  - Stauder K.H.
A1  - Tscherne E.
Y1  - 1953//
N2  - The authors deal with the hormonal side of the question and report 7 cases of sterility in women, who have lost a child during delivery or by accident. Genital findings were normal, but the basal body temperature curves showed anovulatory cycles. These can be ascribed to the influence of the severe psychic trauma upon the production of gonadotrophins. Treatment with gonadotrophic hormones caused ovulatory cycles and pregnancy in 4 cases in connection with the treatment and in 2 cases after it. In 7 cases, in whom gynaecological treatment yielded no success, psychoanalytic treatment showed that the cause of sterility was of psychic nature and pregnancy followed after psychotherapy. The psychic trauma after the loss of a child, excessive attempts to become pregnant, hatred against the husband, incestuous relations and neurotic attitudes and repressed feelings lead through the hypophyseal-diencephalic system to hormonal disturbances which cause sterility. The need for co-operation between gynaecologists and psychoanalysts is stressed. If the organic causes of sterility in the women are eliminated and the fertility of the male partner is verified, the psychiatrist should be consulted as soon as possible, and psychic therapy will then be successful.
