N2  - The authors point out the frequency of functional disorders, mainly in young women, following the removal of a healthy ovary. In cases of cystic ovaries medical treatment must always be tried first; in case of failure, partial surgical removal is indicated in young women, and complete bilateral ovariectomy in patients beyond 40 yr. of age. In order to prevent recurrence of cyst-formation, testosterone, which inhibits production of gonadotrophins, may be administered.
