N2  - A study of the effects of low-dosage irradiation in 40 women with long-standing anovulatory infertility which had been resistant to other forms of treatment for a period of 2 yr. or more. Twenty patients received treatment to the ovary alone, and 20 received both ovarian and pituitary irradiation. The clinical and laboratory results were similar in both groups with improvement in ovarian function occurring in 55% of the 1st group and 60% in the 2nd and with pregnancy resulting in 35% of each group.
