T1  - Hyperoestrinic polyadenomatosis
T3  - Polyadenomatose hyperfolliculinique
A1  - Herschberg A.-D.
Y1  - 1953//
N2  - The author again draws attention to the high incidence in individuals with hyperoestrinism of multiple adenomata affecting selectively the uterus (fibromyomata), the mammary gland (eyetic fibroadenomata) and the thyroid (simple or cystic adenomata). Among 642 cases of hyperoestrinism of less than 5 years' duration 14 instances of double adenomatosis were observed, while among 389 patients with hyperoestrinism of more than 5 years' duration there were 116 cases of double and 42 cases of single adenomatosis. It would appear that cystic conditions of the breast are the first to manifest themselves. Before the 20th year mammary cysts are most commonly encountered; from the 20th to the 35th year double adenomatosis occurs, generally affecting the mammary gland and the thyroid; triple adenomatosis is met with after the 35th year. With the desire to protect patients from operations which are often useless, the author points out that the treatment of polyadenomatosis is the treatment of the hyperoestrinism. With improved modern knowledge of these conditions the prognosis should permit of radical revision and operative treatment should be limited to sclerocystic conditions of the ovary.
