T1  - Results of anaesthetic block of the superior cervical ganglion in certain forms of female sterility
T3  - Resultats de l'infiltration du ganglion cervical superieur dans certaines formes de sterilite chez la femme
A1  - Pirard P.E.
Y1  - 1953//
N2  - The superior cervical ganglion effects innervation of the anterior lobe of the pituitary and vasomotor regulation of the hypothalamus by means of direct efferent pathways. Anaesthetic infiltration of the ganglion causes vasodilatation in this region and changes in the secretory activity of the anterior pituitary. Five cases of sterility treated by this method are presented; in all 5 the infiltration was followed by a pregnancy. The result is ascribed to stimulation of ovulation in women who had anovulatory cycles.
