T1  - Progesterone metabolism I. Pregnanediol excretion in the menstrual cycle
A1  - Fischer R.H.
A1  - McColgan S.P.
A1  - Chaney A.L.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - Free pregnanediol was determined by the Chaney and McKee method in 6 normal women during a normal menstrual cycle. Individual 24 hr. urine specimens were collected without preservative. Two of the cycles observed were apparently anovulatory. The amount of pregnanediol excreted during a cycle varied from 0 to 49.8 mg. with maximum excretion on the 7th or 8th day prior to the next menstrual flow. Disappearance of pregnanediol varied from 4 days before the onset of flow to after the flow, began. In this series no material deviation from the original report of Venning and Browne was noted.
