T1  - Hormonal treatment of the non-secretory cycle of the endometrium
T3  - Palackeho uni.v v olomoucil k hormonalni lecbe asekrecniho cyklu endometria
A1  - Vasek V.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - The author proposes to use the term 'non-secretory cycle' instead of 'anovulatory cycle' as the latter expresses only one of the possible causes of the absence of secretion in the endometrium. Even large doses of gonadotrophin (pregnyl 24,000 rabbit units) and agolutin (140 mg.) are not able to provoke ovulation and to transform the proliferation phase into a secretory phase. Further experiments are contemplated to investigate if this is caused by the refractoriness of the endometrium in the reported cases or whether agolutin does not contain a sufficient amount of progesterone.
