T1  - Histological study of the ovary in the last four months of foetal life. Reconsideration of the problem of endocrine activity of the ovary in the first months of intra-uterine life
T3  - Estudio histologico del ovario en los cuatro ultimos meses de la vida fetal. Revision del problema de la actividad endocrina del ovario durante los primeros meses de la vida intra-uterina
A1  - Rodriguez-Soriano J.A.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - Opinions differ as to the functions of the foetal gonad. The various ideas on the differentiation of the genital tract are subjected to criticism and the following points are discussed: (1) Differentiation of the genital tract under the influence of hormones produced by the already-differentiated gonad; (2) differentiation of the gonad under the influence of the foetal adrenal cortex, regarded as the 3rd gonad (Botella Llusia); (3) differentiation of the genital tract as a result of the action of genetic factors. Histological examinations of gonads, endometrium and cervix of 6-, 7- and 9- month foetuses are reported; these showed histological activity of the ovary in the 6th month, with obvious follicle maturation reaching the graafian follicle stage with differentiation of granulosa and theca cells. In 1 case polycystic ovaries were observed, with follicles bulging out the surface of the ovary; 1 follicle had haemorrhagic contents. In no case could any sign of atretic corpora lutea be found. In 1 case the endometrium was frankly haemorrhagic (this was the same case that showed polycystic degeneration of the ovary). As a general rule the endometrium was only slightly developed and glands were vestigial or non-existent. The cervix was lined with high vaginal epithelium.
