N2  - With 6 to 15 applications (according to the rate of improvement; usually 12) at 1. 5-2 watt/sq. cm. with a duration of 5-10 min., given on alternate days, favourable results were obtained in cases of n on-inflammatory affections which had failed to improve with short-wave therapy. Particularly good effects on the symptoms of sclerocystic ovary were observed. The treatment was given without reference to the day of the menstrual cycle, this being a matter of indifference as no menstrual disturbances were caused.
