T1  - Carcinoma of the oviduct and vaginal smear
T3  - Tubarkarzinom und Scheidenabstrich
A1  - Clauss J.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - In a patient aged 57 yr. with haemorrhages and lower abdominal pain the vaginal smear showed highly atypical cells. Cervical and endometrial biopsy were negative. A cystic ovary and hydrosalpinx were removed. The histological picture was that of a medullary, gland-forming carcinoma originating from the oviduct. Another case discussed is that of a patient aged 50 yr. subjected to laparotamy on account of a positive vaginal smear with an adnexal tumour. A secondary tubal carcinoma was found, with a primary in the ovary. The importance of vaginal smear findings for identification of primary or secondary tubal carcinomas is emphasized.
