Y1  - 1952//
N2  - The determination of alkaline phosphatase in the blood serum is of no importance either for an early diagnosis of ovarian tumours or as an indication regarding correct therapeutic measures. In the autolysates of ovarian tissues affected with benign and more especially malignant tumours and in pol y cystic ovaries, the quantity of alkaline phosphatase considerably exceeds chat found in corresponding normal tissues. Histochemicai tests tor alkaline phosphatase were found to be more markedly positive in the lining epithelium, the vascular endothelium, the cells of the theca interna and the corpus luteum, the interstitial and the tumour cells, i.e. in all those constituents in which cell metabolism is most intense. This increase in alkaline phosphatase is attributed to the increased requirement of free P. which is essential to the function and reproduction of these cells.
