N2  - When part of an ovary has been removed because of cystic changes, the function of the remainder depends on the pituitary-ovarian interaction. When this is defective, as e.g. in sclerocystic ovaries, the result of conservative surgery will be poor. If the cyst is of wolffian origin, no relapse is to be expected when part of the ovary is left behind.
