T1  - Treatment of sterility resulting from anovulatory menstruation
A1  - Siegler S.L.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - The author investigated 953 involuntary sterility patients from 1946-1950. Fifty-five patients (or 5.77%) were diagnosed as having anovulatory menstruation. The pathogenesis, diagnosis, and treatment of this entity are reviewed. Diagnostic criteria for anovulatory menstruation are presented, and the methods and importance of aetiological differential diagnosis considered. Various therapies (hormonal, irradiation or surgical) and their results are discussed in detail. No method of treatment was entirely satisfactory; but irradiation of the pituitary and ovaries, with 80% success in initiating ovulation, proved most effective. Forty-four of the 55 patients developed ovulatory cycles; 27 pregnancies resulted in 23 term deliveries.
