T3  - Estudio de la cristalizacion del moco cervical
A1  - Guerrero Allande J.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - This phenomenon was studied in 6 women with normal and 2 with anovulatory cycles, 4 with sterility and ovarian endocrine disturbances, 2 with amenorrhoea and 14 in various stages of pregnancy. In the normal cycles, few crystals were observed in the first few days; from the 7th to 9th day the crystals began to increase in number and at the time of ovulation they became very numerous, giving the characteristic 'fern leaf' appearance. After ovulation the crystal formation decreased. In the anovulatory cycles, crystals were present throughout the cycle and became more numerous just before menstruation. Few crystals were present in oestrogenic insufficiency and none in amenorrhoea and pregnancy.
