T1  - Regulation of the menstrual cycle after irradiation of the spleen - A gonadotrophic function?
T3  - Die zyklusregulierung nach milzbestrahlung - Eine gonadotrope funktion?
A1  - Wagner H.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - A number of non-pregnant women with hypermenorrhoea were subjected to irradiation of the spleen with X-rays (110 r.). Where the cause of the hypermenorrhoea was endometritis, the bleeding usually ceased and the cycle then proceeded normally. Where glandulocystic hyperplasia was present, however, the bleeding ceased in 2/3 of cases and then, after a certain latent period, cyclic haemorrhages reappeared, but these were shown histologically to be not true menstruation but anovulatory bleeding. Urinary gonadotrophin determinations showed no increase above 40 m.u. after irradiation. It is believed that irradiation of the spleen with this dosage does not affect the production of ovarian hormones, either directly or via the hypophysis.
