T1  - Evaluation of thyroid in the treatment of sterility
A1  - Jarvis G.L.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - Basal body temperature is the most satisfactory means by which the average physician can determine the presence of and approximate the time of ovulation. Anovulatory cycles and cycles with an inadequate progestin phase may be present in patients with normal basal metabolic rates as well as in the hypothyroid patient. Desiccated thyroid, 55 mg. daily, will correct the abnormalities of anovulatory cycles and inadequate luteinization in many patients. Thyroid probably has no effect on patients with sterility due to pituitary defects or with primary gonadal defects.
