T1  - A theory to explain anovulatory cycles
A1  - Roland M.
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - A theory to explain anovulatory cycles assumes inactivity of the factor which normally inhibits the growth of small follicles aside from the one destined to become a graafian follicle. Secretion of oestrogens by too many follicles reaches the peak of concentration early and FSH is prematurely inhibited. The balance of FSH and LH is therefore disturbed and the graafian follicle is not completed. Small doses of X-rays or resection of part of the ovary would reduce the number of follicles and re-establish the hormonal balance.
