N2  - The series consisted of 268 sterile Egyptian women whose basal temperature recordings were charted. As judged by the temperature curves the cycles were occasionally or permanently anovulatory in 94 (35.07%) of the patients. Only in a few cases was endometrial biopsy done to verify the diagnosis. Of these 94 patients 88 were treated with either 'synapoidin' or equine gonadotrophic hormone, sometimes in combination with thyroid extract. Synapoidin induced a definite biphasic temperature curve in 78.9%. Fquine gonadotrophin produced a similar result in 50.7%. Seventeen (19-3%) of the 88 patients treated became pregnant.
