N2  - Nineteen cases of haemoperitoneum are reported as being due to rupture of corpus luteum. Although rupture of corpus luteum is not an uncommon condition it was rarely diagnosed before surgery. The following diagnoses were made before laparotomy: appendicitis, ectopic gestation, cystic ovary and endometriosis. Ovarian haematoma may be caused by rupture of corpus luteum or rupture of a follicle, the former rupture usually occurring during the 2nd half of the menstrual cycle and the graafian follicle ruptures usually during the mid-interval period.
