A1  - Dujovich A.
A1  - Sapisochin E.
A1  - Tynjanker J.
Y1  - 1951//
N2  - The object of this operation is to restore functional normality of the endocrine system: hypophysis-endometrium-ovary, where its disturbances have a morbid anatomical basis of polycystic ovary (dysplastic; sclerocystic) or 'large white ovary' with irregular surface covered with small cysts and a thickened, hard, whitish and unyielding interstitial tissue. Operative correction leads to improvement of the circulation previously impaired by oedema or sclerosis causing tension of the albuginea. The operation gave good results in 69 cases of functional disturbances, some without evident gynaecological lesions (in which this was the only treatment) and some with such lesions (in which this was combined with other measures). In the majority of cases improvement occurred in the menstrual disturbances (with or without somatic, trophic and degenerative signs of gonadal origin). Operation is indicated where medical treatment has failed.
