T1  - The excretion of pregnandiol during the menstrual cycle
T3  - Vylucovani pregnandiolu u menstruacniho cyklu
A1  - Zenisek L.
Y1  - 1951//
N2  - The author studied the excretion of pregnandiol in 11 cases, in which a monophasic curve of basal temperature was registered. All the cycles became biphasic. The excretion of pregnandiol continued for 7-13 days. The maximal daily excretion was 1.8-5.4 mg., the average amount 2.1 mg. The author claims that in a case of biphasic curve of basal temperature and the excretion of pregnandiol in the urine there need not result a complete change of the endometrium into the secretory phase. The author discusses characteristic signs of ovulation, the decreased sensitivity of the endometrium to progesterone, the insufficiently developed corpus luteum and the anovulatory cycle.
