T1  - Carcinoma of the corpus uteri in young women
A1  - Dockerty M.B.
A1  - Lovelady S.B.
A1  - Foust Jr. G.T.
Y1  - 1951//
N2  - Of 1,691 patients with carcinoma of the body of the uterus treated surgically at the Mayo Clinic from 1905 through 1944, 36 (2.1%) were less than 40 years of age. Seven of these patients exhibited features of the Stein-Leventhal syndrome (polycystic ovaries, menstrual irregularity, and sterility). In the other young patients obesity with sterility, hypertension and occasional hirsutism and diabetes often occurred. Twenty-six of the endometrial tumours were adenocarcinomas and the other 10 were adenocanthomas. The existence of chronic hyperoestrogenism is suggested as a high incidence of associated fibromyoma, myohypertrophy, endometrial hyperplasia, and cervical glandular hyperplasia was also found.
