T1  - Polycystic ovaries
T3  - Contribucion al estudio de los ovarios poliquisticos
A1  - Salazar Santos R.
Y1  - 1951//
N2  - The pathogenesis of polycystic ovaries is as follows: Some cause, which may change the ovariau nutrition or acute and chronic infections, or mechanical and vascular changes, produces a sclerosis of the superficial layer of the ovary; in this case the maturing follicles are prevented from rupturing and become encysted. When a sufficiently large number is encysted, this causes a hyperoestrogenaemia, which will inhibit the FSI:, resulting in a definitive change in the hormonal relations, which are even more disturbed by the lack of ovulation, the absence of the corpus luteum and the complete endometrial and genital changes. Treatment is surgical: uni- or bilateral wedge resection of the ovaries. Favourable results are repotted in 38 cases,.
