Y1  - 1951//
N2  - True, non-infective sclerocystic ovaritis may simulate an inflaramatory affection, being accompanied by a rise of temperature, increased FSR, and presence of a pelvic mass. When such signs appear after an abortion or birth they are extremely decertive and resemble those of adnexitis. The only distinctive feature is the sudden regression - or on the contrary the extremely rapid increase in volume of the pelvic mass which soon appears. If regression does not occur it may be necessary to perform, jupcture or even surgical intervention if the usual medical treatment fails. These ovarian disorders are probably due to a disturbance of the functions of the floor of the 3rd ventricle. This article is based on 21 cases, only 2 of which are reported in detail.
