T1  - Sexual precocity in females. Report of two cases, with arrest of precocity in the McCune-Albright syndrome after removal of a cystic ovary
A1  - Pray L.G.
Y1  - 1951//
N2  - A girl aged 51/2 years, with development of secondary sex characteristics and vaginal bleedings, had cafe-au-lait spots. She was treated by removal of the enlarged left ovary, containing 2 large luteinized follicular cysts and numerous primordial follicles. Following surgery, the secondary sex characteristics subsided, returning 11/2 yr. later. Roentgenographic examination then led to a diagnosis of polyostotic fibrous dysplasia (McCune-Albright syndrome). She is now in good health. A girl of 3 years of age had vaginal bleedings occurring at monthly intervals for 4 months. There was general obesity and development of secondary sex characteristics. The output of gonadotrophins, oestrogens and 17-ketosteroids was somewhat increased. Exploratory laparotomy confirmed the diagnosis of constitutional type of sexual precocity. The findings in both patients are briefly discussed.
