T1  - Large ovarian cyst in a newborn infant
A1  - Kunstadter R.H.
A1  - Schultz A.
A1  - Strauss A.A.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - A female infant aged 4 days was found to have a mass in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen. At 32 days laparotomy was performed and an ovarian cyst - 10 x 9 x 6 cm. - was removed together with the right fallopian tube. Recovery followed. Histological examination showed the tumour to be a follicular cystic ovary. The importance of early diagnosis and removal of abdominal tumours in infancy is stressed, because of the incidence of malignancy. Most solid tumours are malignant: most cystic ones benign. As it may be difficult to differentiate between tensely cystic and solid masses by abdominal palpation, laparotomy is always indicated and should not be delayed.
