AN  - 280532389
T1  - Werlhof's disease and pregnancy
T3  - Ziekte van Werlhof en zwangerschap
A1  - Dauvillier P.W.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - A case of Werlhof's disease diagnosed in a 24-year-old II-para at term is reported. The first pregnancy had ended with the birth of a full-term, dead child, after a haemorrhage of 3 days' duration. The second child was born spontaneously and in good condition and showed a normal blood picture. A comprehensive review of the literature on the combination of Werlhof's disease and pregnancy is presented. The problem of coincidence versus toxaemia or hormonal disturbance is discussed. The possibility of a hormonal disturbance is emphasized in the light of thrombocyte counts (normally menstruating women usually show a cyclic variation of the thrombocyte count). Further investigations (on pregnant women; those with high concentrations of one or other hormone; those with an anovulatory cycle and no progesterone production; postoperative patients who still have one ovary; cases of agenesia and those of menorrhagic purpura) will be required to confirm this hypothesis.
