T1  - Studies of metropathia haemorrhagica cystica. A clinical investigation with special rejerence to treatment with chortonic gonadotrophin
A1  - Wahien T.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - A review of the 563 cases of metropathia haemorrhagica treated at the above mentioned clinic, including a study of the hormone excretion and the basal temperature curve in many cases. 20 cases developed symptoms in connection with the menarche, in 30 patients they were connected with the puerperium after delivery or abortion, in 30 patients they were connected with the puerperium after delivery or abortion, in 206 275 Patients the bleeding was associated with the climacterium, 4 were in the menopause, and in 28 the disease had appeared after oestrogenic medication. Thus the majority of the cases had got their bleeding anomaly in connection with one of the physiological anovular periods at menarche, puerperium, and climacterium. For the origin, of anovulation during the fertile period the following factors seemed to be of importance: disease or operation reducing the ovarian substance, diseases affecting the general condition, and mental disturbances. Chorionic gonadotrophin had little or no effect on the anovulation at the menarche, puerperium or menopause but a very good effect in almost all cases in the fertile period.
