AN  - 280533150
T1  - Functional diagnosis and hormone therapy in some forms of amenorrhoea
A1  - Krimskaja M.L.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - For the proper treatment of amenorrhoea, the functional diagnostics of the neurohypophyseo-ovarian system are of the utmost importance. They comprise the following clinical and laboratory tests: (1) the grade of development of the sex organs and secondary sex characteristics, (2) the 'pupillary' phenomenon, (3) vaginal cytology, (4) endometrial biopsy, (5) ability of the endometrium to react with a menstrual-like bleeding on introduction of 150,000-300,000 M.U. of oestrogens and 30-50 mg. of progesterone, (6) determination of urine gonadotropins, oestrogens, pregnandiol and 17-ketosteroids. Treatment was the administration of both oestrogens and progesterone to stimulate the ovaries so that they, in turn, would stimulate the complicated neuro-reflectory system over the neuroreceptor organs, and would serve as substitution therapy. From the results in 55 cases with primary and secondary amenorrhoea, it is concluded that oestrogens and progesterone can stimulate the ovarian activity as well as the development of sex organs and secondary sex characteristics. In a few instances a regular ovarian cycle was obtained, but in most cases only anovulatory bleeding. The results were least favourable in cases of secondary amenorrhoea of precocious climacterium type.
