T1  - Encephalo-cutaneous angiomatosis. Clinical and pathological study of a case of Sturge-Weber-Dimitri syndrome
T3  - Angiomatose encefalocutanea. Estudo clinicopatologico de um caso de S. Sturge-Weber-Dimitri
A1  - Elias Neder J.
A1  - Capriglione L.A.
A1  - Barreto Netto M.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - An oligophrenic subject with encephalo-trigeminal angiomatosis showed convulsive attacks and bilateral buphthalmos. Radiography revealed diffuse calcifications of the left cerebral hemisphere, which were denser in the parietal and occipital lobes. Endocrine examination revealed pluriglandular deficiency (hypophyseo-diencephalic, thyroid, adrenal and gonadal). Pathological examination showed cerebromeningeal angiomatous malformations, calcification of the blood vessels and cortical cells and calcareous granules in the spinal meninges. Calcareous formations were also found in the eyeballs. The endocrine findings were: persistent thymus; adrenal hypoplasia; cystic ovaries; increased size of the thyroid; hypophysis of small size and covered by angiomatous formations. The severe endocrine lesions probably played a part in the aetiology, while the possibility of a hypophyseo-diencephalic origin deserves consideration.
