T1  - Ovarian hirsutism
T3  - Hirsutisme van ovariele oorsprong?
A1  - Stokhuyzen A.W.
Y1  - 1950//
N2  - In a 25-year old hirsute woman an exploratory laparotomy was performed which revealed enlarged ovaries with a thickening of the tunica albuginea and numerous follicular cysts. (Stein-Leventhal). The hypophysis was found enlarged on the roentgenogram, the excretion of FSH was markedly increased (100 U.). Increased production of androgens was revealed by increase of the 17-ketosteroids (22.9 mg). In this patient ovulatory bleeding might occur without ovulation itself, from secretory endometrium under the influence of progesterone produced by luteinized theca interna cells.
